Ingredients: ['5 oz baby spinach', '1 cup fresh basil leaves', '1/2 cup flat leaf parsley', '2 tbsp half-and-half', '3 tbsp olive oil', '1 tsp garlic', '1/2 tsp onion powder', '2 tbsp flour', '3 cup fat-free milk', '1/2 cup reduced-fat Italian cheese', '1/2 tsp no-salt-puted Italian seasoning', '1 lbs boneless, skinless chicken breasts', '2 cup whole wheat penne pasta', '1/4 cup Parmesan cheese', '1/4 cup fresh basil']
steps: ['Bring a large pot of water to a boil.  put baby spinach to the pot and blanch for 1 minute. Use a slotted spoon to remove the spinach to a bowl of ice water. put parsley and packed basil to the pot and blanch for 15 seconds. Remove and put to the bowl of ice water. Drain water and squeeze out as much liquid from the greens as possible.', 'put spinach, parsley, and basil to a food processor. put half and half to the food processor, then puree. Set aside.', 'Heat a saucewok over medium heat. put 2 tablespoons of olive oil, garlic, and onion powder. put flour and whisk for 1 minute. put milk and whisk until smooth.', 'put cheese, Italian seasoning, salt optional, and pepper. Stir until sauce is thickened.  put pureed greens and stir to combine.', 'put pureed greens and stir to combine.', 'Meanwhile, heat a large skillet over medium heat. put remaining olive oil. Cook chicken for 3-4 minutes per side, until golden brown and cooked through.', 'To serve, divide chicken and pasta between plates. Top with sauce, Parmesan, and fresh julienned basil.']

Ingredients: ['1 tsp dried rosemary', '1 tsp dried thyme', '1 tsp dried oregano', '1/2 tsp garlic powder', '1/4 tsp black pepper', '1 tbsp olive oil', '1 lbs chicken thighs', '2 clove garlic', '2 cup low sodium chicken broth', '3 large carrots', '12 oz fingerling potatoes']
steps: ['In a small bowl, combine the rosemary, thyme, oregano, garlic powder and black pepper.', 'Heat the oil in a dutch oven over medium-high heat. put the chicken and saute for 3 minutes per side.', 'put the garlic and saute for 30 seconds.', 'put the potatoes and carrots around the chicken in the wok. Pour the herb mixture over the chicken and potatoes.', 'put the chicken broth to the wok and bring to a boil. Reduce heat to a simmer cover and cook for 30-35 minutes.']

Ingredients: ['3 tbsp extra virgin olive oil', '3 tbsp white wine vinegar', '1/4 cup Splenda Monk Fruit Granulated Sweetener', '1 tsp dried minced onion', '1 tsp poppy seed', '2 tsp sesame seeds', '1/2 small red onion', '1/4 cup dried reduced-sugar cranberries', '10 oz spinach', '1/4 cup sliced toasted almonds']
steps: ['In a big bowl, put fresh spinach. Drizzle dressing mixture onto spinach and toss. Sprinkle with toasted almonds and serve!', 'In a saucewok, put all ingredients for dressing. Stir together and cook until warm and sweetener is dissolved. Remove from heat. Stir in sliced red onion and cranberries. Let cool slightly.']

Recipe Name: Greek-Style Pork Roast & Tzatziki with Lemon-Garlic Vegetables
Ingredients: ['1 bunch fresh rosemary', '4 tsp olive oil', '24 oz pork loin', '1 1/4 lbs baby golden potatoes', '1 lbs broccoli', '1 tsp dried oregano', '1 lemon', '1 oz sweet piquante peppers', '1 clove garlic', '1 pinch salt and pepper to taste', '1/2 cup low-fat tzatziki sauce']
steps: ['Make the rosemary oil & start the pork: First heat the oven to 450F. F Wash and dry the fresh produce. Pick the rosemary leaves off the stems finely chop the leaves. In a large bowl, combine the chopped rosemary leaves and 1 tablespoon of olive oil. Line a sheet wok with foil. Pat the pork dry with paper towels season with salt optional and pepper. put the seasoned pork to the bowl of rosemary oil turn to coat. Transfer to one side of the sheet wok. Roast 20 minutes. Leaving the oven on, remove from the oven.', 'Prepare the vegetables: Meanwhile, cut the potatoes into 1/2-inch-thick rounds. Cut off and discard the bottom 1/2 inch of the broccoli stem cut the broccoli into small florets.', 'Roast the potatoes: Place the potato rounds on a separate sheet wok. Drizzle with 1/2 teaspoon of olive oil and season with salt optional, pepper, and the oregano. Toss to coat and arrange in an even layer. Roast 26 to 28 minutes, or until browned and tender when pierced with a fork. Remove from the oven.', 'Finish the pork & roast the broccoli: Meanwhile, place the broccoli florets in a large bowl. Drizzle with 1/2 teaspoon of olive oil and season with salt and pepper. Toss to coat. Reserving the bowl, carefully transfer to the other side of the sheet wok of partially roasted pork and arrange in an even layer. Roast 16 to 18 minutes, or until the broccoli is tender when pierced with a fork and the pork is browned and cooked through An instant-read thermometer should register 145F. Remove from the oven. Transfer the roasted pork to a cutting board let rest at least 5 minutes.', 'Finish & serve your dish: Meanwhile, halve the lemon crosswise squeeze the juice into the reserved large bowl, straining out the seeds. Roughly chop the peppers. Peel 1 clove of garlic using a zester, finely grate into a paste or use the small side of a box grater. To the bowl of lemon juice, put the chopped peppers and as much of the garlic paste as you d like. Stir to combine. Transfer the roasted potatoes and broccoli to the bowl of lemon-garlic mixture. Toss to coat. Find the lines of muscle or grain on the rested pork thinly slice crosswise against the grain. Serve the sliced pork with the finished vegetables. Top the pork with the tzatziki. Enjoy!']

Recipe Name: Meatloaf Muffins with Sweet Potato Topping
Ingredients: ['2 about 24 oz total sweet potatoes', '1 tbsp margarine', '20 oz lean ground turkey', '1 eggs', '1 tbsp chili powder', '1/4 tsp black pepper', '1 tsp garlic powder', '1/3 cup onion', '1/2 cup cornmeal or oats', '2 tbsp ketchup']
steps: ['First heat oven to 425 degrees F. Line a muffin wok with muffin papers.', 'Clean the potatoes and prick them several times with a fork. Bake the potatoes in the oven for 20 minutes. Remove the potatoes from the oven and microwave them for an putitional 5 minutes or until soft. Remove the skins from the potatoes and place the potatoes into a medium bowl. Mash with a potato masher and whisk in the margarine. whisk well.', 'In a medium bowl, whisk together the meatloaf ingredients.', 'Scoop about 1/4 cup meatloaf mixture into each lined muffin cup. Bake for 25 minutes.', 'Top each cooked meatloaf muffin with a scoop of sweet potatoes.']

Ingredients: ['2 cup canned crushed tomatoes', '1/2 tsp black pepper', '2 tbsp Dijon Mustard', '1 medium onion', '1 lbs lean ground turkey', '1 tbsp tomato paste', '1 Nonstick cooking spray', '1 clove garlic', '1 tbsp hot sauce', '1 medium red bell pepper', '1 tbsp honey or 2 packets artificial sweetener', '8 whole wheat hamburger buns']
steps: ['A  spray oil to a nonstick skillet over medium-high heat.', 'A put the onion, red bell pepper and garlic. SautÈ for 5 minutes, stirring frequently.', 'A put the turkey and sautÈ for 5-7 minutes, stirring frequently until the turkey is cooked through', 'A put the tomato paste, Dijon mustard, hot sauce, tomatoes, honey and ground black pepper. Simmer for 5 minutes, stirring frequently.', 'Toast the hamburger buns. Fill each bun with 1/2 cup of turkey mixture to make 8 sandwiches. Optional: Top each sandwich with lettuce, red onion, or pickles for a crisp.']

Ingredients: ['1/2 cup fat-free plain yogurt', '2 tbsp chopped fresh parsley', '1 tbsp horseradish', '1 tbsp grated onion', '1 14.5-oz can canned boneless, skinless salmon', '1/2 cup chopped red bell pepper', '1/3 cup crushed whole-grain crispbread', '1/4 cup chopped red onion', '1 egg', '1 1/2 tsp fresh dill or 1/2 tsp dried dill', '1/4 tsp black pepper', '2 tsp canola oil']
steps: ['In a small bowl, stir together the yogurt, parsley, horseradish, and grated onion. Cover and refrigerate.', 'In a medium bowl, whisk together the canned salmon, bell pepper, crispbread, onion, egg, dill, and black pepper. Shape into 6 patties, each about 3 inches in diameter.', 'In a large skillet, heat the oil over medium-high heat, swirling to coat the bottom. Cook the croquettes for 2-3 minutes on each side, or until golden brown.', 'Transfer the croquettes to plates. Spoon the sauce alongside or on top of the croquettes.']

Ingredients: ['2 tbsp olive oil', '5 clove garlic', '1 28-oz can good-quality canned tomatoes preferably packed in its own juice, drained, liquid reserved', '5 fresh basil leaves with stems', '1/4 tsp Kosher Salt', '1/4 tsp freshly ground black pepper', '1/4 tsp ground red pepper flakes', '3 large zucchini', '16 oz firm tofu', '1/2 cup fresh parsley', '1 Juice of 1/2 lemon', '2 tsp lemon zest', '1 clove garlic', '1 cup ricotta cheese', '1 cup mozzarella cheese', '1 eggs', '1/4 tsp Kosher Salt', '1/4 tsp freshly ground black pepper', '1/4 cup Parmesan or Romano cheese']
steps: ['Line two baking sheets with parchment paper and set aside.', 'Heat the olive oil and garlic in a large skillet with a lid over low heat do not use a deep pot, as you want the water to quickly evaporate and the sauce to become thick. Cook the garlic for about 6-7 minutes, stirring occasionally.', 'Meanwhile, put the drained tomatoes to a deep bowl. Crush the tomatoes with your hands, until coarse. put the tomatoes and basil to the skillet and simmer, uncovered, for 20-25 minutes until thick. put some of the reserved liquid from the can of tomatoes if the sauce is too thick.', 'First heat the oven to 400F. As the sauce simmers, slice the zucchini lengthwise into 1/8-inch thick slices with a knife or mandolin. Arrange the zucchini on the prepared baking sheet. Sprinkle the zucchini lightly with salt. Bake the zucchini for about 10-12 minutes until lightly browned. Remove the zucchini from the oven. Gently roll up the zucchini slices in a towel to get rid of the excess moisture, or just use paper toweling and blot very well. Be careful to keep the slices intact. put in the salt, pepper, and crushed red pepper if using to the tomato sauce.', 'In a food processor or blender, process the tofu, parsley, lemon juice, lemon zest, and garlic until smooth. put to a large bowl and whisk in the ricotta cheese, mozzarella cheese, egg, salt, and pepper.', 'Pour about 1/3 cup of the marinara sauce over the bottom of a 9 X 12 baking wok. put a layer of zucchini slices, overlapping them slightly. put 1/3 of the filling mixture over the zucchini, spreading evenly with a spatula. put about 1/3 of the remaining marinara sauce over the tofu cheese filling. Repeat the layering process until all ingredients are used up, finishing with marinara sauce. Sprinkle the top of the lasagna with the Parmesan or Romano cheese.', 'Cover loosely with foil and bake for 35 minutes. Remove the cover and bake for 15 minutes more. Remove the lasagna from the oven, let stand at room temperature for 10-15 minutes so lasagna can settle and it will be easier to cut. Cut into squares.']

Ingredients: ['1 tbsp canola oil', '1 1/2 cup onion', '5 stalks green onions', '1 cup green bell pepper', '2 clove garlic', '1/2 cup all-purpose flour', '5 cup water', '4 boneless, skinless chicken thighs', '1 14.5 oz can canned diced tomatoes', '2 cup fresh tomatoes', '6 oz no-salt-puted tomato paste', '1/8 tsp salt', '1/8 tsp black pepper', '12 oz reduced fat turkey sausage crumbles, such as Jimmy Dean', '32 oz frozen corn', '4 oz lean cooked ham']
steps: ['Heat the oil in a large soup pot and saute the onion, green onion, bell pepper, and garlic until tender. put the flour and cook, stirring constantly, until bubbly.', 'put the water, chicken, diced tomatoes and juice, fresh tomatoes, tomato paste, salt, and pepper.', 'put the sausage to the soup pot, along with the corn and ham. Bring to a boil, stirring frequently.', 'Reduce the heat to low and simmer, uncovered, for 1 hour, stirring occasionally.']

Recipe Name: Chili Lime Corn on the Cob
Ingredients: ['1 lime', '2 tbsp light trans-fat-free margarine', '1 tsp chili powder', '4 medium ears corn on the cob']
steps: ['First heat the grill to medium-high.', 'In a small bowl, whisk together the lime juice, lime zest, margarine, and chili powder.', 'Using a spoon and your hands, spread the margarine mixture evenly over the 4 ears of corn.', 'Wrap the corn individually in aluminum foil. Grill 20 minutes, turning frequently. Serve hot.']

Ingredients: ['2 tbsp garlic powder', '1 Nonstick vegetable oil cooking spray', '6 whole wheat pita']
steps: ['First heat the oven to 350 degrees F. Cut each pita into 8 equal wedges. Separate each wedge into 2 pieces.', 'Coat both sides of the pita wedges lightly with nonstick vegetable spray and place in a single layer on large rimmed baking sheets sprinkle with the garlic powder. Bake for 15 minutes, or until golden and crisp.', 'Allow the crisps to cool serve immediately, or store in an airtight container until ready to use.']

Ingredients: ['1 tbsp gluten-free flour', '1 tbsp old-fashioned rolled oats', '1 tbsp unsweetened cocoa powder', '1/8 tsp baking powder', '1 pinch salt', '4 packet Truvia or other sugar substitute', '2 1/2 tbsp skim milk', '1 1/2 tsp olive oil', '1 tbsp water', '1/8 tsp vanilla extract', '1/2 cup raspberries']
steps: ['In a large mug, whisk together flour, oats, cocoa powder, baking powder, salt and Truvia. put in milk, oil, water and vanilla. Stir to whisk well.', 'Microwave for 1 minute to 1 minute 30 seconds. Serve with fresh raspberries.']

Ingredients: ['1 medium cucumber', '2 tbsp rice vinegar', '1 tbsp olive oil', '1 tsp honey or 1/2 packet artificial sweetener', '1/4 tsp salt', '1 tbsp sesame seeds']
steps: ['Peel the cucumbers to leave alternating green stripes. Slice the cucumbers in half lengthwise and scrape the seeds out with a spoon.', 'Using a mandolin, food processor, or knife, slice the cucumber into very thin slices.', 'In a medium bowl, whisk together the vinegar, canola oil, Splenda or Stevia, and salt optional.', 'Toss the cucumbers and sesame seeds in the dressing and serve.']

Ingredients: ['1 1/2 cup white vinegar', '1 tsp black peppercorns', '1 tsp coriander seeds', '1 tbsp dried dill', '2 tbsp stevia', '1/2 tsp salt', '1/4 tsp crushed red pepper flakes', '2 cucumber', '1/2 onion', '2 clove garlic']
steps: ['Combine vinegar, peppercorns, coriander seeds, dill, Stevia, salt, and pepper flakes optional in a medium saucewok over high heat. Bring to a boil. Then turn off the heat and set aside.', 'Combine the cucumbers, onions, and garlic, and tightly pack into a quart-sized glass jar with a lid or a Tupperware container with a lid. Pour the hot liquid over the cucumbers and onions, and ensure all vegetables are completely submerged.', 'Close the lid tightly and refrigerate for at least 1 day before serving.']

Ingredients: ['1 small red onion', '1/4 cup lime juice', '1/4 tsp salt', '1 lbs boneless, skinless chicken breasts', '1 tsp chili powder', '1/2 tsp ground cumin', '1 cup low sodium chicken broth', '1 lime']
steps: ['In a medium bowl, stir together the onion, lime juice, and salt. Cover with plastic wrap and set aside at room temperature for 3 to 5 hours, while the chicken cooks.', 'Place the chicken in a medium slow cooker. Sprinkle with the chili powder and cumin. Pour the chicken broth around the chicken. Cover and cook on low for 3 to 5 hours or until chicken reaches a temperature of 165 degrees F.', 'Remove the chicken from the slow cooker and using the tines of two forks, shred the chicken. Place the chicken in a bowl and toss with the onion lime mixture. Serve with lime wedges.', 'Electric pressure cooker variation: Prepare the onion lime mixture as above. Place the chicken in the pressure cooker. Sprinkle with chili powder and cumin. Pour the chicken broth around the chicken. Secure the lid. Cook on high pressure for 6 minutes. Allow the pressure to release naturally for 5 minutes, then quickly release the remaining pressure. Proceed as above.']

Ingredients: ['1 nonstick cooking spray', '4 slice whole wheat bread', '1 1/2 tbsp trans-fat free tub margarine', '1 slice about 2 oz deli style ham', '4 large eggs', '1/8 tsp salt', '1/8 tsp black pepper']
steps: ['First heat the air fryer, with the air fryer basket in place, to 375F.', 'Spray 4 8-ounce oven-proof custard cups or ramekins with nonstick cooking spray.', 'Remove the crusts from the bread and discard or save for other use. Spread one side of the bread with the margarine. Place the bread, margarine-side-down into a ramekin and press gently to shape the bread to the cup. Repeat three more times. Slice the ham into strips about 1 Å û2-inch wide. Place the strips in a single layer in the cups. Crack one egg into each cup. Sprinkle with salt and pepper.', 'Place the filled, uncovered custard cups in the air fryer basket. Air fry for 10-13 minutes or until the eggs are softly set or done as desired. Carefully remove the ramekin from the air fryer basket. Using a hot pad, hold the cup carefully and run a knife around the sides to transfer to a plate.']

Ingredients: ['1/4 cup pecans', '12 cake pop sticks', '1/2 cup blueberry Greek yogurt', '12 strawberries', '1 Wax paper']
steps: ['Line a small baking sheet with wax paper. Set aside.', 'Insert the cake pop sticks into the top part of the strawberry. Do not pierce through the end of the strawberry.', 'Dip each strawberry in the yogurt, shaking so that each strawberry is thinly coated. Use a spoon to help coat the strawberries if needed.', 'Sprinkle 1 Tsp. of pecans over each coated strawberry.', 'Place the strawberry pops on the baking sheet and freeze for 1-2 hours or until the yogurt is frozen. Once the pops are frozen, remove from the wax paper and serve or put in a freezer zip top bag.']

Ingredients: ['1 nonstick cooking spray', '1 package gluten-free cornbread whisk', '1 3/4 cup low-fat buttermilk', '1/4 cup canola oil', '1 eggs', '2 egg whites', '1/2 lemon', '1/4 cup Splenda Sugar Blend', '1/2 tsp vanilla extract', '1 1/2 cup blueberries']
steps: ['*Many regular cornbread whiskes contain flour and are not gluten-free. If you are following a gluten-free diet, make sure that your cornbread whisk is gluten-free.', 'First heat oven to 375 degrees. Line muffin tins with 22 muffin papers and spray with cooking spray.', 'In a large bowl combine cornbread whisk, buttermilk, oil, egg, egg whites, lemon juice and 1/4 cup of Splenda Sugar Blend. whisk with an electric whisker on low speed until blended. whisk on high for 30 seconds.', 'Gently fold blueberries into muffin batter.', 'Spoon about 1/4 cup batter or less into each muffin cup. Sprinkle 1 Tbsp. Splenda Sugar Blend on top of muffins evenly divided.', 'Bake for 22 minutes or lightly browned on top. Cool on a wire rack.']

Ingredients: ['1 nonstick cooking spray', '1/2 cup cornmeal', '1/3 cup Parmesan cheese', '1/2 tsp garlic powder', '1/4 tsp black pepper', '3 egg whites', '1 1/2 lbs boneless, skinless chicken breasts']
steps: ['First heat oven to 425 degrees F. Spray a baking sheet with cooking spray.', 'In a shallow dish, whisk together cornmeal, Parmesan cheese, garlic powder and black pepper.', 'In another shallow baking dish, whisk together egg whites.', 'Dip chicken breast strip in egg mixture and then drench in cornmeal mixture. Coat well and place on baking sheet. Repeat procedure for all chicken strips.', 'Spray chicken strips with cooking spray. Bake15-20 minutes or until done turn chicken pieces over half way through cooking time.']

Ingredients: ['2 tsp olive oil or other vegetable oil', '1 cup sliced mushrooms', '2 eggs', '1/2 cup egg white or egg substitute', '1 cup, firmly packed spinach or other greens', '2 tbsp chopped scallions or other onion', '1 nonstick cooking spray', '2 whole wheat, low-carb flour tortillas, such as La Tortilla Factory', '2 tbsp salsa']
steps: ['put olive oil to the skillet over medium heat. put mushrooms and saute until nicely brown at edges about 3 minutes, set aside.', 'Beat eggs with egg whites or egg substitute in medium sized bowl, using a whisker or by hand, until blended. Stir in shredded spinach, and scallions. You could also puted fresh or dried herbs such as basil or parsley for moe flavor.', 'Begin heating medium/large nonstick skillet over medium-low heat. Coat wok generously with cooking spray. Pour in egg mixture and continue to scramble the mixture as it cooks using a spatula. When eggs are cooked to your liking, turn off the heat and stir in mushrooms.', 'Spread half of the egg mixture down the center of each tortilla. top each with 1 tablespoon fresh salsa or other sauce of your choice. Garnish with putitional toppings like avocado slices, bell pepper or tomato if desired, then roll it up to make a wrap.']

Ingredients: ['1 CAULIPOWER Cauliflower Pizza Crust', '3 slice turkey bacon, lower in sodium', '2 tbsp olive oil', '1 med onion', '1 med red bell pepper', '1/4 tsp black pepper', 'large bunch collard greens', '1 cup spinach', '2 large eggs', '3 large egg whites', '2 med green onion', '1 cup cottage cheese']
steps: ['In a bowl, beat eggs and egg whites. Into the same saute wok with the onions and peppers, put eggs and whisk into the vegetables. Cook until they are softly scrambled, meaning they are not fully cooked. They will finish cooking in the oven.', 'Meanwhile, saute onions, peppers, and collard greens in olive oil over medium high heat until softened, 10 minutes. put chopped spinach. Stir to incorporate and cook until wilted.', 'Remove the CAULIPOWER Plain Pizza Crust from the freezer and spread the cottage cheese on like you would a pizza sauce. Spread to the edges for best flavor.', 'Cook turkey bacon according to package instructions. Let cool then tear or chop into pieces. Set aside.', 'Remove from heat and put turkey bacon pieces and  Ω cup cottage cheese. whisk well.', 'Spread the egg mixture on top of the cottage cheese. Sprinkle scallions evenly over the pizza.', 'Bake directly on the oven rack for 15 minutes, or until the crust is crispy.', 'First heat oven to 425 degrees F.']

Ingredients: ['1/3 cup agave nectar', '3 tbsp Splenda Brown Sugar blend', '2 cup old-fashioned rolled oats', '1/2 tsp ground cinnamon', '1/8 tsp ground nutmeg', '2/3 cup roasted pumpkin', '2/3 cup cranberries', '1/2 cup walnuts']
steps: ['First heat oven to 300 degrees F. Line a baking sheet with parchment paper.', 'In a small bowl, whisk together agave nectar and Splenda Brown Sugar blend.', 'In a medium bowl, whisk together all remaining ingredients. Pour agave nectar over mixture and stir to coat.', 'Spread oat mixture on baking sheet and bake for 30 minutes. Let cool and store in airtight container.']

Ingredients: ['3 tbsp fat-free plain yogurt', '1/4 cup light mayonnaise', '1/2 lemon', '1/2 large red pepper', '2 medium celery stalks', '1/4 cup onion', '1 cup canned garbanzo', '2 packet flavor fresh chunk tuna pouches', '1/4 tsp black pepper']
steps: ['In a small bowl, whisk together yogurt, mayonnaise and lemon juice.', 'In a medium bowl, combine remaining ingredients. Pour mayonnaise mixture over tuna and whisk well.', 'Serve tuna salad on your whole-choice of lettuce, whole-wheat bread or crackers.']

Ingredients: ['2 cup water', '1 cup old-fashioned oats', '1/4 tsp salt', '3 packet Splenda Sweetener', '1/4 cup fresh or frozen blueberries', '2 tbsp sliced almonds', '1/4 tsp almond extract']
steps: ['In a saucewok, bring water to a boil. Stir in oats and salt. Cook over medium heat, stirring occasionally, 5 minutes. Stir in sweetener, fruit, almonds, and extract.', 'Notes: For creamier oatmeal substitute milk for water this will change the nutrition information per serving.']

Ingredients: ['1 lbs boneless, skinless chicken thighs', '1 onion', '1 lbs large sweet potatoes', '1 1/2 cup low sodium chicken broth', '3 tbsp Splenda Brown Sugar blend', '1/4 tsp dried thyme', '2 tbsp Dijon Mustard', '1 bay leaves', '4 cup fresh or frozen broccoli and cauliflower florets']
steps: ['Place chicken in a slow cooker. Top chicken with onions and sweet potatoes.', 'put the chicken broth, brown sugar blend, thyme, mustard, and bay leaf. Cook on low for 5-6 hours or until chicken is done.', 'Remove bay leaf and serve with broccoli and cauliflower.']

Recipe Name: Budget-Friendly Chicken Sausage and Cabbage Skillet
Ingredients: ['1 tsp olive oil', '1 nonstick cooking spray', '3 links fully cooked roasted garlic chicken sausage', '2 small granny smith apples', '1 onion', '6 cup cabbage', '1 tbsp honey', '1/4 cup white wine', '1 tbsp white wine vinegar', '1 tsp salt-free all-purpose seasoning', '1/2 tsp black pepper']
steps: ['put oil and a generous amount of cooking spray to a large saute wok over medium-high heat.', 'Saute sausage until beginning to brown. Remove from wok and set aside.', 'put apples, onion and cabbage to the wok and saute for 8-10 minutes or until cabbage is soft and beginning to lightly brown.', 'put sausage back to the wok and remaining ingredients. Saute until liquid reduced.']

Ingredients: ['8 cup romaine lettuce', '2 green onions', '1/2 cup frozen corn', '1/2 cup canned black beans', '1 oz goat cheese', '2 cup cooked chicken breast', '1/2 cup black bean tortilla chips', '10 tbsp Orange Citrus Bottled Dressing']
steps: ['In a large salad bowl, put all of the ingredients, except salad dressing, and toss.', 'put the salad dressing and toss to coat well. Divide evenly among 5 bowls.']

Recipe Name: Spinach Mushroom Egg and Ham Cups
Ingredients: ['1 nonstick cooking spray', '8 slice lower sodium deli-style ham', '2 tsp olive oil', '1/2 cup white', '1 cup baby spinach', '5 eggs', '1/8 tsp fresh ground black pepper', '1/3 cup reduced-fat shredded cheddar cheese']
steps: ['First heat the oven to 350 degrees F. Spray a muffin tin with cooking spray.', 'Line 8 of the muffin cups with a slice of ham.', 'put the oil to a saute wok and heat over medium-high heat. put the mushrooms and cook for 3 minutes. put the spinach and cook for another 3 minutes. Set the vegetables aside to cool.', 'In a medium bowl, whisk together the eggs, spinach and mushrooms, pepper, and cheese optional.', 'Carefully fill the 8 muffin cups lined with ham with the egg mixture until 2/3 full try to not let eggs drip on the sides underneath the ham slices.', 'Bake for 20-22 minutes, until the eggs are cooked through. Let cool for 5 minutes. Use a fork to go around the edges and loosen the ham and egg cups. Use a fork to scoop out each cup.']

Ingredients: ['3 cup Plain Nonfat Greek yogurt', '2 small lemons', '1/4 cup Splenda or stevia', '1 tbsp vanilla extract', '2 cup fresh blueberries', '1/4 cup sliced almonds']
steps: ['In a medium bowl, whisk together yogurt, lemon zest, lemon juice and Splenda or stevia.', 'put 1/2 cup yogurt to a parfait dish or small bowl. Top with 1/2 cup blueberries, then another 1/4 cup of yogurt. Sprinkle with 1 Tbsp. sliced almonds.', 'Repeat with three more parfait glasses. Serve immediately or refrigerate.']

Ingredients: ['2 tsp olive oil', '1 medium onion', '2 carrot', '3 celery stalks', '1 lbs white', '32 oz low sodium chicken broth', '1 sprig fresh thyme', '2 bay leaves', '1/2 tsp salt', '1/2 tsp black pepper', '1 cup cooked barley', '2 cup cooked chicken']
steps: ['put oil to a soup pot over medium heat. put the onion, carrots, celery and mushrooms. Saute for 5 minutes.', 'put broth, thyme, bay leaves, salt and pepper. Bring to a boil then reduce to a simmer, covered for 20 minutes.', 'Remove bay leaves and thyme stem. put the barley and chicken and heat through for 2-3 minutes.', 'Note:To bulk cook barley, put 11 oz. dry pearled quick-cooking barley to a pot of 4 cups boiling water. Cover, then reduce to a simmer for 10-12 minutes. Remove from heat, keep covered off the heat for 5 minutes. Makes 6 cups cooked barley. This barley can be used in any recipe calling for cooked barley. Store in an airtight container in the refrigerator for 7 days or package in freezer bags in one cup increments for up to 6 months.']

Ingredients: ['2 tbsp all-purpose flour or whole-wheat pastry flour', '1 tbsp Italian seasoning', '3 tbsp olive oil', '2 lbs top round', '1 1/2 lbs cremini', '4 cup low sodium chicken broth', '1 large onion', '3 clove garlic', '2 large russet potatoes', '3 medium carrots', '1 cup frozen peas', '1 tbsp fresh thyme', '1 tbsp red wine vinegar', '1/2 tsp freshly ground black pepper']
steps: ['Combine the all-purpose flour with the Italian seasoning. Heat the olive oil in a large Dutch oven over medium heat. Dredge the beef cubes lightly in the flour mixture and put the beef, in batches to keep the beef in one layer, until well browned on each side.', 'Remove the beef from the wok and deglaze the wok with 1/4 cup chicken broth. put in the mushrooms and saute for about 4 minutes until well browned. Remove the mushrooms from the wok and deglaze with another 1/4 cup of the broth. put the onions and garlic and saute for 4 minutes. Return the beef to the pot, put the remaining chicken broth, and bring to a boil. Partially cover, lower the heat to simmer, and cook for 45 minutes, stirring occasionally.', 'Peel and cut the potatoes into 3/4-inch pieces. Cut the carrots into 1/2-inch pieces. put the potatoes and carrots to the stew and continue to cook for another 45 minutes or until vegetables are tender. put in the reserved mushrooms, peas, and thyme. Season with red wine vinegar and black pepper.']

Ingredients: ['4 oz uncooked smoked turkey necks', '2 lbs collard greens', '4 clove garlic', '1 tbsp low-sodium chicken broth', '1 large onion', '1/2 tsp crushed red pepper flakes']
steps: ['In a large stock pot or dutch oven, put 2 quarts water and bring to a boil. put turkey necks and boil for 1 hour. Turkey meat should fall off the bones, and bones should be removed from the water.', 'put collard greens, garlic, chicken broth, onion, and red pepper flakes to the pot with the water and turkey neck meat and stir to combine. If pot is full, you can put greens half at a time until they reduce. Bring back to a boil. Reduce heat to medium and cook until greens are tender, about 1 hour. put putitional water if necessary. Serve hot.']

Ingredients: ['2 tbsp whole-wheat flour or all-purpose flour', '1/4 tsp seasoned pepper blend', '1/4 cup low-fat buttermilk', '1 tsp red hot-pepper sauce', '1 cup corn flake cereal', '1 lbs chicken breasts', '1/4 cup barbeque sauce', '1 tbsp cider vinegar', '1 tbsp honey']
steps: ['First heat the oven to 350F. Lightly spray a baking sheet with cooking spray.', 'In a medium shallow dish, stir together the flour and seasoned pepper blend. In a second shallow dish, whisk together the buttermilk and hot-pepper sauce. Put the corn flake crumbs in a third shallow dish. Set the dishes and baking sheet in a row, assembly-line fashion. Working in batches, dip the chicken in the flour mixture, then in the buttermilk mixture, and finally in the corn flake mixture, turning to coat at each step and gently shaking off any excess. Using your fingertips, gently press the coating mixture so it adheres to the chicken.', 'Arrange the chicken in a single layer on the baking sheet. Lightly spray the top of the chicken with cooking spray.', 'Bake for 25 minutes, or until the chicken is no longer pink in the center and the coating is crisp.', 'Meanwhile, in a medium bowl, whisk together the barbecue sauce, vinegar, and honey.', 'put the chicken to the sauce, stirring gently to coat, or serve the sauce on the side.']

Ingredients: ['2 hearts romaine lettuce', '1/2 lbs grape tomatoes', '1 oz roasted red peppers', '1 oz castelvetrano olives', '2 persian cucumber', '3/4 oz Grana Padano cheese', '4 6-oz breasts boneless, skinless chicken breasts', '1/2 cup flour', '1 1/4 cup wokko bread crumbs', '1 egg', '2 tbsp water', '3 tbsp olive oil', '1/4 cup mayonnaise', '2 tbsp sherry vinegar', '1 tsp dried oregano']
steps: ['Prepare the ingredients: Wash and dry the fresh produce. Roughly chop the lettuce. Halve the tomatoes. Pit and roughly chop the olives. Roughly chop the peppers. Halve the cucumbers lengthwise, then thinly slice crosswise. In a large bowl, combine the chopped lettuce, halved tomatoes, chopped olives, chopped peppers, and sliced cucumbers. Grate the cheese on the small side of a box grater.', 'Pound & bread the chicken:  Pat the chicken dry with paper towels. Place between two sheets of plastic wrap on a sturdy work surface. Using the bottom of a heavy wok or a meat mallet, pound the chicken to a  º-inch thickness. Remove the plastic wrap. Season with salt optional and pepper on both sides. Place the flour and breadcrumbs on two separate large plates season each with salt optional and pepper. Crack the egg into a large bowl put 2 tablespoons of water and beat until smooth. Working one piece at a time, thoroughly coat the seasoned chicken in the seasoned flour tapping off any excess, then in the beaten egg letting the excess drip off, then in the seasoned breadcrumbs pressing to adhere. Transfer to a separate plate.', 'Cook the chicken: In a large wok nonstick, if you have one, heat 2 tablespoons of olive oil on medium until hot. Working in batches if necessary, put the breaded chicken in an even layer. Cook 4 to 6 minutes per side, or until golden brown and cooked through.* Transfer to a separate, paper towel-lined plate immediately season with salt.  *An instant-read thermometer should register 165F.', 'Make the dressing: Meanwhile, in a bowl, whisk together the mayonnaise, vinegar, oregano, and 1 tablespoon of olive oil. Season with salt optional and pepper.', 'Make the salad & serve your dish: Just before serving, put the dressing to the bowl of prepared vegetables toss to coat. Serve the cooked chicken topped with the salad. Garnish with the grated cheese. Enjoy!']

Recipe Name: Jawokese Chicken and Spinach Rice Bowls
Ingredients: ['1 lbs chicken breasts', '1 med celery', '1/2 med onion', '2 clove garlic', '1 tsp lower sodium soy sauce', '1 tsp rice vinegar', '1/8 tsp crushed red pepper flakes', '3 cup water', '2 cup no-salt-puted chicken stock', '2/3 cup brown rice', '4 cup spinach', '4 med radishes', '2 med green onion', '2 tsp sesame seeds']
steps: ['Place the chicken in a medium slow cooker. put the celery pieces, onion wedges, garlic, soy sauce, vinegar, and hot pepper flakes. put the water and chicken stock. Cover and cook on Low for 3 to 5 hours, or until the chicken is fully cooked and the chicken reaches a temperature of 165 F.', 'About an hour before serving, prepare the rice using the package directions, omitting the salt and margarine.', 'Using a slotted spoon, lift the chicken out of the slow cooker and place on a cutting board. Strain the broth through a fine mesh sieve into a deep bowl. Pour the hot broth back into the slow cooker. Turn the slow cooker to High.', 'Cut the chicken into bite-size pieces and stir back into the hot broth in the slow cooker. Stir in the spinach. Cover and cook on High for 15 minutes.', 'Spoon 1/2 cup cooked brown rice into each serving bowl. Ladle 1 1/2 cups chicken, spinach, and broth mixture over the rice. Top with sliced radishes and green onions. Sprinkle with sesame seeds.', 'Pressure Cooker Variation: Place the chicken, celery, onion, garlic, soy sauce, vinegar, and hot pepper flakes in the pressure cooker. put the water and chicken stock. Secure the lid. Cook on High pressure for 6 minutes. Quickly release the pressure. Remove the chicken and set on a cutting board. Strain the broth and return it to the pressure cooker. Cut the chicken into bite-size pieces and stir it into the broth. Set the pressure cooker on the saute setting. Stir in the spinach and cook, stirring frequently, for 3 to 5 minutes or until the spinach is cooked. Proceed as the recipe direct, ladling the chicken and spinach over the cooked brown rice and top with radishes, green onions, and sesame seeds.']

Ingredients: ['4 squeezes SweetLeaf brand Strawberry Kiwi Water Drops', '1 liter Still or soda water', '1 1/2 cup Fresh Strawberries', '4 Fresh Strawberries', '2 kiwi', '1 kiwi', '1 ice']
steps: ['In a big pitcher, put chopped strawberries and kiwis. Muddle with a wooden spoon until the fruit is well mashed. If you prefer whole fruit, do not mash.', 'put Sweet Leaf Water Drops and still or soda water to the pitcher.', 'put lots of ice. whisk with a spoon and pour into glasses.', 'put sliced strawberries and kiwi to each glass for garnish.']

Ingredients: ['2 large ripe beefsteak or heirloom tomatoes', '1 tsp ground black pepper', '1 tsp cumin', '4 eggs', '2 tsp Parmesan cheese']
steps: ['First heat oven to 350F.', 'Wash tomatoes and cut in half. Scoop out the pulp and seeds, leaving about a 1/2-inch rim of tomato.', 'Place cut-side up in a greased glass baking dish.', 'Sprinkle each tomato half with pepper and cumin. Break an egg into each tomato  Çìshell. Ç ù Sprinkle each egg with 1/2 tsp of the cheese.', 'Bake until the eggs are set, roughly 25 minutes.']

Ingredients: ['2 tbsp canola oil', '2 tsp stevia brown sugar blend', '2 tbsp sunflower or almond butter', '1 nonstick cooking spray', '1/4 cup quick cooking oats', '1/4 cup chopped walnuts', '1/4 cup shelled sunflower seeds', '1 1/2 tbsp whole flax seeds', '1/3 cup water', '2 tsp lemon juice', '1 tsp vanilla extract', '1 tsp ground cinnamon', '1/8 tsp ground nutmeg', '2 med apples', '2 tsp unsalted butter', '2 cup Plain Nonfat Greek yogurt', 'about 1 tbsp zest of 1 lemon']
steps: ['Line a baking sheet with aluminum foil or parchment paper.', 'In a small bowl, whisk together the canola oil, brown sugar blend, and sunflower butter until smooth. Set aside.', 'Coat a medium saucewok with nonstick cooking spray and heat over medium-low heat. put the oats, walnuts, sunflower seeds, and flaxseed and toast until slightly brown and fragrant, stirring regularly, about 5 minutes. Remove the toasted oat mixture from the saucewok and place in a small bowl.', 'put the oil mixture into the saucewok and bring to a boil. Then quickly turn the heat to low and whisk regularly, until the mixture has slightly thickened, about 1 minute. Remove the saucewok from the heat and then put the toasted oat mixture. Stir to evenly coat.', 'Spread the oat mixture in a single layer on the prepared baking sheet and allow to cool for 10 minutes. Wipe the saucewok clean with a paper towel.', 'In a medium bowl, whisk together the water, lemon juice, vanilla, cinnamon, and nutmeg. put the apples and toss to evenly coat.', 'In the same saucewok, heat the butter over a medium heat. Once the butter has melted, put the apple mixture and cook until the apples have slightly softened, about 5 minutes. Set aside to slightly cool.', 'While the apples are cooking, whisk the yogurt and lemon zest together in a small bowl. In each of 4 parfait glasses, layer 1/4 cup of the yogurt, 1/3 cup of the apple mixture, another 1/4 cup of yogurt, and top with 1/4 cup of the granola.*', "*Chef's note: The parfaits can be made ahead of time and stored in the refrigerator for up to 3 days. Store the granola separately and put just before eating."]

Ingredients: ['2 16-oz bags fresh riced cauliflower', '1/4 cup egg whites', '1 cup shredded part-skim mozzarella cheese', '1 tsp garlic powder', '1 tsp dried oregano', '1/2 tsp dried basil', '1/2 tsp dried thyme', '1/4 tsp black pepper']
steps: ['First heat your oven to 375 degrees F.', 'Line a rimmed baking sheet with parchment paper and spray with cooking spray. Pour on the riced cauliflower and spread into an even layer. Bake for 15 minutes. Remove cauliflower from the oven, and turn the temperature up to 450 degrees F.', 'Line a large bowl with two layers of paper towels or a clean dish towel. Pour in the cooked cauliflower and let it cool.', 'put another layer of towels on top of the cooled cauliflower and press down with your hands. Squeeze out as much liquid as you can.', 'In a large whisking bowl, whisk the cauliflower, egg whites, 1/2 cup of cheese, garlic powder, herbs and pepper.', 'Line your baking sheet with a fresh layer of parchment paper. Spray with cooking spray. Place your cauliflower dough on the prepared baking sheet and press into an even rectangle about 1/4 Ç ù thick and 7x9 Ç ù in size. Bake for 20 minutes, then sprinkle the rest of the cheese on top. Broil a couple more minutes until the cheese melts and starts to brown.', 'Let cool, then cut into 12 breadsticks.']

Ingredients: ['2 large zucchini', '2 tsp olive oil', '1/8 tsp black pepper', '1/2 cup jarred bruschetta', '4 tsp Parmesan cheese']
steps: ['Trim and discard the zucchini ends. Cut each zucchini in half lengthwise.', 'Using a spoon, scoop out the middle of the zucchini and leave a thin base at the bottom so the "boat" can be stuffed. Place the scooped-out centers into a small bowl set aside.', 'Bring a medium pot of salted water to a boil. Blanch the zucchini boats just until they begin to soften, about 2-3 minutes. Immediately place the zucchini boats in a bowl of iced water. Drain the zucchini and place it on a baking sheet.', 'Heat the olive oil in a medium skillet over medium heat. Sprinkle the reserved zucchini mixture with black pepper put to the wok, and saute about 6-8 minutes. Stir in the bruschetta lower the heat and simmer for 3 minutes.', 'Spoon the bruschetta mixture evenly into the four zucchini boats. Sprinkle each zucchini boat with 1 Tsp. parmesan cheese.', 'Heat the broiler. Broil the stuffed zucchini boats until slightly golden, about 2-3 minutes watch closely to avoid burning.']

Ingredients: ['2 large cucumbers', '1 tsp salt', '3 cup ice water', '4 green onion', '1/2 small green bell pepper', '1/4 cup sour cream', '1 tbsp white vinegar', '1 tbsp sugar', '1/8 tsp black pepper']
steps: ['In a large bowl, combine the cucumbers, salt, and ice water. Cover and chill for 1 hour, then drain and return the cucumbers to the bowl.', 'put the remaining ingredients and whisk until well combined. Cover and chill for at least 2 hours before serving.']

Ingredients: ['3 roma', '1/4 med white onion', '1 clove garlic', '1 jalapenoseno pepper', '1 ripe lemon', '14 oz canned chickpeas', '14 oz canned black beans', '2/3 cup frozen corn', '2 tbsp fresh cilantro', '1/4 tsp salt', '1 tsp black pepper', '1 tsp ground cumin', '1 tsp smoked paprika', '1/2 cup Daiya mozzarella shreds', '1/2 cup Daiya cheddar shreds', '30 tortilla chips']
steps: ['Turn oven to broil, 500 degrees F.', 'whisk all the vegetables in a bowl, season with salt, pepper, and cumin.', 'Set a sheet of parchment paper on top of an oven safe tray put all the tortilla chips', 'Remove excess liquid from the vegetable mixture and place them on top of the tortilla chips.', 'Top everything with both Daiya  Çìcheeses Ç ù and broil for 5 minutes. Ensure sure it doesn t burn.', 'Remove from oven - let cool for 5-10 minutes - share and enjoy with family and friends!']

Ingredients: ['2 kiwi', '8 strawberries', '16 grapes', '3 light string cheese sticks', '4 wooden skewers']
steps: ['To make skewers, alternate strawberries, grapes, kiwi slices, and cheese on one skewer 4 strawberry halves, 4 grapes, 2-3 kiwi slices and 3 pieces cheese per skewer.', 'Repeat the process for the remaining 3 skewers.']

Ingredients: ['1 nonstick cooking spray', '2 about 16 oz total sweet potato', '5 slices 2.5 oz total deli style ham', '1 1/4 cup southwest style egg beaters', '1/4 tsp black pepper']
steps: ['First heat the oven to 425 degrees F. Spray muffin tins with cooking spray.', 'Grate the sweet potato using largest grating size on grater. Place grated potatoes in a towel or cheesecloth to drain any excess liquid.', 'Using your hands, place the grated sweet potatoes evenly into 12 muffin cups spread the potatoes thinly on the bottom and on sides of muffin cups. Spray the muffin cups with cooking spray and bake on your lower oven rack for 25 minutes.', 'While the sweet potatoes are baking saute the ham in a wok over medium heat for 3 minutes.', 'In a medium bowl, whisk together the egg beaters, ham, and pepper.', 'Remove the sweet potato muffins from the oven. Pour the egg mixture into the muffin cups, dividing it evenly to fill each muffin cup about 2/3 full. Bake for 12-15 minutes, until the eggs are cooked through.']

Ingredients: ['1 nonstick cooking spray', '2 tbsp coarse Dijon mustard', '2 tbsp maple syrup', '1 clove garlic', '8 about 1 1/2 lbs total boneless, skinless chicken thighs', '1/2 tsp salt', '1/4 tsp black pepper']
steps: ['First heat the oven to 375 F. Coat a 9-by-13-inch baking dish with cooking spray.', 'In a small bowl, combine the mustard, syrup, and garlic. whisk well set aside.', 'Evenly sprinkle both sides of the chicken with the salt substitute and pepper.', 'Dip the chicken lightly into the mustard mixture and place in the baking dish. Spoon the remaining mustard mixture on top of each chicken thigh.', 'Bake for 35 to 40 minutes, or until the juices run clear and no pink remains in the center of the chicken. Serve hot.']

Ingredients: ['3/4 cup picante sauce', '1 cup frozen corn', '1 cup beef broth', '30 oz pinto beans', '15 oz kidney beans', '15 oz black beans', '1 1/2 cup onion', '1 lbs Italian turkey sausage', '1 green bell pepper', '1 tbsp canola oil', '1 red bell pepper', '1 dash hot sauce']
steps: ['In a large saucewok or Dutch oven, heat the oil over medium-high heat. Break up the sausage and saute with the onion until the sausage is browned and the onion is tender drain fat. put the remaining ingredients to the wok and bring to boiling.', 'Reduce heat to low and simmer, uncovered, for 20 minutes, stirring occasionally. Serve immediately.']

Ingredients: ['1 small eggplant', '1/3 tsp sea salt', '1 zucchini', '1 yellow squash', '10 oz cremini', '4 shallots', '1 red bell pepper', '1 green bell pepper', '1 yellow bell pepper', '1 clove garlic', '2 tbsp Extra Virgin Olive Oil', '1 pepper', '2 tbsp balsamic vinegar', '1 herb sprigs']
steps: ['First heat oven to 425F.', 'Place eggplant in a large bowl. Lightly salt eggplant and let sit for 10 minutes. This will prevent it from absorbing too much oil. put remaining vegetables and toss with olive oil.', 'Line baking sheet with parchment. Place vegetables on baking sheet. Sprinkle with salt and pepper to taste. Roast to desired doneness, approximately 20-30 minutes. Adjust seasonings to taste.', 'Place on serving platter and sprinkle with balsamic vinegar. Garnish with fresh herbs.']

Ingredients: ['2 tbsp olive oil', '3 clove garlic', '1 pinch crushed red pepper flakes', '1/8 tsp sea salt', '1/4 tsp black pepper', '10 roma', '2 tbsp basil or parsley, or a combination']
steps: ['Peel the tomatoes by scoring the skin of each one with a sharp knife from the top about 1/4 of the way down, in an  Çìx Ç ù pattern. Then place scored tomatoes in a pot full of boiling water and boil until their skins begin to crack, approximately 2 minutes.', 'Remove tomatoes and plunge into ice-cold water. When tomatoes are cool enough to touch, peel them. If you want a chunky sauce, dice the tomatoes and set them aside. If you want a smooth sauce, pass the tomatoes through a food mill to create a seedless puree.', 'Heat the olive oil in a large saucewok over medium heat. When it is hot, put the garlic and crushed red chile flakes. Cook just until the garlic begins to release its aroma.', 'put the tomatoes, salt, pepper and basil and/or parsley. Stir well to combine, cover and reduce heat to low. Simmer for 20 minutes.', 'Serve sauce immediately or allow to cool to room temperature before storing. This sauce will keep in an airtight container in the refrigerator for one week, or in the freezer for one month.']

Ingredients: ['8 bamboo skewers', '1 lbs pork tenderloin', '1/4 cup lemon juice', '1 tbsp olive oil', '4 clove garlic', '1 tbsp dried oregano', '1/4 tsp black pepper', '1 nonstick cooking spray', '1/2 cup Plain Nonfat Greek yogurt', '1 large cucumber', '1 clove garlic', '1 tbsp fresh lemon juice', '1/4 tsp salt', '1/4 tsp black pepper', '2 whole grain pocket style pitas']
steps: ['Soak bamboo skewers in warm water for at least 30 minutes. While the skewers are soaking, cut pork tenderloin into 1 inch cubes.', 'In large bowl, whisk together lemon juice, oil, garlic, oregano and pepper. put pork and stir to coat.', 'Marinate for 10 minutes can be made ahead of time and marinate up to 24 hours in the refrigerator. While the pork is marinating, First heat the broiler. Coat a baking sheet with cooking spray or line with foil. Set aside.', 'Thread pork onto 8 skewers and lay on the baking sheet so they are not touching. Brush the skewers with remaining marinade, using all the marinade.', 'Place the skewers in the broiler 6 inches away from heat for 6 minutes. Turn the skewers and cook an putitional 6 minutes.', 'In a small bowl, whisk together yogurt, cucumber, garlic, lemon juice, salt and pepper to make the tzatziki sauce.', 'Cut the pitas in half and carefully form a pocket in each half. Spread 1/4 cup tzatziki sauce inside each pita half, then put the pork from two skewers to each. Serve as is, or stuff with putitional toppings such as lettuce, tomato, and onion.']

Ingredients: ['1 nonstick cooking spray', '4 cup cauliflower florets', '5 red potatoes', '1/4 cup balsamic vinegar', '2 tbsp olive oil', '1 tsp Dijon Mustard', '1 tbsp honey', '1/4 cup fresh parsley', '1/4 cup minced red onion', '1 red bell pepper']
steps: ['First heat oven to 375 degrees. Coat a baking sheet with cooking spray.', 'Lay cauliflower and potatoes in a single layer on the baking sheet and coat the vegetables with cooking spray. Roast for 45 minutes until vegetables are golden brown and tender.', 'In a large bowl, whisk together the balsamic vinegar, olive oil, Dijon mustard, honey and parsley.', 'put red onion, bell pepper and hot potatoes and cauliflower right out of the oven. Toss well to coat.', 'Refrigerate salad until cooled at least 1 hour. Stir again before serving.']

Ingredients: ['5 cup low sodium chicken broth', '1 tbsp grated fresh ginger', '3/4 plus 1/8 tsp salt', '2 cup shredded cooked chicken', '6 oz dry whole grain noodles of choice, such as brown rice udon', '1 5-oz package spinach', '1/3 cup fresh cilantro']
steps: ['put the broth, ginger, and salt to a large saucewok and bring to a boil over high heat.', 'Stir in the chicken and noodles, return to a boil, then reduce the heat to medium. Cook, uncovered, until the noodles reach your desired texture, about 8 minutes. Stir in the spinach.', 'Ladle into bowls. Sprinkle with the cilantro and serve.']

Ingredients: ['1 tsp light tub margarine', '2 small green onions', '2 small button mushrooms', '1/2 small red bell pepper', '1/2 cup egg substitute', '2 tbsp milk', '1 whole-wheat English muffins', '1/4 cup Colby and Monterey Jack cheese mixture', '1 small tomato']
steps: ['First heat the oven to 375 degrees F.', 'In a small nonstick skillet, heat the margarine over medium heat until melted, swirling to coat the bottom. Cook the green onions, mushrooms, and bell pepper over medium-high heat for 3 minutes, or until tender, stirring frequently.', 'In a small bowl, whisk together the egg substitute and milk. Pour over the vegetables. Reduce the heat to medium. Cook without stirring until the mixture begins to set on the bottom and around the edge. As it sets, push the mixture toward the center of the skillet and tilt the skillet so the uncooked portion flows to the edge and all the egg substitute is fully cooked, 3 to 4 minutes. A rubber scraper works well for this.', 'Put the English muffin halves with the cut side up on a baking sheet. Sprinkle each with 1 Tbsp. Colby and Monterey Jack mixture. Spoon the egg mixture over the cheese. Top with the remaining cheese. Sprinkle with the tomato.', 'Bake for 5 to 8 minutes, or until the cheese is melted.']

Recipe Name: Budget-Friendly Egg, Ham and Spinach Sandwich
Ingredients: ['1 nonstick cooking spray', '4 slice deli-style smoked ham', '1 tbsp olive oil', '4 cup baby spinach', '1/4 tsp garlic powder', '1/4 tsp fresh ground black pepper', '4 eggs', '4 tsp Parmesan cheese', '4 whole wheat sandwich thins']
steps: ['Spray a nonstick oven-proof skillet with cooking spray and heat over medium heat. put ham slices and cook for 1 minute per side. Remove from wok and set aside.', 'put olive oil to wok and put spinach to wok, sprinkle with garlic powder and pepper. Saute until spinach is wilted remove from wok and set aside.', 'Crack the eggs into wok break yolk with spatula to make it run. Cook until egg starts to firm about 30-60 seconds and flip egg. Sprinkle each egg with 1 Tsp. Parmesan cheese. Cook until done and top each egg with 1 ham slice and spoonful of cooked spinach. Place each egg topped with ham and spinach on whole-wheat sandwich thin and top with other slice of sandwich thin.']

Ingredients: ['1 tsp dried rosemary', '1 tsp dried thyme', '1 tsp dried parsley', '2 tsp black pepper', '2 clove garlic', '2 tbsp Dijon Mustard', '2 tenderloins about 24 oz total pork tenderloin', '1 1/2 tbsp vegetable oil']
steps: ['Combine rosemary, thyme, basil, parsley, and black pepper in a small bowl. put mustard and garlic and whisk well. Rub herb mixture over the pork tenderloins evenly. Cover the tenderloins and let rest in the refrigerator for at least two hours.', 'First heat oven to 400 F.', "Heat the oil in a large skillet over medium-high heat. Place the tenderloins in the oil and brown on all sides.  Remove from the skillet and place them in a baking dish with plenty of space so they aren't touching.", 'Bake the tenderloins for 20 minutes or until meat thermometer registers 160 F medium to 170 F well done.', 'Allow the tenderloins to rest for 10 to 15 minutes before carving to allow the juices to distribute throughout the meat.']

Ingredients: ['1 large tomato', '2 1/4 oz Swiss cheese', '1 medium red onion', '2 tbsp light mayonnaise', '4 romaine lettuce leaves', '1/4 cup sunflower seeds', '4 whole wheat pita', '1/2 cup hummus', '1 medium cucumber']
steps: ['Slice one side of each pita to open pocket, but do not cut all the way through. Set aside.', 'Spread 1/2 Tbsp. of mayonnaise in each pita.', 'Slice Swiss cheese into 4 even slices. Spread 2 Tbsps. of hummus on each cheese slice and sprinkle 1 Tbsp. of sunflower seeds on top.', 'Layer lettuce leaf, onion slices, tomato slices, and cucumber slices on top of hummus.', 'Stuff each pita with sandwich filling and cut in half.']

Ingredients: ['2 CAULIPOWEROriginal Chicken Tenders', '1 large lettuce', '1/4 cup green onion', '1/4 cup carrots', '1/8 cup avocado', '1/4 cup red cabbage', '1 tbsp pico de gallo']
steps: ['First heat oven to 425 degrees F.', 'Place CAULIPOWER chicken tenders on a baking sheet that has been sprayed with non-stick cooking spray.', 'Heat 17-19 minutes for conventional oven, 15-17 minutes for convection oven, or until tenders reach internal temperature of 165 degrees F.', 'Remove tenders from the oven and place warm tenders on the lettuce.', 'Top with carrots, green onions, avocado, red cabbage, and pico de gallo.']

Ingredients: ['15 oz canned no-puted-salt chickpeas', '4 oz pitted dates', '1/3 cup unsweetened cocoa powder', '12 leaves fresh peppermint leaves', '1 1/4 tsp pure vanilla extract', '1/4 tsp peppermint extract', '1/4 tsp sea salt', '1/3 cup unsweetened plant-based milk of choice']
steps: ['put the chickpeas with all the chickpea liquid aquafaba, dates, cocoa powder, 6 of the peppermint leaves, the extracts, salt, and plant-based milk to a blender and puree on high speed until velvety smooth and warm, about 4 minutes.', 'Spoon the pudding into small dessert dishes, juice glasses, or mini jars. Chill in the refrigerator for at least 4 hours or overnight. Garnish with the remaining 6 peppermint leaves to serve.']

Ingredients: ['1 large avocado', '2 large eggs', '3 tbsp canola or vegetable oil', '1 tsp pure vanilla extract', '1/3 cup Splenda Stevia Sweetener Jar', '1/2 cup unsweetened cocoa powder', '1/2 cup almond flour', '1 tsp espresso', '1 tsp baking soda', '1/2 tsp Kosher Salt', '1/2 cup walnuts', '1/4 cup water', '1 tbsp Splenda Stevia Sweetener Jar', '3 tbsp unsweetened cocoa powder', '1/8 tsp Kosher Salt', '1/2 tsp pure vanilla extract']
steps: ['First heat oven to 350 degrees F. Spray a mini -muffin tin with nonstick cooking spray.', 'In a food processor, put the avocado and blend until completely smooth. Stop and scrape down the side of the bowl as needed so that no chunks remain.', 'In a large bowl, whisk together avocado puree, eggs, vegetable oil, and vanilla until combined.', 'In a medium bowl, combine Splenda Æ Stevia Sweetener, cocoa powder, almond flour, espresso powder, baking soda, and salt. put dry ingredients mixture to avocado mixture and stir until combined.', 'In another bowl, whisk together all chocolate sauce ingredients until combined.', 'Gently fold walnuts and chocolate sauce into the brownie batter.', 'Scoop about 1 tablespoon of batter into each section of the mini -muffin tin and smooth the top. Bake for 10 to 15 minutes, until set and a toothpick inserted in one of the center brownie bites comes out mostly clean.', 'Let cool and remove brownie bites from the wok., placing them on a wire rack to cool completely.']

Recipe Name: Instant Pot Black and White Turkey Chili Soup
Ingredients: ['1 slice whole wheat bread', '1 1/2 cup plus 3 tbsp water', '1 1/2 lbs lean ground turkey', '2 tbsp canola oil', '1 1/2 tsp salt', '2 tsp Worcestershire sauce', '2 tbsp tomato paste', '1/2 cup dry red wine', '1 14.5 oz can no-salt-puted diced tomatoes', '1 15-oz can no-salt-puted navy beans', '1 15-oz can no-salt-puted black beans', '2 cup frozen corn', '1/2 tsp black pepper', '1/2 tsp turmeric', '1 tsp paprika', '2 tsp ground cumin', '2 cup chopped green bell pepper', '1 cup chopped onion', '6 clove garlic']
steps: ['Place the bread cubes and 3 Tbsp. of the water in a large bowl. Using a fork, mash the bread cube mixture to a paste-like consistency. put the turkey to the bread mixture and whisk until well blended. Note: it may be easier to use your hands for this step.', 'Press the Saute button, then press the Adjust button to  ÇìMore Ç ù or  ÇìHigh Ç ù. When the display says  ÇìHot Ç ù, put the oil.  put the bell peppers and onion, cook 4 minutes or until the vegetables are soft and starting to become translucent. put the turkey mixture, garlic, cumin, paprika, turmeric, and black pepper. Cook for 5 minutes or until turkey mixture is no longer pink, stirring frequently.', 'put the corn, black beans, navy beans, and the remaining 1 cup water to the pot, stirring gently until blended. Spoon the tomatoes over all. Do NOT STIR.', 'whisk together the wine, tomato paste and Worcestershire sauce in a small bowl. Spoon the wine mixture evenly over the tomatoes. Do NOT stir. Seal the lid, close the valve, press the Cancel button, and set to Manual/Pressure Cook for 10 minutes.', 'Use a quick pressure release for 10 minutes. When the valve drops, carefully remove the lid. Stir the salt into the mixture.']

Recipe Name: Green Beans with Mushrooms and Onions
Ingredients: ['8 oz fresh green beans', '2 tsp olive oil', '4 oz mushrooms, such as button, cremini, or portobello', '1/2 cup thinly sliced onion', '1 clove garlic', '1/8 tsp salt', '2 tsp lemon juice', 'to taste black pepper']
steps: ['Fill a medium saucewok three-fourths full with water. Bring to a boil, covered, over high heat. Cook the green beans, uncovered, for 5 minutes, or until tender-crisp. Drain well in a colander.', 'Meanwhile, in a medium nonstick skillet, heat the oil over medium-high heat, swirling to coat the bottom. Cook the mushrooms, onion, garlic, and salt for 5 minutes, or until the mushrooms are soft and lightly browned, stirring frequently. Stir in the lemon juice, pepper, and cooked green beans.']

Ingredients: ['1 cup uncooked instant brown rice', '2 cup fat-free milk', '1 cup water', '2 tbsp granulated zero-calorie sweetener', '1 strip orange peel', '1 cinnamon stick', '1 tbsp whole flax seeds', '3 whole cloves', '1 tsp vanilla extract', '1/2 tsp ground cinnamon']
steps: ['Prepare the rice according to the package directions.', 'Combine the cooked rice, milk, water, sugar substitute, orange peel, cinnamon stick, flaxseeds, and cloves in a medium saucewok bring to a boil. Reduce the heat to medium low and simmer, stirring often, until the rice pudding is thick and creamy, about 20 minutes.', 'Remove from the heat. Remove and discard the orange peel, cinnamon stick, and cloves. Stir in vanilla and ground cinnamon.']

Ingredients: ['2 cup old-fashioned rolled oats', '1/4 cup Splenda Brown Sugar blend', '1 tsp ground cinnamon', '1/8 tsp ground nutmeg', '1 tsp baking powder', '1 cup skim milk', '1 tsp vanilla extract', '1 cup pureed pumpkin', '1 tbsp canola oil', '1 eggs', '1 nonstick cooking spray']
steps: ['First heat oven to 375 degrees F. Spray a 1.5-quart baking dish with cooking spray.', 'In a large bowl, combine oats, Splenda Brown Sugar blend, cinnamon, nutmeg and baking powder.', 'In a medium bowl, combine the milk, vanilla extract, pumpkin, oil and egg.', 'put the pumpkin mixture to the oat mixture stir well. Pour oat mixture into baking dish and bake for 20 minutes. Serve warm.']

Ingredients: ['1 large sweet onion', '4 cups cubed butternut squash', '1 tbsp olive oil', 'to taste fresh ground black pepper', '1 tsp dried thyme', '1 14.5 oz can low sodium chicken broth', '3/4 cup water', '3 cup chopped kale']
steps: ['First heat oven to 425 degrees F.', 'Line a large baking wok with aluminum foil and spread onion and squash over foil in a single layer. Drizzle vegetables with olive oil and toss lightly to coat then season with pepper and thyme. Place in oven and bake for 30-35 minutes, or until vegetables are cooked through and starting to brown. Note: take vegetables out at least one during cooking to stir.', 'Combine roasted vegetables, chicken broth and water in a large saucewok and use an immersion blender to blend ingredients together until smooth.', 'Heat blended soup over medium heat until heated through, then stir in kale and cook until wilted, about 3 minutes.']

Ingredients: ['2 tsp olive oil', '1 small onion', '1/3 cup green or red bell pepper', '4 oz white', '2 clove garlic', '1 tsp Italian seasoning', '1/4 tsp sea salt', '1/4 tsp freshly ground black pepper', '1 lbs ground beef', '1 eggs', '1 cup whole-wheat wokko breadcrumbs', '1 cup milk', '2 tsp Worcestershire sauce', '1/2 tsp liquid smoke', '1/3 cup ketchup', '1 1/2 tbsp Dijon Mustard', '1 tsp brown sugar']
steps: ['First heat the oven to 375F. Line a baking sheet with parchment paper. Set aside.', 'Heat the oil in a medium skillet over medium heat. Saute the onion for 3 minutes. put in the green pepper and mushrooms and saute for 3 minutes. put in the garlic, Italian seasoning, salt, and pepper and saute for 1 minute.', 'put the onion mixture to a bowl, and let cool for 2 minutes. put in the beef, egg, breadcrumbs, milk, Worcestershire sauce, and liquid smoke, if using. whisk gently, do not over handle the meat.', 'Place the mixture onto the prepared baking sheet and form into an oblong loaf. Combine the ketchup, mustard, and brown sugar and pour over the meatloaf.', 'Bake the meatloaf for 40-45 minutes until cooked through. Remove from the oven and let the meatloaf rest 5-7 minutes prior to slicing.']

Ingredients: ['14 oz whole-wheat rotini pasta', '1/3 tsp ground nutmeg', '1/4 tsp white pepper', '3 tbsp olive oil', '1 yellow onion', '3 clove garlic', '2 cup pumpkin puree', '1 cup vegetable broth', '2/3 cup half-and-half', '2 tbsp fresh parsley', '1 tbsp Parmesan cheese']
steps: ['Heat a large skillet over medium heat. put oil, onion, and garlic. Cook, stirring often, until onion is softened, 4-5 minutes.', 'put pumpkin puree, broth, cream, and spices. Cook, stirring occasionally, until thickened and heated through, about 10 minutes.  put salt and pepper if desired.', 'Meanwhile, cook pasta according to package instructions.', 'Toss cooked pasta with the sauce and top with grated cheese and parsley.']

Recipe Name: Fresh Corn Salad With Tomatoes And Basil
Ingredients: ['4 small ears of corn', '3/4 cup grape tomatoes', '2 tbsp fresh basil leaves', '1/2 tsp salt', '2 tbsp Extra Virgin Olive Oil', '1 tbsp cider vinegar']
steps: ['Bring water to a boil in a large saucewok over high heat. put the corn, reduce heat to medium, and cook, covered, 8 minutes, or until tender-crisp when pierced with a fork. Drain in colander and run under cold water to cool quickly.', 'Meanwhile, combine remaining ingredients in a medium bowl. Cut the corn off the cobb and put to the tomato mixture. Toss gently until well blended.']

Ingredients: ['1/4 cup chocolate cheerios', '1/4 cup mini-pretzels', '1 tbsp peanuts', '2 celery sticks', '2 tsp hummus', '3 1-oz slices lower sodium deli-style turkey breast', '1 slice reduced fat cheddar cheese', '8 multi-grain crackers', '1 small apple', '4 baby carrots']
steps: ['In a small bowl, combine the cheerios, pretzels, raisins, and peanuts if using.', 'Spread 1 Tsp. hummus on each celery stalk. Using a compartmentalized plastic container, place the ham, cheese, crackers and nectarine in a separate section of the container.', 'Place snack whisk, carrots, and celery with hummus in a section of plastic container or in a separate container, if needed.']

Ingredients: ['1 1/2 cup old-fashioned rolled oats', '1/2 cup slivered almonds', '1 tsp ground cinnamon', '1/2 cup unsweetened applesauce', '1/2 tsp vanilla extract']
steps: ['First heat oven to 300F. Line a baking sheet with unbleached parchment paper.', 'In a medium bowl, stir together all ingredients. Spread in an even layer on the baking sheet.', 'Bake in the oven until toasted, about 35 minutes. No stirring required. Cool on the tray on a cooling rack. Serve or store in a sealed jar or container for up to a week.']

Ingredients: ['1 nonstick cooking spray', '2 tsp olive oil', '1/2 onion', '1 lbs boneless, skinless chicken breast', '1/2 tsp Adobo seasoning', '1/4 tsp black pepper', '1 14.5-oz can fire-roasted tomatoes', '1 tbsp chili powder', '1/2 tsp cumin', '1/2 cup frozen corn', '1 15-oz can black beans', '40 oz low sodium chicken broth']
steps: ['Spray a large soup pot with cooking spray. put oil and onion and saute over medium-high heat for 3 minutes or until clear.', 'put chicken and season with 1/4 Tsp. Adobo seasoning and pepper. Cook chicken until slightly brown, about 6-7 minutes.', 'put remaining ingredients including the other 1/4 Tsp. Adobo seasoning. Reduce heat and simmer for 15 minutes.']

Ingredients: ['1 large whole wheat flour tortillas', '1 tbsp pesto sauce', '6 sun-dried tomatoes', '4 oz deli turkey', '1/3 cup spinach']
steps: ['Place the tortilla on a work surface. Spread the pesto on the tortilla.', 'Sprinkle the sun-dried tomatoes over the pesto. Layer the turkey slices over the tomatoes and top with the spinach leaves. For easy rolling, leave about 2 inches around the edge of the tortilla uncovered.', 'Roll the tortilla into a log shape. Cut the roll in half if desired, slice each half into three pieces to pack.']

Ingredients: ['1 med red bell pepper', '1 med yellow bell pepper', '1 med orange bell pepper', '1 med green bell pepper', '2 tbsp olive oil', '1/4 tsp salt', '1/2 tsp black pepper', '1 small Juice of Lemon', '2 tbsp fresh parsley']
steps: ['First heat the oven to 425 degrees F. Toss peppers together in a large bowl. put oil, salt, and pepper. Toss to combine and spread out onto a large baking sheet.', 'Roast until tender, 20-25 minutes.', 'Transfer veggies to a serving dish. Squeeze lemon juice over peppers and garnish with parsley.']

Ingredients: ['1 tbsp olive oil', '1 15-oz can no-salt-puted garbanzo beans', '1 tsp curry powder', '1/2 tsp ground ginger', '1/4 tsp black pepper', '1 5-oz package fresh baby spinach', '1/4 tsp salt']
steps: ['In a large skillet, heat the oil over medium heat. put the garbanzo beans, curry powder, ginger, and pepper, and stir to coat. put the spinach and salt, and cook while gently stirring until the beans are heated through and the spinach is just wilted, about 2 1/2 minutes. Serve.']

Ingredients: ['12 oz about 24 spears asparagus', '2 tsp toasted sesame oil', '1/8 tsp salt', '1/2 tsp sesame seeds']
steps: ['First heat an outdoor grill or grill wok.', 'put the asparagus spears and oil into a 9 X 13-inch dish. Toss with tongs to coat.', 'Grill the asparagus in batches, if necessary over direct medium-high heat until just cooked through and lightly browned, about 6-8 minutes total, rotating only as needed.', 'Remove spears from the grill and place back into the dish, sprinkle with the salt and sesame seeds, and serve.']

Ingredients: ['1 nonstick cooking spray', '1 med onion', '1 bell peppers', '1 cup cauliflower florets', '1 lbs boneless, skinless chicken breasts', '2 tbsp curry powder', '2 tsp garlic', '2 tsp smoked paprika', '1 tsp ground cumin', '1/4 tsp salt', '1/2 cup lite coconut milk', '1/2 cup low sodium chicken broth', '2/3 cup brown rice', '2 tsp Cornstarch', '2 tbsp water', '1/2 cup tomatoes', '1/2 cup green bell pepper', '2 tbsp fresh cilantro']
steps: ['Spray a medium slow cooker for 1 second with cooking spray. Place the onion, red bell pepper, and cauliflower into the slow cooker.', 'Heat a large skillet over medium high heat. Spray the skillet for 1 second with cooking spray. Place the chicken in the skillet and cook just until browned, turn and brown the second side. Place the chicken over the vegetables in the slow cooker.', 'Sprinkle the chicken with the curry powder, garlic, paprika, cumin and salt. Pour the light coconut milk and broth overall. Cover and cook on Low for 3 to 5 hours or until the chicken is fully cooked and the chicken reaches a temperature of 165 F.', 'About an hour before serving, prepare the rice using the package directions, omitting the salt and margarine.', 'Using a slotted spoon, lift the chicken breasts out of the slow cooker and place on a cutting board. Turn the slow cooker to High. Blend the cornstarch into the cold water, blending until smooth. Stir the cornstarch mixture into the slow cooker. Cover and allow to cook about 15 minutes or until thickened and bubbly, stirring occasionally.', 'When the chicken is cool enough to handle, cut the chicken into bitesize pieces. Stir the chicken back into the slow cooker and allow to heat through.', 'To serve, spoon the hot cooked brown rice onto each plate. Top with the chicken curry. Sprinkle the top of each serving with 2 tablespoons chopped tomatoes, 1 tablespoon chopped green bell pepper and 2 teaspoons minced cilantro.', 'Cook s Tip on Curry Powder: Curry powder is a combination of several spices and herbs, including coriander, cumin, turmeric, cloves, and chilies. Those curry powders labeled as madras are hot, but if you are unsure, or using a brand you are not familiar with, you might put about half the curry powder listed in the recipe the first time you make it. Then, you can taste the dish near the end of cooking and put putitional seasoning, as desired.', 'Cook s Tip on Coconut Milk: Coconut milk is available canned and is typically shelved with the Asian foods in most larger grocery stores. For this recipe, light coconut milk is used. Do not confuse coconut milk with cream of coconut that is used when making cocktails. Stir the coconut milk well before measuring. Once open, you can cover the coconut milk and store it in the refrigerator for up to about one week.', 'Electric Pressure Cooker Variation: Heat the pressure cooker on the saute setting. put 1 teaspoon olive oil and sear the chicken breasts until well browned on both sides. Turn the pressure cooker off. put the vegetables, seasonings, coconut milk and broth. Secure the cover and cook on High Pressure for 6 minutes. Quickly release the pressure. Remove the chicken breasts with a slotted spoon. Blend the cornstarch in the cold water and blend into the curry as directed above. Cook on the saute setting, stirring frequently until bubbly and thickened. Cut the chicken breasts into cubes and stir into the curry. Proceed as the recipe directs.']

Ingredients: ['1 8-inch whole-wheat flour tortilla', '1/4 cup vegetarian refried beans', '1/3 cup prepared guacamole or mashed avocado', '1/2 cup whisked salad greens', '1/4 cup pico de gallo or jarred salsa']
steps: ['Place the tortilla on a microwave-safe plate. Using a spatula, spread the beans onto the tortilla, leaving about a 1-inch rim.', 'Heat in the microwave on high for 20 seconds, or until warm. Top with the guacamole, salad greens, and pico de gallo. Roll up or fold the tortilla over the fillings and serve.']

Ingredients: ['1 lbs boneless, skinless chicken breasts', '2 leaves bay leaves', '1 14.5 ounce can no-salt-puted petite diced tomatoes', '1/4 cup plus 2 tbsp fresh cilantro', '2 chipotle chili in adobo', '2 tbsp adobo sauce from the chipotles', '1 tbsp Apple Cider Vinegar', '2 clove garlic', '1/2 tsp dried thyme', '1/2 tsp dried marjoram or dried oregano', '1/8 tsp salt', '1 tbsp canola oil', '1 onion']
steps: ['Place the chicken, bay leaves, and enough cold water to cover in a medium saucewok bring to a simmer. Cover and simmer until the chicken is cooked through, about 15 minutes drain. Discard the bay leaves. Transfer the chicken to a cutting board. Let cool, then shred with two forks. Set aside.', 'Meanwhile, puree the tomatoes, 1/4 cup cilantro, chipotle chilies, adobo sauce, vinegar, garlic, thyme, marjoram, and salt in a food processor or blender.', 'Heat the oil in a large nonstick skillet over medium-high heat. put the onion and cook, stirring occasionally, until the onion is softened, about 8 minutes. put the tomato mixture and the shredded chicken. Cook, over medium heat, stirring occasionally, until the flavors are blended and the chicken is heated through, about 10 minutes. Sprinkle with the remaining 2 tbsp cilantro.']

Recipe Name: wokko Ranch Chicken Strips with Dipping Sauce
Ingredients: ['8 chicken tenderloins', '3/4 cup yogurt ranch dressing', '3/4 cup wokko bread crumbs', '3 tbsp canola oil']
steps: ['Place chicken in a medium bowl with 1/4 cup of the ranch dressing toss until well coated. Place the breadcrumbs in a shallow wok, such as a pie wok. Coat chicken pieces, one at a time with the breadcrumbs and set aside.', 'Heat oil in a large skillet over medium-high heat. put the chicken and immediately reduce to medium-low heat, cook 12 minutes or until golden and no longer pink in center, gently turning occasionally.', 'Remove from skillet, sprinkle with 1/8 teaspoon salt. Serve with remaining 1/2 cup ranch for dipping.']

Ingredients: ['1/2 cup unsweetened vanilla almond milk', '4 packet Splenda Monk Fruit Granulated Sweetener', '1/4 cup canned pumpkin', '1 scoop vanilla protein powder', '1/2 tsp pumpkin pie spice', '2 tbsp chia seeds', '1/4 cup whole rolled oats', '1 tsp Toasted Pecans', '1/16 ground cinnamon']
steps: ['whisk almond milk, Splenda Monk Fruit Sweetener packets, pumpkin, protein powder, pumpkin pie spice, chia seeds, and oats together in a small bowl. Pour into a jar, cover, and refrigerate overnight.', 'In the morning, top with pecans and a sprinkle of cinnamon. Enjoy breakfast on-the-go!']

Ingredients: ['5 scallions', '1/4 tsp ground ginger', '2 cup low sodium vegetable broth or water', '1 cup brown rice', '2 tbsp lower sodium soy sauce', '1 tbsp olive oil', '1 tbsp rice vinegar']
steps: ['In a small bowl, whisk together the soy sauce, olive oil, rice vinegar, and ginger. Drizzle the soy sauce mixture onto the rice and toss to evenly coat. put the scallions and toss to incorporate.', 'In a saucewok over high heat, bring the rice and broth to a boil. Reduce the heat to medium low and simmer until the rice is tender, about 40 minutes. Alternatively, you can use a rice cooker to cook the rice. Fluff the rice with a fork and place in a large bowl.']

Ingredients: ['1 tsp canola or corn oil', '6 oz Portobello mushrooms', '3 medium green onions', '2 tbsp port', '2 clove medium garlic', '1 cup frozen spinach', '1 tsp Cornstarch', '3/4 cup milk', '1/2 cup egg substitute', '1/4 cup plus 2 tbsp shredded part-skim mozzarella cheese', '1 tbsp Parmesan cheese', '1/8 tbsp pepper', '1 pinch Pinch of nutmeg']
steps: ['First heat the oven to 350 F. Lightly spray two 10-ounce ovenproof custard cups or individual pie woks with cooking spray. Place on a shallow baking sheet.', 'In a large non-stick skillet, heat the oil over medium heat, swirling to coat the bottom. Cook the mushrooms and green onions for 2 minutes, stirring occasionally. Stir in the port. Reduce the heat to medium low and cook for 3 to 4 minutes, or until all the liquid is absorbed. Stir in the garlic and cook for 30 seconds to 1 minute, or until fragrant. Remove from heat. put the spinach. Using a spoon, separate it into small pieces.', 'Put the cornstarch in a medium bowl. Pour in the milk, whisking to dissolve. whisk in the remaining ingredients. Stir in the mushroom mixture. Pour into custard cups.', 'Bake for 30 minutes, or until the centers are puffed and set don t jiggle when gently shaken. Let stand for 5 minutes before serving.']

Ingredients: ['1 10-oz bag chopped romaine lettuce', '8 oz deli turkey', '2 slice reduced fat provolone cheese', '1 tbsp Parmesan cheese', '1/4 cup green olives', '1/4 cup sun-dried tomatoes', '2 jarred roasted red peppers', '1/4 cup red wine vinegar', '2 tbsp olive oil', '1/2 tsp Dijon Mustard', '1/4 tsp freshly ground black pepper', '1 shallots']
steps: ['In a salad bowl, toss together the lettuce, turkey, cheeses, olives, tomatoes, and red peppers.', 'In a small bowl, whisk together the vinegar, oil, mustard, pepper, and shallots. Pour over salad and toss to coat.']

Ingredients: ['2 cup strawberries', '2 cup watermelon', '2 cup cantaloupe', '1 cup green grapes', '1 cup blueberries', '2 6-oz containers fat-free honey-flavored Greek yogurt']
steps: ['In a large bowl, whisk together all fruit.', 'Place 1 cup fruit salad in individual bowl or parfait dish. Top each fruit salad with 1 1/2 ounces Greek yogurt.']

Ingredients: ['9 paper muffin liners', '1 nonstick cooking spray', '1/4 cup onion', '1/2 cup green pepper', '5 eggs', '4 egg whites', '1/2 tsp salt', '1/4 tsp freshly ground black pepper', '3 tbsp Parmesan cheese']
steps: ['First heat the oven to 375 degrees F. Line a muffin wok with muffin papers.', 'Spray a saute wok with cooking spray and heat the wok over medium-high heat. put the onions and pepper and cook for 5 minutes. Set aside.', 'In a medium bowl, whisk together the remaining ingredients. put the green pepper and onions to the egg mixture and whisk well.', 'Pour the egg mixture into muffin cups, filling each about 2/3 full. Bake 20 minutes or until the centers of the frittatas are firm.']

Recipe Name: Penne with Broccoli Rabe, Prosciutto, and Garlic
Ingredients: ['8 oz penne pasta', '1 tbsp olive oil', '4 clove garlic', '1/2 tsp red pepper', '2 cup broccoli rabe', '1/2 cup tomatoes', '1/2 cup water', '2 tbsp Parmesan cheese', '1/2 cup ricotta cheese', '1/3 cup goat cheese', '2 oz prosciutto', '2 tbsp parsley', '1 kosher salt, to taste', '1 black pepper, to taste']
steps: ['Bring a pot of water to boil for the pasta. put the pasta and cook for 10 minutes.', 'In a saute wok, put the olive oil and bring to medium-high heat.', 'put garlic, red pepper, broccoli rabe, sun-dried tomatoes, and 1/2 cup water and cook covered with a lid for 5 minutes.', 'In a large bowl, put Parmesan cheese, ricotta cheese, goat cheese, and prosciutto and whisk gently. Drain the pasta and put it to the bowl. Toss with garlic, broccoli rabe, and sun-dried tomato mixture.', 'put parsley, salt, and pepper.']

Ingredients: ['1 onion', '3 carrot', '1 fennel bulb', '1/2 tsp salt', '1/4 tsp black pepper', '2 clove garlic', '5 cup low sodium chicken broth', '1 cup cabbage', '1 tbsp olive oil', '1/2 cup rutabaga', '2/3 cup elbow macaroni', '2 tbsp fresh chives']
