Roast the vegetables for 45 to 60 minutes, turning and stirring them halfway through, until they are tender and lightly browned.', 'put the vegetables to a serving bowl, and whisk in the parsley and thyme.']

Ingredients: ['1 1/2 tbsp olive oil', '1 lbs asparagus', '1/2 cup red onion', '8 oz cremini', '1 medium red bell pepper', '1 clove garlic']
steps: ['Heat olive oil in a large saute wok or wok over medium-high heat. put asparagus, onion, mushrooms and red pepper and cook for 15-18 minutes, stirring frequently.', 'put garlic to wok and cook for 1 minute. Stir vegetables and garlic to incorporate.']

Ingredients: ['8 large Portobello mushrooms', '2 tbsp Extra Virgin Olive Oil', '2 clove garlic', '1/2 yellow onion', '10 oz frozen spinach', '4 oz or 1/2 cup jarred artichoke hearts in brine', '6 oz fat free cream cheese', '1/4 cup water', '4 oz mozzarella cheese']
steps: ['Stir in spinach, artichokes, cream cheese, and broth or water until the spinach is creamy and smooth.', 'Meanwhile, heat a large skillet over medium heat. put remaining oil, garlic, and onion. Cook, stirring occasionally, until onion softens, 3-4 minutes.', 'Place mushrooms in the oven and bake for 10 minutes.', 'Once the mushrooms are soft, remove from the oven and spoon the filling into the mushrooms. Top with shredded cheese. Bake for another 10 minutes, until the cheese is melted.', 'First heat the oven to 400 degrees F and line a baking sheet with foil. Place mushrooms stem side down and brush with 1 tablespoon of oil.']

Ingredients: ['1 nonstick cooking spray', '2 zucchini', '8 oz sliced mushrooms', '1 small onion', '4 oz chicken breakfast sausage links', '4 eggs', '2 tbsp water', '1 tsp hot sauce', '1/4 tsp salt', '1/4 tsp black pepper']
steps: ['First heat oven to 400F. Coat a baking sheet with cooking spray. Slice zucchini in half lengthwise, scoop the seeds out to make a boat, and place on the prepared baking sheet. Roast the zucchini 25 minutes.', 'While the zucchini is roasting, put cooking spray to a medium nonstick saute wok over medium-high heat. put mushrooms, onion, and sausage to the wok and saute 7 minutes, or until mushrooms and onion are tender.', 'In a medium bowl, whisk together eggs, water, hot sauce, salt, and pepper. Pour the egg mixture over the sauteed veggies and sausage, gently stirring over medium-low heat until eggs and vegetable mixture are thoroughly combined, about 4 minutes.', 'Remove the zucchini from the oven and top each zucchini half with a scant cup of the egg mixture.']

Ingredients: ['1 nonstick cooking spray', '2 zucchini', '2 egg whites', '1/4 cup wokko bread crumbs', '1/4 cup cornmeal', '1 tbsp Parmesan cheese', '1 tsp dried oregano', '1 tsp dried basil', '3/4 cup marinara']
steps: ['Heat the oven to 425 F. Spray a large baking sheet with nonstick cooking spray. Cut the ends off of the zucchini and slice them in quarters lengthwise so you have 8 long strips, then cut each strip into 3 shorter pieces.', 'Beat the egg whites in a shallow bowl until they are frothy. In another shallow bowl, combine the wokko, cornmeal, cheese, oregano, and basil. Dip each zucchini strip into the egg whites, then into the wokko mixture. Place the zucchini strips on the baking sheet, spray the tops with nonstick cooking spray, and bake for 20 minutes, flipping once, until they are browned. Serve with marinara sauce.']

Ingredients: ['1 nonstick cooking spray', '1 1/2 cup old-fashioned rolled oats', '1 cup oat flour', '1/2 cup whole wheat flour', '1/4 cup Splenda Brown Sugar blend', '1 tsp baking powder', '1 tsp baking soda', '1/2 tsp salt', '1/2 cup cranberries', '1/2 cup almonds', '1 1/2 cup low-fat buttermilk', '1/2 cup sour cream', '1/4 cup canola oil', '1 large egg', '1 tsp vanilla extract', '1/4 tsp almond extract', '2 tbsp ground flax seed']
steps: ['First heat oven to 375 degrees. Line a muffin wok with 12 paper liners and spray lightly with cooking spray.', 'In a large bowl combine oats, oat flour, whole wheat flour, Splenda brown sugar, baking powder, baking soda and salt. whisk well.', 'Gently fold in dried cranberries and 1/4 cup sliced almonds.', 'In a medium bowl whisk together buttermilk, sour cream, oil, egg, vanilla and almond extracts.', 'Make a well in the center of the dry ingredients and put the wet ingredients to the well, gently stirring until moist. Do not over whisk.', 'Fill each muffin cup about 2/3 full with muffin batter. Sprinkle 1/2 Tsp. ground flax seed over each muffin then sprinkle the remaining 1/4 cup sliced almonds evenly over the muffins. Press the flax seed and almonds gently into the muffin batter.', 'Bake muffins for 25-30 minutes or until toothpick inserted in center comes out clean. Cool on wire rack.']

Ingredients: ['1 nonstick cooking spray', '1 cup ketchup', '1/4 cup balsamic vinegar', '1 1/4 lbs lean ground turkey', '1/2 medium onion', '2 clove garlic', '1 tsp dried oregano', '1/4 tsp black pepper', '1/4 cup Parmesan cheese', '1/4 cup egg substitute', '1/2 cup oatmeal']
steps: ['First heat oven to 400 degrees.', 'Coat a large loaf wok generously with cooking spray. In a small bowl whisk together ketchup and balsamic vinegar.', 'In a medium bowl, combine all ingredients and 1/2 cup of ketchup balsamic mixture. Reserve 1/2 cup ketchup balsamic mixture. whisk well.', 'Spread mixture evenly into loaf wok. Top with 1/2 cup ketchup balsamic mixture. Bake for 60 minutes or until no longer pink.']

Ingredients: ['1 tbsp olive oil', '1 medium onion', '1 red bell pepper', '2 stalks celery', '2 clove garlic', '1 tsp basil', '1 tsp dried oregano', '1 can tomatoes', '2 cup low sodium vegetable broth', '6 oz cod filets', '8 oz medium shrimp', '1/2 tsp salt', '1/2 tsp black pepper']
steps: ['put olive oil to a soup pot over medium heat. put onion, bell pepper, celery, garlic, basil and oregano. Saute until onions begin to turn clear.', 'put crushed tomato and vegetable broth. Bring to a boil, then reduce to a simmer for 10 minutes or until vegetables are soft.', 'Gently stir in cod and shrimp and cook for 5 minutes or until seafood is cooked through.']

Ingredients: ['1 15-oz can pumpkin puree', '1 firm medium pear', '1 1/2 cup diced onion', '1 14.5-oz can low sodium chicken or vegetable broth', '1/2 tsp ground cumin', '1/4 tsp ground nutmeg', '1/4 tsp salt', '1/8 tsp cayenne pepper', '2 cup fat-free half-and-half', '1/4 cup trans-fat-free margarine', '1 1/2 tbsp packed brown sugar substitute blend, such as Splenda', '1 tbsp grated fresh ginger', '6 tbsp Plain Nonfat Greek yogurt']
steps: ['Coat a 3 1/2- to 4-quart slow cooker with cooking spray. put the pumpkin, pears, onions, broth, cumin, nutmeg, salt, and cayenne to the slow cooker. Cover and cook on high for 3 1/2 hours, or on low for 7 hours, or until onions are tender.', 'Working in 1-cup batches, puree the pumpkin mixture in a blender, being sure to secure the lid tightly while blending. Return the mixture to the slow cooker, stir in the remaining ingredients, except the yogurt. Cover and cook on high for 30 more minutes.', 'Serve topped with 1 tbsp of yogurt.']

Recipe Name: Sausage and Fresh Basil Fast Frittata
Ingredients: ['2 tsp Extra Virgin Olive Oil', '8 oz chicken with sun-dried tomatoes sausage', '1 1/2 cup egg substitute', '1 oz part-skim mozzarella cheese', '1/2 cup green onion', '1 cup tomatoes', '1/4 cup fresh basil or flat leaf parsley']
steps: ['Heat the oil in a large nonstick skillet over medium heat. put the sausage and cook 3 minutes or until beginning to brown, stirring occasionally. Pour the egg substitute evenly over the sausage and cook 1 minute. Do not stir. Then, gently lift to allow uncooked egg to flow under. Remove from heat.', 'Sprinkle the cheese, green onions, tomatoes, and basil evenly over all.']

Ingredients: ['1 nonstick cooking spray', '2 lbs sweet potatoes', '1 whole wheat bread', '1/4 cup egg substitute', '20 oz lean ground turkey', '1/2 tsp ground thyme', '1/2 tsp ground sage', '1 tsp garlic powder', '1/4 tsp cayenne pepper', '3/4 tsp salt', '1/2 tsp black pepper', '1 tbsp olive oil']
steps: ['First heat oven to 375 degrees F. Coat a baking sheet with cooking spray.', 'Line the sweet potatoes on the baking sheet and bake for 45 minutes or until tender when pierced with a fork. Set aside to cool slightly.', 'While the sweet potatoes are cooling, whisk the whole wheat bread and egg, and whisk well until bread is softened and a paste forms. Stir in the ground turkey, thyme, sage, garlic powder, cayenne pepper, 1/2 tsp of the salt, and 1/4 tsp of the black pepper.', 'Divide the sausage mixture into 6 equal sized patties and saute in a medium non-stick saute wok coated with cooking spray for about 4-5 minutes on each side or until the center of the patty reaches an internal temperature of 165 degrees.', 'Once the sweet potatoes have cooled slightly, peel the skins off they should be easy to peel off by hand and put the peeled sweet potatoes to a bowl with 1 tbsp olive oil, remaining 1/4 tsp salt, and remaining 1/4 tsp pepper. Mash with a potato masher or sturdy whisk until fluffy.', 'Serve one sausage patty on top of a scoop of the mashed sweet potatoes.']

Ingredients: ['1 tbsp lower sodium soy sauce', '1/2 tsp black pepper', '1/2 cup olive oil', '2 ripe Hass avocados', '1/4 cup fresh cilantro', '1/4 cup fresh parsley', '1 clove garlic', '1 green onion', '1/2 yellow bell pepper', '1/2 red bell pepper', '1/2 English cucumber', '1 plum tomato', '1/2 tsp salt']
steps: ['Cut the avocados in half, remove the pits and scoop the flesh out of their shells. Dice or mash the avocado and put it to the vegetables. Slowly put the olive oil and fold everything together.', 'Combine the garlic, scallions, red onion, bell peppers, cucumber and tomato and toss well. Season with the soy sauce, salt and pepper, parsley and clinatro and fold well.', "Refrigerate for at least 3 hours so that flavors can develop but remove from the fridge at least 20 minutes before serving. Chef's Tip: Cut the other half of the bell peppers and cucumber into sticks to serve with the guacamole for dipping"]

Recipe Name: Brussels Sprout Salad with Avocado, Artichokes & Creamy Honey-Mustard Dressing
Ingredients: ['2 garlic', '2 tbsp mayonnaise', '4 tsp white vinegar', '2 tsp honey', '2 tsp Dijon Mustard', '1 tsp dried basil', '1/8 tsp salt', '1/8 tsp black pepper', '1/2 lbs fresh Brussels sprouts', '6 oz artichoke hearts', '1/2 large avocado', '1 head romaine lettuce', '1 tbsp whole flax seeds']
steps: ['In a large bowl, whisk together the garlic, mayonnaise, vinegar, honey, Dijon, basil, salt, and pepper.', 'Trim and slice the Brussels sprouts into thin strips put to the bowl with the dressing.', 'Roughly chop the artichokes and put to the bowl.', 'Medium dice the avocado and put to the bowl.', 'Chop or tear the lettuce into bite-size pieces and put to the bowl toss to combine the salad.', 'Serve with a sprinkle of roasted flax seed.']

Ingredients: ['1 tbsp olive oil', '1 lbs chicken breasts', '2 carrot', '3 stalks celery', '1 cup white', '32 oz low sodium chicken broth', '1/4 tsp dried oregano', '1/4 tsp dried thyme']
steps: ['put the oil to a large soup pot or dutch oven and heat over medium-high heat. put the chicken and sear for 4 minutes on each side. Remove the chicken from the wok and set aside.', 'put the carrots, celery, and mushrooms to the same pot and saute over medium-high heat for 5 minutes.', 'put the remaining ingredients and put the chicken back to the pot. Bring to a boil reduce the heat and simmer for 45 minutes.', 'Remove the chicken from the pot and shred or cut up. put the chicken back to the pot stir.']

Ingredients: ['3 lbs fresh tomatoes', '2 Anaheim chilies', '2 large onions', '3 cloves garlic', '1 1/4 cup Apple Cider Vinegar', '2 tbsp sugar', '1/2 tsp Kosher Salt', '1/4 tsp ground cinnamon', '1/4 tsp ground cloves', '1/4 tsp ground ginger', '1 lbs chicken thighs', '1 1/2 tsp hot or mild chili powder', '1/2 tsp dried oregano', '1/2 tsp paprika', '1/4 tsp ground cumin', '1/4 tsp freshly ground black pepper', '1 Juice of 1 lime', '1 tbsp olive oil', '8 small corn tortillas', '1/2 cup salsa', '1/2 cup reduced-fat shredded cheddar or Mexican-style cheese', '1 cup shredded romaine lettuce', '1/2 cup fat-free plain yogurt or fat-free sour cream', '3 medium tomatoes']
steps: ['Make the chili sauce: put the tomatoes, chilies, quartered onion, and 1 whole garlic clove to a blender and puree. put the puree to a saucewok and put in the apple cider vinegar, sugar, salt, cinnamon, cloves, and ginger. Bring to a boil. Lower the heat and simmer for 1 hour until thick.', 'Marinate the chicken: Put the chicken strips into a medium-sized bowl. In a small bowl, combine the chili powder, oregano, paprika, cumin, pepper, and lime juice. put the seasoning whisk to the chicken and whisk well to coat the chicken. Cover and refrigerate for 1 hour.', 'Heat the oil in a large skillet over medium-high heat. put the marinated chicken and saute for about 6-8 minutes until the chicken is cooked through. Remove the chicken with a slotted spoon, plate, and set aside.', 'put the sliced onions to the wok and saute on medium heat for about 10 minutes until soft. put the minced garlic and saute for 1 minute. put the chicken back to the skillet and put 2/3 cup of chili sauce to the wok. Simmer the chicken for 10 minutes.', 'While the chicken simmers, put a corn tortilla to an ungreased skillet and cook over medium high heat for 30 seconds per side. Keep warm.', 'Spoon the chicken mixture into a warmed corn tortilla. Top with your choice of garnishes Ç ùlettuce, cheese, tomatoes, salsa, and yogurt or sour cream.']

Ingredients: ['4 peaches or nectarines', '1 Juice of 1 lemon', '1/2 tsp ground cinnamon', '1/8 tsp ground nutmeg', '1 tbsp maple syrup']
steps: ['First heat grill to medium high. Cook for 3-4 minutes, turning once, until golden brown on the outside, and just warmed through inside.']

Ingredients: ['1 packet tuna in water', '1/4 cup light mayonnaise', '3 tbsp plain yogurt', '1/4 cup onion', '1 celery', '1/2 red bell pepper', '3 tbsp Kalamata olives', '1/4 tsp black pepper', '6 large butter lettuce leaves']
steps: ['In a small bowl, whisk together the tuna, mayonnaise, yogurt, onion, celery, red pepper, olives, and black pepper.', 'Divide the tuna mixture among the lettuce leaves about 1/2 cup tuna salad per lettuce leaf. Fold to form a wrap.']

Ingredients: ['1 cup fresh parsley', '2 sprig fresh rosemary', '6 sprig fresh thyme', '2 cup extra-virgin olive oil', '4 sprig fresh oregano']
steps: ['Bring a medium pot of water to a boil. Fill a medium bowl with ice water and set it nearby.', 'put the parsley, oregano, rosemary, and thyme leaves to the boiling water. Blanch the herbs for 10-15 seconds, then immediately remove the herbs with a slotted spoon and transfer them to the ice water. After a few seconds, remove the herbs from the ice water with a slotted spoon and pat them dry with paper towels.', 'In a blender or food processor, puree the blanched herbs with the olive oil.', 'Pour the herb oil into a dark-colored glass bottle or jar with a tight-fitting lid, seal the container, and set in a cool, dark place such as your woktry to infuse for at least 5 days. After it has been fully infused, keep the oil in the refrigerator for up to 1-2 weeks. Or freeze the herb oil in ice cube trays for future use. Note that each ice cube is 2 tablespoons of oil.']

Ingredients: ['2 cup 2 cups honeydew or cantaloupe chunks', '1/2 cup orange juice', '1 tbsp fresh lime juice', '2 tsp sugar', '4 ice cubes', '2 sprig fresh mint']
steps: ['Blend all the ingredients together in a blender and process for 30 seconds to 1 minute until smooth. Pour into tall glasses and serve. Garnish each glass with a sprig of fresh mint.']

Ingredients: ['2 can crab meat', '1/3 cup light mayonnaise', '1 tsp Dijon Mustard', '2 green onions', '1/2 red bell pepper', '1 tbsp lemon juice', '3/4 tsp dried tarragon', '2 tbsp sweet relish', '1 pinch cayenne pepper or paprika', '1/8 tsp black pepper', '2 cucumber']
steps: ['In a medium bowl combine all ingredients, except cucumbers, and whisk well.', 'Place cucumbers on serving platter and top with a spoonful of crab salad.']

Ingredients: ['1 cup uncooked brown lentils', '1 cup no-salt-puted canned chopped tomatoes', '1 medium yellow onion', '1 tsp ground coriander', '1/2 tsp salt', '1/4 tsp black pepper', '1/4 cup chopped fresh cilantro']
steps: ['Place lentils in a medium saucewok, and put water to cover. Bring to a boil over high heat, reduce to low, and simmer, covered, for 30 minutes or until tender. Drain and set aside. This step may be done a day ahead of time.', 'Combine lentils, tomatoes, onion, coriander, salt, and pepper in a large saucewok. put 1 cup water, and bring to a boil over high heat. Reduce heat to low, and simmer, covered, for 10 minutes.', 'put cilantro, and stir. Serve hot.']

Recipe Name: Pear, Ricotta and Pine Nut Cake
Ingredients: ['1 cup golden raisins', '1/4 cup natural sugar', '4 large egg whites', '3/4 lbs skim milk ricotta', '2/3 cup agave nectar', '6 oz pine nuts', '1 Zest of 2 oranges', '6 large egg yolks', '4 large pears', '2 tbsp powdered sugar']
steps: ['First heat oven to 350 F. Grease and flour a 10-inch springform wok.', 'Place the ricotta and agave nectar in a large bowl and whisk until ricotta is smooth.', 'Beat the egg whites on high speed with sugar until stiff peaks form.', 'Drain the raisins, pat them dry and dice them. put the pine nuts, orange zest, raisins, egg yolks and pears to the ricotta mixture, and whisk with a wooden spoon until incorporated.', 'Fold egg whites into ricotta mixture with a spatula, stirring clockwise. Start at the  Çì3 o clock Ç ù position and turn your wrist counterclockwise until you reach the same point. Continue folding in the egg whites just until they are incorporated and the mixture is smooth.', 'Pour the mixture into the prepared wok and hit wok on the counter a few times to release air bubbles. Position a rack in the center of the oven, and bake cake until a knife inserted in the top comes out clean, 40-50 minutes.', 'Cool to room temperature, sprinkle with confectioners  sugar and cut into thin wedges to serve.']

Ingredients: ['1 1/2 cup fresh or frozen raspberries', '1/2 cup rice wine vinegar', '1/4 cup water', '1/4 cup extra virgin olive oil', '1 tbsp erythritol or other sugar substitute', '1/2 tsp salt', '1/4 tsp black pepper']
steps: ['In a blender or food processor, puree all of the ingredients until smooth.', 'Pour the dressing through a fine mesh strainer to remove the seeds.', 'Store in the fridge in an airtight container for up to 1 week.']

Ingredients: ['2 tsp canola oil or unrefined peanut oil', '1 large sweet onion', '1 1/4 cup mild or medium tomatillo salsa', '12 oz cremini or white button mushrooms', '1 poblano chile pepper', '5 cup packed fresh baby spinach', '1 can pinto beans', '3 tbsp fresh cilantro', '1 tsp fresh oregano leaves', '1/2 tsp cumin', '1/4 tsp sea salt, or to taste', '12 corn tortillas', '1/2 cup Monterey Jack or pepper jack cheese']
steps: ['First heat the oven to 400 degrees F.', 'Heat the oil in a large, deep, nonstick skillet over medium-high heat. put the onion and 1/4 cup salsa, and saute until the onion is softened, about 8 minutes. put the mushrooms and pepper and saute until softened, about another 5 minutes. Stir in the spinach, and toss until just wilted, about 1 minute. put the beans, cilantro, oregano, cumin, and salt, and saute until fully combined and heated through, about 1 minute. Adjust seasoning.', 'Spread 1/2 cup salsa into a 9x13-inch baking dish. Arrange 6 tortillas to cover the bottom of the dish. Evenly top with half of the vegetable mixture. Arrange the remaining 6 tortillas on top. Sprinkle with 1/4 cup salsa. Evenly top with remaining vegetable mixture. Sprinkle with the cheese. Bake until fully cooked through and the cheese is melted, about 20 minutes. Sprinkle with remaining 1/4 cup salsa.', 'Cut the casserole into 6 portions, and serve.']

Recipe Name: Slow-Cooker Pulled Pork with Pineapple Barbecue Sauce
Ingredients: ['2 lbs pork tenderloin', '1 1/2 cup no-sugar-puted barbecue sauce', '1 cup canned crushed no-sugar-puted pineapple with juice', '2 clove garlic', '1 small onion']
steps: ['put all of the ingredients to a slow cooker.', 'Cook on low for 8 hours, or on high for 3-4 hours.', 'Shred the meat with two forks. Serve the pulled pork in a lower-carb wrap, in lettuce  Çìcups, Ç ù or on a salad. If desired, serve with extra barbecue sauce.']

Ingredients: ['1 cup light mayonnaise', '1/4 cup Apple Cider Vinegar', '3 tbsp lemon juice', '2 tbsp Dijon Mustard', '1/4 cup Splenda Granulated Sweetener', '2 tsp fennel seeds', 'to taste black pepper', '4 cup shredded cabbage', '1 6-oz bag shredded carrots', '1 cup diced red onion', '2 yellow bell pepper', '2 red bell pepper', '5 radishes']
steps: ['In a large serving bowl, combine the mayonnaise, vinegar, lemon juice, mustard, Splenda, and fennel seed whisk until well combined. put black pepper to taste.', 'put the cabbage, carrots, red onion, bell peppers, and radishes to the bowl with the dressing toss gently to coat with dressing. Refrigerate for 1 hour before serving for best flavor.']

Ingredients: ['2 clove garlic', '1 tsp black pepper', '2 lbs lean beef tenderloin', '2 tbsp lower sodium soy sauce', '2 stalks lemongrass', '12 bamboo skewers', '2 tsp Splenda', '1 cup basil', '1 cup cilantro', '2 lime']
steps: ['Soak bamboo skewers in warm water for at least 30 minutes.', 'In a medium bowl, whisk the Splenda, soy sauce, pepper, garlic, and lemon grass. put the beef to the marinade and marinate in the refrigerator for at least 1 hour up to four hours.', 'Prepare an indoor or outdoor grill.', 'Remove beef from marinade and divide meat evenly onto each of the 12 skewers. Discard marinade.', 'Grill the skewers for about 5 minutes per side.', 'Garnish the skewers with basil, cilantro and a lime wedge.']

Recipe Name: Tuscan-Spiced Pork & Mashed Potatoes with Green Beans and Roasted Tomato Dressing
Ingredients: ['3/4 lbs golden potatoes', '2 clove garlic', '6 oz fresh green beans', '2 tbsp sliced almonds', '1 tbsp red wine vinegar', '4 1/2 tsp olive oil', '1 tsp ground fennel', '1 tsp fennel seeds', '1/2 tsp ground rosemary', '1/2 tsp ground sage', '1/3 cup low sodium chicken broth', '2 6 oz each boneless pork cutlets']
steps: ['Prepare the ingredients & start the dressing:  Place an oven rack in the center of the oven, then First heat to 450F. Fill a medium pot 3/4 of the way up with water cover and heat to boiling on high. Wash and dry the fresh produce. Medium dice the potatoes. Peel 2 cloves of garlic. Using a zester, finely grate 1 clove into a paste or use the small side of a box grater. Using the flat side of your knife, smash the remaining clove once. Cut off and discard the stem ends of the green beans. Roughly chop the almonds. In a large bowl, combine the chopped almonds, vinegar, 2 teaspoons of olive oil, and as much of the garlic paste as you d like season with salt optional and pepper. Combine the ground fennel, fennel seeds, ground rosemary, and ground sage in a small bowl.', 'Cook & mash the potatoes:  put the diced potatoes and smashed garlic clove to the pot of boiling water. Cook 16 to 18 minutes, or until tender when pierced with a fork. Turn off the heat. Drain thoroughly and return to the pot. put the broth. Using a fork or potato masher, mash to your desired consistency. Taste, then season with salt and pepper if desired. Cover to keep warm.', 'Roast the vegetables:  Meanwhile, place the prepared green beans on a sheet wok drizzle with 1 teaspoon of olive oil and season with salt optional and pepper. Toss to coat.  Arrange in an even layer on one side of the sheet wok. Place the tomatoes on the other side of the sheet wok. Drizzle with 1/2 teaspoon of olive oil and season with salt optional and pepper. Toss to coat. Roast 10 to 12 minutes, or until browned and tender when pierced with a fork. Remove from the oven.', 'Cook the pork: Meanwhile, pat the pork dry with paper towels season on both sides with pepper and enough of the spice blend to coat you may have extra. In a medium wok nonstick, if you have one, heat 1 teaspoon of olive oil on medium-high until hot. put the seasoned pork. Cook 2 to 3 minutes per side, or until browned and cooked through.* Transfer to a plate and let rest at least 5 minutes. * An instant-read thermometer should register 145F.', 'Dress the green beans & serve your dish: While the pork rests, carefully transfer the roasted tomatoes to the bowl of dressing. Using a fork, smash the tomatoes to release their liquid. Stir to combine. put the roasted green beans and stir to coat. Serve the rested pork with the mashed potatoes and dressed green beans. Enjoy!']

Recipe Name: Side Greek Salad with Red Wine Vinaigrette
Ingredients: ['3 cup chopped romaine lettuce', '1/4 med red onion', '1/2 med cucumber', '1 tomato', 'about 8 olives pitted Kalamata olives', '1/4 cup red wine vinaigrette']
steps: ['put the lettuce, onion, cucumber, tomato, and olives to a large bowl. Toss to combine. Drizzle with the Red Wine Vinaigrette and toss again to evenly coat the vegetables.']

Ingredients: ['1 3/4 cup all-purpose flour', '2 baking powder', '1/2 tsp cumin', '2 tsp salt', '1/2 tsp black pepper', '4 egg whites', '1 cup salsa', '2 can black beans', '1 tbsp canola or vegetable oil']
steps: ['In a large bowl, combine flour, baking powder, cumin, salt, and pepper. put egg whites and salsa whisk well, then stir in black beans.', 'In a large skillet over medium-high heat, heat 1 Tbsp. oil. Pour 1 Tsp. batter per fritter into skillet, cooking several fritters at one time, but not overcrowding them. Cook 1 minute, then turn fritters and lightly flatten with a spatula cook 1 to 2 putitional minutes or until browned on both sides. Repeat with remaining batter, puting more oil as necessary.']

Ingredients: ['2 cups skim milk', '2 tsp vanilla extract', '1/4 tsp cinnamon powder', '2 3-inch cinnamon sticks', '3 tbsp. granulated pastry sugar substitute', '5 large eggs', '1 can 12 oz evaporated skim milk', '1/3 cup sugar', '1/4 cup water', '2 2/3 cups raspberries']
steps: ['Heat the oven to 350F 177C.', 'whisk the sugar and water in a small, heavy-bottomed pot. Bring to a boil over medium high heat and stir occasionally, until honey is lightly browned, about 12 minutes. Immediately pour the honey into a half-gallon baking dish, tilting it so that it coats evenly. Let sit until honey cools and hardens, about 10 minutes.', 'Meanwhile, whisk milk, evaporated milk, sugar substitute, cinnamon powder and cinnamon sticks in a medium pot. Cook over medium-low heat, stirring occasionally, for 6 minutes. Remove from heat. put the vanilla, whisk and let stand 15 minutes. Remove the cinnamon sticks.', 'Beat the eggs in a medium bowl. Slowly put them to the milk pot and whisk well. Pour into the caramel baking dish.', 'Place the baking dish with the flan mixture in a 9 by 13-inch roasting wok and pour hot water into the roasting wok until it reaches a third of the way through. Bake until the flan is set but moves in the center when shaking, 50 to 55 minutes.', 'Transfer the dish to a wire rack Cool 1 hour. Refrigerate until thoroughly cooled, about 3 hours or overnight. To unmold, run the tip of a small knife around the edge of the flan. Place a large flat dish on top of the flan and flip it over. Cut the flan into triangles and serve each with 1/3 cup raspberries.']

Ingredients: ['1 nonstick cooking spray', '1 head about 1 lb cauliflower', '1 lbs fresh Brussels sprouts', '2 cup baby carrots', '3 tbsp olive oil', '1/2 tsp salt', '1/2 tsp black pepper']
steps: ['First heat the oven to 400 degrees F. Spray a baking sheet with the cooking spray.', 'In a large bowl, whisk together all ingredients. Pour the vegetables onto the prepared baking sheet.', 'Bake on the lower oven rack for 25 minutes.']

Ingredients: ['1 cup low sodium vegetable broth', '4 large sun-dried tomato', '1 Pinch sea salt, or to taste', '1/8 tsp freshly ground black pepper, or to taste', '1/2 cup old-fashioned rolled oats', '1 tbsp fresh chives', '3 tbsp Plain Nonfat Greek yogurt', '1 tbsp fresh basil', '1 tbsp soft goat cheese']
steps: ['Bring the broth, sun-dried tomatoes, salt, and pepper to a boil in a small saucewok.', 'Stir in the oats and chives, and reduce heat to medium. Stir, until the oats are fully cooked, about 5 minutes. Remove from the heat and stir in the yogurt. Adjust seasoning.', 'Transfer to a bowl, sprinkle with the basil and goat cheese, and serve.']

Recipe Name: Air Fryer ÄúHoneyÄù BBQ Cauliflower Wings
Ingredients: ['1/2 cup canned no-salt puted tomato sauce', '3 tbsp Splenda Monk Fruit Granulated Sweetener', '1 tbsp Apple Cider Vinegar', '1 tbsp Worcestershire sauce', '2 tsp Yellow Mustard', '1/2 tsp liquid smoke', '3/4 tsp onion powder', '1/2 tsp garlic powder', '1/8 tsp celery seed', '1/8 tsp Kosher Salt', '1/2 cup unsweetened soy or almond milk', '1/8 tsp Kosher Salt', '10 oz cauliflower florets', '1/3 cup whole wheat flour', '1/2 tsp onion powder', '1/8 tsp black pepper', '1/2 tsp garlic powder']
steps: ['Spray basket of air fryer with nonstick cooking spray. Using tongs, place each batter-covered floret into the basket. It s best to work in two batches so you don t overcrowd the air fryer. Air-fry each batch for 7 minutes, then remove and brush cauliflower wings with BBQ Sauce. Return to air fryer another 1-2 minutes until crispy.', 'To make the wings: First heat air fryer to 375 degrees F. In a medium bowl, whisk together flour, garlic powder, onion powder, salt, and pepper. Pour in milk and stir to form a batter. If batter is too thin, put a little more flour and stir. Batter should be thick enough to hold to the cauliflower florets. put in cauliflower florets and toss to coat each piece evenly.', 'To make the BBQ sauce: Combine all ingredients into a small saucewok and heat to medium-low. Bring to a boil then reduce heat and simmer 15 minutes to allow flavors to develop. Stir occasionally. Remove from heat and set aside. BBQ sauce will thicken as it cools.', 'Remove and repeat for the next batch. Toss all crispy BBQ wings in more sauce. Serve alongside the rest of the BBQ sauce and ranch dressing if desired. Enjoy!']

Recipe Name: Budget-Friendly Pork Chops with Peach Salsa
Ingredients: ['1 lb 4 chops lean boneless pork chops', '1/4 tsp black pepper', '1/2 tsp garlic powder', '1 tsp dried oregano', '2 peaches', '1/2 green pepper', '1/3 cup red onion', '1 tbsp rice wine vinegar', '1 tsp olive oil', '1 tsp fresh cilantro']
steps: ['Prepare an indoor or outdoor grill. Season pork chops with pepper, garlic powder and oregano. Grill pork chops over medium heat for 3-4 minutes per side or until done.', 'In a small bowl, whisk together the peaches, bell pepper, red onion, vinegar, oil, and cilantro.', 'Top each cooked pork chop with about 1/4 cup salsa mixture and serve.']

Ingredients: ['1 tbsp Smart Balance margarine', '1/2 tsp ground cinnamon', '2 tbsp Splenda Brown Sugar blend', '2 medium Anjou Pears', '1 tbsp walnuts', '1/4 cup water']
steps: ['First heat the oven to 400 degrees F.', 'In a small bowl using fingers combine margarine, cinnamon and brown sugar. put walnuts and whisk.', 'Arrange the pears cut side up in an 8-inch square glass baking dish. Pour 1/4 cup water in bottom of wok.', 'Divide the brown sugar mixture evenly among the pear halves and place in middle of pears.', 'Bake until the pears are tender and beginning to brown, about 45 minutes.']

Ingredients: ['1 nonstick cooking spray', '1 tsp olive oil', '4 cup baby spinach', '1 clove garlic', '4 eggs', '1 egg yolk', '1/2 tsp lemon juice', '2 tbsp low sodium vegetable broth', '1/4 cup fat-free plain yogurt', '1/4 tsp salt', '1 Dash of ground black pepper', '2 whole-wheat English muffins']
steps: ['put the cooking spray and oil to a saute wok over medium heat. Saute the spinach until wilted. Stir in the garlic and saute 1 putitional minute.', 'Prepare a double boiler with a heat-proof bowl. put the egg yolk, lemon juice, and vegetable broth, whisking constantly until hot but not curdled. Remove from heat and whisk in yogurt, salt optional, and pepper.', 'Top each English muffin half with 1/4 of spinach mixture, one poached egg, and 2 Tbsps. sauce.']

Ingredients: ['2 lbs flank steak', '2 cup fresh breadcrumbs', '2 shallots or garlic cloves', '1/4 cup fresh Italian parsley', '1/2 cup fresh basil', '1 cup spinach', '1 cup white', '1/4 cup fresh oregano', '1/2 cup Parmigiano-Reggiano', '1 cup red wine', '1/4 cup olive oil', '2 clove garlic', '1 tsp fine sea salt', '1 tsp freshly ground black pepper', '1 tbsp Worcestershire sauce', '1 putitional fresh herbs', '1 Nasturtium flowers']
steps: ['Cut the flank steak into 2 thin steaks with a long, thin knife.', 'whisk all stuffing ingredients together and spread over each piece of flank steak. Roll and tie.', 'whisk all marinade ingredients together. Place flank steaks in plastic bag and put marinade. Marinate in the refrigerator for several hours.', 'First heat grill or grill wok. Drain marinade from steaks.', 'Grill to desired doneness. Slice into very thin rounds and place on platter and garnish with fresh herbs and nasturtium flowers.']

Ingredients: ['8 plum', '2 medium cucumbers', '1/2 small red onion', '1 tbsp olive oil', '3 tbsp balsamic vinegar', '1 oz fresh basil', '1/4 tsp salt', '1/4 tsp black pepper', '4 oz fresh mozzarella']
steps: ['In a large bowl, combine all ingredients. whisk well.', 'Let the salad marinate for 1 hour in the refrigerator.']

Recipe Name: Huevos Rancheros with Pinto Beans, Brown Rice and Chicken Sausage
Ingredients: ['1 Nonstick cooking spray', '2 3-oz links chorizo or other spicy fully cooked chicken sausage', '1/2 cup diced onion', '1 medium jalapenoseno pepper', '1 cup cooked pinto beans', '1 tbsp chili powder', '1 tsp ground cumin', '1/4 tsp cayenne pepper', '3/4 cup low sodium chicken broth', '1 cup cooked brown rice', '2 eggs', '4 egg whites', '1 pinch salt', '1/4 tsp black pepper', '2 tbsp cold water', '1/4 cup queso fresco or feta cheese']
steps: ['Spray a medium nonstick saute wok with cooking spray over medium heat. put sausage, onion and jalapenoseno pepper. Saute for 2-3 minutes.', 'put beans, chili powder, cumin, cayenne pepper and broth. Simmer until the broth is absorbed, about 8-9 minutes', 'Stir in brown rice and set aside.', 'In a small bowl, whisk together eggs, egg whites, salt, pepper and cold water.', 'put cooking spray to another nonstick saute wok over medium heat. Scramble eggs until just set.', 'To serve, scoop 1 cup of sausage mixture into a bowl and top with 1/3 cup scrambled eggs and 1 Tbsp. crumbled cheese.', 'Bulk cooking dry beans: put 1 lb 16 oz. dry pinto beans to a large pot of boiling water at least 6 cups of water. Boil rapidly for 2 minutes. Remove from heat and cover. Let sit for 1 hour. Drain and rinse beans. put 6 fresh cups of water. Bring to a boil, then reduce to a simmer for one hour or until the beans are soft but not split. Makes 5 cups cooked beans. These beans can be used in any recipe calling for cooked or canned beans. Store in an airtight container in the refrigerator for 7 days or package in freezer bags in one cup increments for up to 6 months.', 'Bulk cooking brown rice: put 1 lb 16 oz. of long grain not instant brown rice to a large soup pot with 5 cups of water. Bring to a boil then reduce to a simmer. Cover and simmer for 45 minutes or until all liquid is absorbed. Makes 10 cups cooked brown rice. This rice can be used in any recipe calling for cooked brown rice. Store in an airtight container in the refrigerator for 7 days or package in freezer bags in one cup increments for up to 6 months.']

Ingredients: ['1 nonstick cooking spray', '4 large poblano peppers', '1 tbsp olive oil', '1 package white', '1 cup carrots', '4 green onion', '4 clove garlic', '1/8 tsp salt', '2 tbsp chopped fresh basil leaves, or 2 Tsps. dried basil leaves', '4 tbsp queso fresco']
steps: ['First heat the broiler. Line a broiler wok with foil. Lightly spray the foil with nonstick spray. Place the poblanos on the wok and broil, 4 inches from the heat, turning occasionally, until the poblanos are tender and slightly charred in spots, about 8 minutes.', 'Place the poblanos in a zip-close plastic bag squeeze out the air and seal the bag. Let stand 15 minutes. Leave the broiler on.', 'Heat the oil in a large nonstick skillet over medium-high heat. put the mushrooms, carrots, scallions, garlic, and salt and cook, stirring occasionally, until the vegetables are tender, about 8 minutes. Remove from the heat. Stir in the basil until well whisked.', 'Meanwhile, peal the poblanos. Make one slit to create a pocket and remove the seeds. Stuff each pepper with one-quarter of the mushroom mixture and top with 1 Tbsp of cheese.', 'Broil the stuffed peppers, 4 inches from the heat, until the filling is hot and the cheese begins to melt, about 4 minutes.']

Ingredients: ['1 tbsp olive oil', '1 onion', '2 clove garlic', '1 tsp curry powder', '1/2 tsp ground coriander', '1/4 tsp cayenne pepper', '1/4 tsp salt', '1/4 tsp freshly ground black pepper', '3 cup low sodium chicken broth', '15 oz canned pumpkin', '1 cup fat-free half-and-half', '1 tsp sugar-stevia sweetener', '1/4 cup pumpkin seeds', '1/4 cup fresh chives']
steps: ['In a large saucewok, heat the oil over medium heat. put the onion and saute for 5 to 7 minutes, until soft. put the garlic, curry powder, coriander, cayenne, salt, and pepper and saute for 1 minute.', 'put the broth and bring to boiling. Lower the heat and simmer, uncovered, for 20 minutes.', 'put the pumpkin and simmer for 10 minutes. Using an immersion blender, process the soup until smooth. Or carefully put the hot soup in batches to a blender and process until smooth return the soup to the pot.', 'put the half-and-half and sugar-stevia sweetener and simmer on low for 2 minutes. Ladle into individual serving bowls. Garnish each bowl with generous pinches of pumpkin seeds and chives.']

Ingredients: ['1/2 cup low sodium tomato sauce', '1 tsp Italian seasoning', '1/4 tsp, or to taste crushed red pepper flakes', '1 clove garlic', '1/2 cup roasted red peppers']
steps: ['Place peppers and garlic in food processor or blender and process until smooth. put tomato sauce, olive oil and Italian seasonings.  Process until well blended.  Ready to use on pizza, pasta or as a replacement for tomato sauce in recipes. May be refrigerated up to 3 days or frozen until ready to use.']

Ingredients: ['1 nonstick cooking spray', '2 stalks celery', '3 small carrots', '1 onion', '1/2 head green cabbage', '5 sprig fresh thyme', '1 cup fat-free low-sodium chicken broth', '2 1/2 lbs bone-in turkey breast half', '1 tsp olive oil', '1 tbsp salt-free all-purpose seasoning', '1/2 tsp ground black pepper']
steps: ['First heat the oven to 375 F. Coat a baking dish with nonstick cooking spray.', 'Toss the celery, carrots, onion, cabbage, and thyme together and place in the wok. Pour the chicken broth over the vegetables.', 'Remove the skin from the turkey breast. Place the turkey bone side down on top of the vegetables. Drizzle the turkey and vegetables with the olive oil. Sprinkle them with the all-purpose seasoning and black pepper.', 'Roast the turkey and vegetables in the oven for 1 hour, or until the internal temperature of the turkey is 165 F.', 'When the dish comes out of the oven, set the turkey on a cutting board to rest. Remove the thyme stems and stir the vegetables.', 'Slice the turkey into 4-oz portions and serve each with  º of the vegetable mixture.']

Ingredients: ['1 loaf about 2 lbs day-old whole-grain bread', '1 tbsp olive oil', '1 large onion', '3 large celery stalks', '1/3 cup walnuts', '1/2 bunch fresh sage', '3 cup low sodium chicken broth', '1 egg', '1/2 cup dried cranberries or cherries', '1 salt and pepper to taste', '1 tsp paprika']
steps: ['First heat the oven to 375 F. put the bread to a large bowl.', 'Heat the olive oil in a large skillet over medium heat. put the onions and celery, and saute for 3 minutes. put the walnuts and saute for 2 minutes. put in the sage and cook for 1 minute.', 'put the onion-sage mixture to the bread. Pour the hot chicken broth and egg over the onion-sage, and whisk well until moist. put in the cranberries or cherries. Season well with salt and pepper. put the mixture to a large casserole dish, and sprinkle with paprika. Bake for about 40-45 minutes, or until the top is browned and crusty.']

Ingredients: ['1 tsp caraway seeds', '1/4 cup plus 2 tsp vegetable oil', '1 cup cornmeal', '1 cup whole wheat flour', '1 1/2 tsp baking powder', '1/2 tsp baking soda', '1/2 tsp salt', '2 eggs', '1 cup low-fat buttermilk', '1/4 cup honey']
steps: ['First heat the oven to 400 degrees. In a small, dry skillet, toast the caraway seeds over medium heat for 2 to 3 minutes, just until lightly browned and fragrant set aside. When the oven is hot, put 2 tsp. of the vegetable oil to a 9-inch cast-iron skillet. Heat the wok in the oven for 5 minutes.', 'Meanwhile, in a large bowl, whisk the cornmeal, flour, baking powder, baking soda, salt, and caraway seeds.', 'In a separate bowl, beat the eggs with a wire whisk. put the buttermilk, honey, and the 1/4 cup vegetable oil.', 'put the wet ingredients to the dry ingredients and whisk until just combined.', 'Carefully put the batter to the hot skillet and bake for 20 to 22 minutes, or until the cornbread is cooked through and a cake tester or toothpick inserted in the middle comes out clean. Let the cornbread cool for 5 minutes. Cut into 16 same-sized wedges and serve warm.']

Recipe Name: Slow Cooker Apricot Barbecue Pulled Chicken Sliders
Ingredients: ['1 lbs boneless, skinless chicken breasts', '1/4 cup barbecue sauce', '1/2 cup apricot preserves', '1/4 tsp black pepper', '8 Cloudbread', '1/2 cup mozzarella cheese', '1/2 cup roasted red peppers', '1/4 cup fresh basil']
steps: ['Place chicken in the bowl of a slow cooker.', 'In a small bowl, whisk together the barbecue sauce, apricot preserves, salt, and pepper. Pour sauce into the slow cooker and stir to coat the chicken. Cook on high for 4 hours, until the chicken is soft and cooked through.', 'Once the chicken is finished, remove from the slow cooker and shred. Return to the sauce and stir to combine.  To serve, divide chicken between cloud bread rounds. Top with shredded cheese, peppers, and basil.']

Ingredients: ['1/4 cup all-purpose flour', '1 tsp smoked paprika', '1/2 tsp thyme leaves', '1/4 tsp garlic powder', '1/4 tsp salt', '1/2 tsp black pepper', '4 pork chops', '2 tbsp canola oil', '2 medium Roma tomatoes']
steps: ['Combine the flour, paprika, thyme, garlic powder, 1/4 Tsp. of the salt and black pepper in a shallow pie wok. Coat the pork chops evenly on both sides.', 'Heat the oil in a large nonstick skillet over medium-high heat and cook 4 minutes on each side or until no longer pink in center. Sprinkle with the diced tomatoes and remaining 1/8 Tsp. salt.']

Ingredients: ['12 oz frozen artichoke hearts', '1 1/2 cup Plain Nonfat Greek yogurt', '10 oz frozen spinach', '1/2 cup grated Parmesan cheese', '1/2 cup roasted red peppers', '2 green onions', '1 tbsp minced onion or 1 tsp onion powder', '1 tsp horseradish', '1/2 tsp garlic powder', '1/8 tsp salt', 'to taste hot sauce']

Ingredients: ['4 large ripe beefsteak or heirloom tomatoes', '1/2 tsp black pepper', '1/2 tsp salt-free garlic and herb seasoning blend, such as Mrs. Dash', '4 eggs', '2 tsp reduced fat parmesan cheese', '2 slice bacon']
steps: ['First heat oven to 350 degrees F. Coat a 9x13-inch baking dish with cooking spray.', 'Cut 1/4 inch off the top of each tomato. Scoop out pulp and seeds, leaving about 1/2-inch-think shell. Ingredients: ['2 lbs pork tenderloin', '1 can jellied cranberry sauce', '1/2 cup orange juice', '1 tsp mustard powder', '1/4 tsp ground cloves', '1 package whole wheat egg noodles', '1 head broccoli', '1 package baby carrots', '1 tbsp water', '2 tbsp Cornstarch', '2 tbsp water']
steps: ['8 hours before serving, place pork tenderloin in slow cooker', 'In a medium bowl, whisk together cranberry sauce, orange juice, dry mustard, and ground cloves mashing cranberry sauce.', 'Pour over roast and cook on LOW for 8 hours, or on HIGH for 4 hours.', '20 minutes before serving, put a large pot of water on to boil.', 'put noodles to boiling water, set timer for 10 minutes or according to package directions.', 'Place broccoli, baby carrots, and 1 Tbsp. of water in microwave-safe dish, cover, and cook on HIGH for 7 minutes.', 'Drain 2 cups of juice from roast. Skim off any fat if there is any, pork tenderloin is so lean. put water if necessary, to make 2 cups. Pour into small saucewok and bring to a boil over medium heat.', 'In a small cup, whisk together cornstarch and 2 Tbsps. of water and pour into boiling juice while whisking. Ingredients: ['2 whole bananas', '6 tbsp unsweetened cocoa powder', '3 tbsp Splenda Granulated Sweetener', '1/8 tsp salt', '2 tsp pure vanilla extract', '1 tbsp almond butter', '2 tbsp sliced almonds']
steps: ['In a food processor, pulse bananas, half of the cocoa powder, Splenda Sweetener, and salt until pea-sized chunks form. put vanilla extract and the rest of the cocoa powder. Continue to pulse. mixture will gather and form a frozen soft-serve ice-cream consistency. Drizzle in almond butter and pulse twice more.', 'Scoop into bowls and serve topped with almonds or stir in almonds. Place in a freezer-safe container and enjoy within 3 days.', 'Note: Toast almonds for a deeper, delicious flavor. Keep sliced bananas in a zip top bag in the freezer to have them ready on hand for making nice cream any time.']

Ingredients: ['4 frozen salmon filets', '1 tbsp olive oil', '1 tbsp grill seasoning', '4 cup romaine lettuce', '1/2 cup red onion', '1 cup cucumber', '1 ripe avocado', '1/4 cup lime juice', '1 tbsp olive oil', '1 tsp Dijon Mustard', '1 tsp stevia', '1/4 tsp salt', '1/4 tsp black pepper']
steps: ['First heat an indoor or outdoor grill.', 'Pat the thawed salmon filets dry with a paper towel. Set aside.', 'Build each salad starting with 1 cup of Romaine lettuce, top with 1/4 of the sliced onion, 1/4 cup of the sliced cucumber, the grilled salmon filet and 1/4 of the sliced avocado, Repeat for remaining three salads.', 'In a small bowl, whisk together the lime juice, olive oil, Dijon mustard, Stevia, salt and pepper. Ingredients: ['1/4 cup water', '1 1/2 cup low sodium canned beans', '1/4 tsp ground black pepper', '1/4 cup fresh herbs', '1 clove garlic']

Ingredients: ['3 lbs apple', '1/4 cup Splenda Stevia Sweetener Jar', '1 1/2 tsp ground cinnamon', '1/8 tsp ground cloves', '1/4 tsp ground nutmeg', '1/4 tsp Kosher Salt', '1 tsp pure vanilla extract']
steps: ['Slice apples into 1-inch x 1-inch chunks and place in a large bowl. Sprinkle with Splenda Stevia, spices, salt, and vanilla. Toss together.', 'Pour apples into a crockpot or slow-cooker, using a spatula to scrape all of the spices into the slow cooker as well. Cover and cook on low for 8-10 hours until apples are falling apart and fork-tender.', 'Carefully scoop cooked apples into a high-powered blender or an immersion blender, blending until it s the consistency you like in an apple butter smooth or slightly chunky.', 'Let the apple butter cool, then scoop it into jars. Use immediately or store in the refrigerator. Enjoy!', 'Note:  Stir some into your morning oatmeal, spread it on whole grain toast, or put as a glaze to your roast beef, turkey, or ham.  How much Splenda Stevia you need will depend on how naturally sweet the apples are. Adjust sweetener after blending your apples, puting more if necessary.']

steps: ['In a blender whisk together all ingredients until smooth.', 'Pour smoothie mixture evenly into 4 ice pop molds. Insert ice pop handle on top. Place upright and freeze until solid about 3 hours.']

Ingredients: ['1 5-oz package arugula or other salad greens', '1/3 cup light Italian salad dressing', '4 hard-boiled eggs', '1/4 cup canned, sliced black olives', '1 5-oz can tuna packed in water', '2 cup grape tomatoes']

Recipe Name: wokna Cotta de Calabaza Baja en Grasas

steps: ['whisk the milk, Splenda brown sugar, low-fat buttermilk, and unflavored gelatin in a medium saucewok away from the heat. Ingredients: ['1/3 cup 100% pomegranate juice', '2 tsp sugar', '1 pear', '1/4 tsp Cornstarch', '1 tbsp water', '1/4 tsp lemon zest', '1/4 tsp vanilla extract', '2 tbsp sliced almonds']

Recipe Name: Red, White, and Blue Pudding Trifle
Ingredients: ['1 oz instant vanilla pudding whisk', '2 cup milk', '8 oz light whipped topping', '2 1/2 cup raspberries', '2 1/2 cup blueberries', '1 1/2 cup strawberries']
steps: ['In a large bowl, prepare pudding according to package directions. Ingredients: ['1 nonstick cooking spray', '1 tbsp grated orange zest', '1/2 tsp ground cinnamon', '1/2 tsp ground cumin', '1/2 tsp paprika', '1/4 tsp ground allspice or ground nutmeg', '1/4 tsp salt', '1/4 tsp black pepper', '1/8 tsp cayenne pepper', '5 lbs turkey breast with bone and skin']
steps: ['First heat the oven to 325 F. Lightly spray a roasting wok and baking rack with cooking spray.', 'In a small bowl, stir together all of the ingredients except the turkey.', "Put the turkey on a cutting board or flat work surface. Carefully loosen the skin from the turkey breast by gently inserting your fingers between the skin and the meat, making a pocket for the orange zest mixture. do not break the skin. Discard any fat beneath the skin. Still working carefully, spread the orange zest mixture under the loosened skin as evenly as possible. Transfer the turkey to the rack in the wok.", "Roast the turkey for 1 hour and 45 minutes, or until it reaches an internal temperature of at least 170 F. Be sure the thermometer does not touch the bone.", 'Remove the turkey from the oven and let stand for 15 minutes.', 'Discard the skin and all visible fat. Slice the turkey and serve.']

Ingredients: ['1 nonstick cooking spray', '1 small about 1 pound butternut squash', '2 small turnips', '2 parsnips', '2 carrots', '1 large onion', '3 celery stalks', '1/2 small head green cabbage', '4 clove garlic', '1 tbsp olive oil', '1 tbsp Herbs de Provence', '2 quarts low sodium vegetable broth', '1 tbsp sherry vinegar', '1 tsp salt', '1/2 tsp black pepper']

Ingredients: ['1 nonstick cooking spray', '2 slice whole wheat bread', '1/4 tsp black pepper', '1/2 tsp salt', '4 salmon filets', '1 tbsp Splenda Brown Sugar blend', '2 clove garlic', '1/4 cup onion', '1/4 cup Dijon Mustard', '2 tbsp olive oil', '1/4 cup parsley']

Recipe Name: Togarashi Tilapia & Marinated Cucumber with Miso Stir-Fried Vegetables
Ingredients: ['1 tbsp honey', '6 oz fresh green beans', '10 oz baby bok choy', '2 clove garlic', '4 oz mini sweet peppers', '1 med persian cucumber', '2 tbsp Apple Cider Vinegar', '1 tbsp sesame oil', '1 tbsp white miso', '3 tbsp water', '2 1/2 tsp olive oil', '2 tilapia or other white fish fillet', '1 tbsp togarashi', '1 pinch salt and pepper to taste']
steps: ['Prepare the ingredients & make the sauce: Remove the honey from the refrigerator to bring to room temperature. Wash and dry the fresh produce. Cut off and discard the stem ends of the green beans halve crosswise. Cut off and discard the root ends of the bok choy roughly chop, separating the stems and leaves. Peel and roughly chop 2 cloves of garlic. Cut off and discard the stems of the peppers remove the cores, then quarter lengthwise. Combine in a bowl put the chopped bok choy stems. Halve the cucumber lengthwise, then thinly slice crosswise. Place in a bowl put the vinegar and half the sesame oil. Stir to coat. Set aside to marinate, stirring occasionally, at least 10 minutes. In a separate bowl, whisk together the honey kneading the packet before opening, miso paste, remaining sesame oil, and 1 tablespoon of water.', 'Start the stir-fry: While the cucumber marinates, in a medium wok nonstick, if you have one, heat 1/2 teaspoon of olive oil on medium-high until hot. put the halved green beans in an even layer. Cook, without stirring, 2 to 3 minutes, or until lightly browned. put 2 tablespoons of water carefully, as the liquid may splatter. Cook, stirring occasionally, 1 to 2 minutes, or until the green beans are slightly softened.', 'Finish the stir-fry: To the wok, put the prepared pepper mixture season with salt optional and pepper. Cook, stirring occasionally, 3 to 4 minutes, or until softened. put the chopped bok choy leaves and sauce. Cook, stirring frequently, 1 to 2 minutes, or until the sauce is thickened. Transfer to a bowl. Cover with foil to keep warm. Rinse and wipe out the wok.', 'Cook the fish & serve your dish: Pat the fish dry with paper towels. Season on both sides with salt optional, pepper, and all but a pinch of the togarashi. In the same wok, heat 2 teaspoons of olive oil on medium-high until hot. put the seasoned fish and cook 3 to 4 minutes per side, or until browned and cooked through an instant-read thermometer should register 145F. Turn off the heat. Serve the finished stir-fry topped with the cooked fish and marinated cucumber discarding any liquid. Garnish with the remaining togarashi. Enjoy!']

Use 1/3 cup batter for each wokcake and cook until brown on bottom and some bubbles begin to break around edges. Turn wokcake over and cook until brown and slightly firm to the touch in the center.', 'Repeat procedure for remaining 9 wokcakes.']

Ingredients: ['1 whole avocado', '3 eggs', '2 tbsp olive oil', '1 cup spinach', '1 whole CAULIPOWER Cauliflower Pizza Crust']
steps: ['First heat oven to 425 degrees F.', 'Remove your CAULIPOWER Æ pizza crust from the box and the plastic wrapping and place on a clean surface.', 'Heat wok, fry the eggs, and place them on the pizza crust.', 'Top with spinach, avocado, and olive oil.', 'Place pizza in the oven and bake for 13-16 minutes.', 'Remove from oven, allow to cool, and serve.']

Ingredients: ['1 nonstick cooking spray', '2 tbsp olive oil', '1 large onion', '3 clove garlic', '1 large bell pepper', '1 can anchovies packed in oil', '1 cup black olives', '1/8 tsp fennel seeds', '1 tsp black pepper', '8 cod filets', '4 tomato slices', '1 tbsp tomato paste', '1 cup red wine']
steps: ['First heat oven to 375F.', 'Prep a baking dish with nonstick cooking spray.', 'Heat the olive oil in a heavy skillet and put onions, garlic, and bell pepper, cooking until the onion is soft. put the anchovies, olives, fennel seed, and black pepper. Stir to combine.', 'Place 4 pieces of the cod in a single layer in the baking dish. Spread evenly with the anchovy/olive mixture.', 'Top each piece with another piece, making a cod  Çìsandwich. Ç ù Top each with a slice of tomato.', 'Combine the diluted tomato paste with the red wine and pour over the fish.', 'Bake for 20 minutes until the fish is flaky, basting every 5 minutes or so.']

Ingredients: ['1 cup whole farro', '1 3/4 cup chicken or vegetable broth', '1 can diced tomatoes with green chilies', '1 1/4 tsp sea salt', '1 tbsp Extra Virgin Olive Oil', '8 oz ground turkey', '1 med green bell pepper', '1 small white onion', '1 tbsp salt-free cajun seasoning', '1 can no-salt-puted red kidney beans']
steps: ['put the farro, broth, diced tomatoes with liquid, and salt to a medium saucewok. Bring to a boil over high heat. Reduce the heat to medium low, cover, and simmer for 20 minutes. The farro will be halfway cooked.', 'Meanwhile, heat the oil in a large nonstick skillet over medium-high heat. put the turkey, bell pepper, onion, and cajun seasoning and saute until the turkey is crumbled and well-done and onion is softened, about 5 minutes.', 'Stir the turkey mixture and beans into the farro mixture, cover, and continue to simmer until the farro is tender, about 20 minutes. Remove from heat and let stand, covered, for 5 minutes to complete the cooking process. Then serve.']

Recipe Name: Chopped Salad with Cilantro Lime Dressing
Ingredients: ['4 cup romaine lettuce', '2 carrot', '2 celery stalks', '2 roma', '1/2 cup cucumber', '1 cup canned black beans', '2 tbsp cider vinegar', '2 tbsp lime juice', '2 tbsp cilantro', '2 tsp honey', '1/2 tsp sea salt', '1/4 tsp black pepper', '1/4 cup olive oil', '2 tbsp pumpkin or sunflower seeds']
steps: ['Place the lettuce on a shallow platter. In rows, arrange the carrots, celery, plum tomatoes, cucumber, and black beans.', 'Prepare the salad dressing. whisk together the cider vinegar, lime juice, cilantro, honey, salt, and pepper. Slowly drizzle in the oil, whisking to incorporate.', 'Drizzle on the dressing. Top with toasted pumpkin or sunflower seeds.']

Ingredients: ['1 nonstick cooking spray', '1 tbsp olive oil', '1 bunch asparagus', '1 small onion', '1 red or yellow bell pepper', '1/2 tsp salt', '1/4 tsp black pepper', '2 eggs', '6 egg whites', '1/3 cup skim milk', '6 wedges Laughing Cow Light Original Cheese Wedges']
steps: ['First heat oven to 375 degrees.', 'Spray a muffin wok with cooking spray.', 'put olive oil and a generous amount of cooking spray to a medium saute wok. Saute asparagus, onion and bell pepper for 7-9 minutes or until cooked through. Season with salt optional and pepper and set aside to cool slightly.', 'In a medium bowl, whisk together eggs, egg whites and milk.', 'Evenly distribute the sauteed vegetables among the 12 muffin cups. Cups should be 1/2 to 3/4 full. Gently pour egg mixture over the vegetables in each muffin cup, distributing evenly. Cups should full but not overflowing.', 'Take one half of a Lite Laughing Cow Cheese Wedge and gently press it down in the middle of each quiche. Repeat for remaining 11 quiches.', 'Bake for 20 minutes. Serve immediately.']

Ingredients: ['2 tsp extra virgin olive oil', '8 oz fresh green beans', '1 cup grape tomatoes', '1/4 tsp ground cinnamon', '1/8 tsp salt']
steps: ['Heat the oil in a large nonstick skillet over medium heat. put the green beans and tomatoes, cover, and cook until the green beans are tender yet crisp and the tomatoes are fully softened, about 10 minutes. Toss with tongs a couple of times throughout the cooking.', 'Sprinkle the vegetables with the cinnamon and salt. Toss to combine, and then serve.']

Ingredients: ['5 tsp unsalted butter', '3 tsp fresh minced sage', '3 tsp fresh minced thyme', '3 tsp fresh rosemary', '1 Kosher salt and freshly ground black pepper to taste', '1 1/2 cup low sodium chicken broth', '1 cup white wine', '5 lbs turkey breast']
steps: ['First heat the oven to 350 degrees F. Line a large roasting wok with foil. Set a rack inside the roasting wok and coat it with cooking spray. Set aside.', 'In a small bowl, combine the butter with 2 Tsps.. each of the sage, thyme, and rosemary, plus salt and pepper. Reserve the remaining 1 Tsp. of each of the herbs.', 'In a small saucewok, combine the chicken broth and wine, and bring to a gentle boil. put the reserved herbs and lower to a simmer.', 'With your hands, separate the turkey breast skin from the breast meat, creating a pocket without removing the skin. Rube the butter herb mixture all over the breast meat. Place the skin back down on the breast.', 'Set the turkey on the prepared rack in the wok. You can also put veggies like peeled carrots, peeled parsnips, onions, or small potatoes to the wok they will cook along with the turkey. Roast the turkey for about 1 hour, 20 minutes to 1 hour, 40 minutes until the internal temperature reaches 170 degrees F and the juices run clear. Baste every 15-20 minutes with the mixture of chicken broth and white wine.', 'Remove the turkey from the oven, cover loosely with foil, and let stand for 15 minutes before slicing. Discard the skin and serve.']

Ingredients: ['8 eggs', '1 14.5-oz can garbanzo beans', '2 clove garlic', '1 small lemon', '1 tbsp olive oil', '1/4 cup low sodium vegetable broth', '1/4 tsp salt', '1/4 tsp black pepper', '1/4 cup salsa', '1 tbsp chopped fresh parsley']
steps: ['Slice hardboiled eggs in half lengthwise and discard the yolk.', 'put garbanzo beans, garlic, lemon zest, lemon juice, olive oil, broth, salt, pepper, salsa and parsley to a blender or food processor. Process until hummus is smooth.', 'Fill each egg half with a heaping tablespoon of hummus.']

Ingredients: ['1 nonstick cooking spray', '1 tsp olive oil', '1 small onion', '4 oz asparagus', '1/2 cup cooked whole millet', '4 chicken breasts', '2 tbsp Dijon Mustard', '1/4 cup bread crumbs', '1 tbsp dried tarragon', '1/2 tsp salt', '1/2 tsp black pepper']
steps: ['First heat oven to 375 degrees F. Coat a 9-inch x 13-inch baking dish with cooking spray. Set aside.', 'put the olive oil to a nonstick saute wok over medium heat. put the onions and asparagus and saute for 4-5 minutes, or until the onions turn clear.', 'whisk the sauteed vegetables with the cooked millet and set aside to cool.', 'Slice a pocket into one side of each chicken breast that runs the entire length of the chicken breast, without coming out the other side.', 'Once the millet and vegetables are cooled, stuff 1/2 cup of filling in the pocket of each chicken breast and lay them side by side in the baking dish.', 'Brush each breast with Dijon mustard.', 'In a small bowl, whisk together the breadcrumbs, tarragon, salt optional, and pepper. Divide the breadcrumb topping among each breast, coating the top completely. Spray each breast with cooking spray and bake for 35 minutes or until the internal temperature of chicken is 165 degrees F.', 'Let the chicken rest for at least 5 minutes before slicing.']

Ingredients: ['1 nonstick cooking spray', '1 cup old-fashioned oats', '1 cup whole-wheat flour', '1/4 cup sugar', '1/2 tsp ground cardamom', '1/4 tsp ground nutmeg', '1/4 tsp baking soda', '2 egg whites', '3 tbsp canola oil', '1 orange', '1 1/2 cup apple butter']
steps: ['First heat the oven to 350F. Lightly spray an 8-inch square baking dish with cooking spray.', 'In a medium bowl, stir together the oatmeal, flour, sugar, cardamom, nutmeg, and baking soda.', 'In a small bowl, using a fork, lightly beat the egg whites. Stir in the oil and 2 tbsp fresh orange juice.', 'put the egg white mixture to the oatmeal mixture, stirring until the combined mixture holds together. Press three-fourths of the mixture into the baking dish.', 'In a medium bowl, whisk together the fruit butter and 2 tsp of the orange zest. Using a rubber scraper, spread the fruit butter mixture over the oatmeal mixture. Sprinkle with the remaining oatmeal mixture.', 'Bake for 30-35 minutes, or until the top is golden brown. Transfer the dish to a cooling rack and let cool completely, then cut into 24 equal bars.']

Ingredients: ['1 small', '1 cup Greek yogurt', '1 tsp honey', '1 cup water', '1 Juice of Ω lime', '1/4 cup ice cubes', '1/4 tsp cardamom', '1 bunch mint leaves', '1/4 tsp cardamom']
steps: ['Combine all lassi ingredients in a food processor and blend until smooth.', 'Serve in 6 tall thin glasses and garnish with mint leaves and ground cardamom before serving.']

Ingredients: ['1 medium red cedolla', '1/4 tsp salt', '1 green bell pepper', '4 garlic cloves', '1 lbs lean ground beef', '1/2 cup frozen whisked vegetables', '1/2 cup tomato sauce', '2 tsp marinade seasoning', '1/2 cup shredded low-fat mozzarella cheese', '1 tbsp. fresh flat-leaf parsley', '1/4 tsp paprika', '1 tbsp. olive oil', 'nonstick olive oil spray', '4 2 lb very ripe plants']
steps: ['Heat the oven to 375F 191C. Pour cooking spray into an 8-inch baking dish.', 'In a large pot, boil the banana in enough water to cover it. Lower the heat to medium-low and cook until the banana becomes very soft, about 25 minutes. Drain but save 1 cup of the liquid. Put the banana back into the pot and mash with a potato masher, puting salt and cooking fluid, 1/2 cup at a time, until the mixture is even.', 'Heat the oil in a large nonstick skillet over medium high heat. put the onion, red pepper and garlic. SautÈ, stirring occasionally, until vegetables are soft, about 8 minutes.', 'put beef and drala, separating with a wooden spoon, about 10 minutes. put the whisked vegetables, tomato sauce and marinade. Cook, stirring occasionally, until flavors combine, about 10 minutes.', 'Pour half of the banana mixture into an even layer in a baking dish. Pour the meat mixture evenly over the banana layer. Spoon the rest of the banana mixture over the meat. Pour the cheese on top and sprinkle with paprika. Bake until the filling is hot, the cheese is melted, and the edges are browned, about 25 minutes.']

Ingredients: ['1/8 tsp black pepper', '1/4 cup pine nuts', '2 clove garlic', '1 cup fresh packed basil leaves', '1 tbsp olive oil', '8 bamboo skewers', '2 tbsp Parmesan cheese', '1 1/4 lbs boneless, skinless chicken breasts', '2 zucchini', '24 cherry tomatoes']
steps: ['Soak the bamboo skewers in warm water for at least 30 minutes.', 'First heat an indoor or outdoor grill.', 'While the skewers are soaking, blend the olive oil, garlic, basil, pine nuts, black pepper and parmesan cheese in a blender or food processor.', 'Thread alternating pieces of chicken, zucchini and tomato onto the soaked skewers, using 3 pieces of chicken, 3 pieces of zucchini and 3 tomatoes.', 'Brush the kabobs with the basil mixture, coating well.', 'Grill the kabobs about 7 minutes, brushing with the basil mixture until it is all used. Turn the kabobs frequently until the chicken is cooked through and reaches 165 degrees F.']

Ingredients: ['1 cup canned chickpeas', '1 tbsp olive oil', '2 tbsp BBQ spice blend', '2 packet Splenda Stevia Sweetener']
steps: ['First heat oven to 350 degrees F.', 'With paper towel, pat chickpeas until completely dry. Spread on a rimmed baking sheet. Drizzle with olive oil and toss to coat. Spread into an even layer.', 'Bake for 35-45 minutes or until dry. Cool to room temperature.', 'In a bowl, combine spice blend and Splenda Stevia Sweetener. put roasted chickpeas and toss to coat well. Let dry overnight.']

Ingredients: ['4 tomatoes', '1/2 red onion', '2 tbsp balsamic vinegar', '1 1/2 tsp olive oil', '1/4 tsp salt', '1/4 tsp black pepper', '1/4 cup fresh basil']
steps: ['Arrange the tomatoes on a platter in an overlapping style. Scatter the onion on top of the tomatoes.', 'In a small bowl or liquid measuring cup, whisk the vinegar and oil. Drizzle the vinaigrette over the tomatoes. Sprinkle with the salt, pepper, and basil, and serve.']

Recipe Name: Shakshuka with Red Peppers and Goat Cheese
Ingredients: ['1/2 tbsp olive oil', '1 small yellow onion', '2 clove garlic', '1/2 red bell pepper', '1/2 tsp paprika', '1/8 tsp Sea salt', '1/8 tsp black pepper', '1 28-oz can canned crushed tomatoes', '3 cup baby spinach', '8 eggs', '1/4 cup goat cheese']
steps: ['First heat your oven to 425 degrees.', 'Heat the olive oil over medium-high heat in a large oven-proof skillet. put the onion and saute for about 3 minutes, until translucent. put the garlic, red pepper and spices and saute until the red pepper is soft about 2 minutes.', 'put the crushed tomatoes and the spinach. Saute for 2 minutes. Turn off the heat.', 'Using a wooden spoon, create 8 wells in the wok of veggies. Crack an egg into each well. Put the skillet in the First heated oven and bake for about 7 minutes or until the eggs are set.', 'Remove from the oven and crumble the goat cheese on top while still warm. Cut into 4 equal slices with 2 eggs each to serve.']

Recipe Name: Smoothie de Banana, Mantequilla de man≠ y Chocolate con leche
Ingredients: ['1 8-oz bottle Splenda Diabetes Care Chocolate Shake', '1 tbsp chia seeds', '1 cup ice', '1/2 frozen banana', '1 tbsp peanut butter']
steps: ['Place all ingredients in a blender until all ingredients are combined and smooth. Divide the smoothie between two glasses and serve.']

Recipe Name: Spiced Pork & Glazed Apple with Roasted Vegetables
Ingredients: ['1 12-oz lean boneless pork sirloin roast', '1 tsp quatre epices', '1 1/2 tsp olive oil', '1 med red onion', '1 purple top turnip', '4 oz fresh Brussels sprouts', '6 oz carrots', '1 med apple', '2 tbsp vegetable demi-glace', '1 pinch salt and pepper to taste']
steps: ['Prepare & sear the pork: Place an oven rack in the center of the oven, then First heat to 450F. Pat the pork dry with paper towels season on all sides with salt optional, pepper, and the quatre epices. In a medium wok, heat 1/2 teaspoon of olive oil on medium-high until hot. put the seasoned pork. Cook, turning occasionally, 4 to 6 minutes, or until browned on all sides. Leaving any browned bits or fond in the wok, transfer to the center of a sheet wok.', 'Prepare the vegetables: Meanwhile, wash and dry the fresh produce. Halve and peel the onion cut into 1/2-inch-wide wedges, keeping the layers intact. Medium dice the turnip. Cut off and discard the stem ends of the brussels sprouts halve lengthwise. Peel the carrots cut crosswise into 1-inch pieces. Place the prepared vegetables in a large bowl. Drizzle with 1/2 teaspoon of olive oil and season with salt optional and pepper toss to coat. Transfer to the sheet wok of seared pork and arrange in an even layer around the edges.', 'Roast the pork & vegetables: Roast the seared pork and prepared vegetables 22 to 24 minutes, or until the vegetables are browned and tender when pierced with a fork and the pork is cooked through. An instant-read thermometer should register 145F. Remove from the oven. Transfer the roasted pork to a cutting board and let rest at least 5 minutes.', 'Prepare, cook & glaze the apple: Meanwhile, core and medium dice the apple. Once the pork and vegetables have roasted about 20 minutes, in the wok of reserved fond, heat 1/2 teaspoon of olive oil on medium-high until hot. put the diced apple season with salt optional and pepper. Cook, stirring frequently, 6 to 8 minutes, or until softened. put the demi-glace carefully, as the liquid may splatter. Cook, stirring frequently and scraping up any fond, 30 seconds to 1 minute, or until combined. Turn off the heat.', 'Slice the pork & serve your dish: Find the lines of muscle or grain on the rested pork thinly slice crosswise against the grain. Serve the sliced pork with the roasted vegetables. Top the pork with the glazed apple. Enjoy!']

Ingredients: ['1 tbsp olive oil', '1/2 sweet onion', '1/4 tsp ground ginger', '1/4 tsp dried dill', '1/4 tsp salt', '1/8 tsp black pepper', '1/2 lemon', '1 lbs salmon']
steps: ['First heat the oven to 350 F. Heat the olive oil in a large, heavy ovenproof skillet over medium heat, and put the onions. Cook for 8 to 10 minutes, stirring occasionally, until they are golden.', 'Meanwhile, in a small bowl, combine the ginger, dill, salt, and pepper set aside. Top the onions with the lemon slices and then the salmon, and top the salmon evenly with the spices. Transfer the skillet to the oven and cook the salmon for about 20 minutes, until it is cooked through. Remove from the oven and serve immediately. Green Beans With Lemon and Garlic make a great side dish for the salmon.', 'Slow Cooker Directions: Cut the salmon fillet into pieces that will fit into the slow cooker. Combine the onions in the bottom of the slow cooker. Place each piece of salmon onto a separate piece of aluminum foil large enough to fold into a packet. Sprinkle the spices evenly over the salmon pieces and top with lemon slices. Fold the foil into a packet, and place the packets into the slow cooker on top of the onions, stacking as needed. Cook on low for 6 to 8 hours or on high for 3 to 4 hours for thinner fillets check for doneness sooner. Remove the salmon from the packets, then top with the onions before serving.']

Ingredients: ['1/2 tsp salt', '2 tsp poppy seed', '2 1/2 cup cooked chicken breasts', '1/3 cup celery', '1/8 tsp black pepper', '1/2 cup walnuts', '1 cup fresh strawberries', '4 tsp Splenda Granulated Sweetener', '11 oz canned, no sugar puted mandarin oranges', '2 tsp rice vinegar', '1/2 cup light mayonnaise', '1/4 cup green onion']
steps: ['In a large bowl, combine and toss the chicken salad ingredients.', 'In a small bowl, combine all dressing ingredients and whisk well.', 'Pour the dressing over the chicken mixture and stir to combine. Cover and refrigerate until chilled, about 4 hours.']

Ingredients: ['1 nonstick cooking spray', '2 small sweet potatoes', '1 12-oz bag frozen cauliflower rice', '2 tsp olive oil', '1 small onion', '2 clove garlic', '1 15.5-oz can black beans', '1 cup salsa', '1/2 cup shredded Mexican cheese blend', '2 cup shredded lettuce', '1/4 cup Plain Nonfat Greek yogurt', '1 cup diced tomatoes']
steps: ['First heat the oven to 400 degrees F. Coat a baking sheet with cooking spray. Scrub and dry the potatoes and place them on the baking sheet. Bake the potatoes 45 minutes-1 hour until very tender.', 'While the potatoes are cooking, cook the instant brown rice according to the package directions. Set the cooked rice aside but keep warm.', 'put the olive oil to a nonstick wok over medium heat. put the onions and garlic and saute 5 minutes or until the onions start to soften.', 'put the beans and salsa, and simmer to heat the beans through. Set the bean and salsa mixture aside but keep warm.', 'When the potatoes are done cooking, let them cool slightly, then peel and large dice the cooked potato.', 'To build one burrito bowl, put 1/2 cup cooked rice to the bottom of the bowl. Top with 1/4 of sweet potatoes. Top with 1/2 cup bean and salsa mixture, then top with 2 Tbsp cheese. Repeat the process for the remaining three bowls.', 'Right before serving, top one bowl with 1/2 cup shredded lettuce, 1 Tbsp. Greek yogurt and 1/4 cup tomatoes.']

Recipe Name: Togarashi Chicken & Orange Glaze with Miso-Roasted Vegetables & Marinated Pear
Ingredients: ['1 tbsp honey', '6 oz fresh green beans', '1/2 lbs cremini', '3/4 lbs carrots', '1 lbs red cabbage', '1 med navel orange', '1 med pear', '1 tbsp rice wine', '1 tbsp sesame oil', '3 tbsp white miso', '2 tbsp olive oil', '1 tbsp warm water', '4 boneless, skinless chicken breasts', '1 tbsp togarashi']
steps: ['Prepare the ingredients & marinate the pear: Remove the honey from the refrigerator to bring to room temperature. Place an oven rack in the center of the oven, then First heat to 450F. Wash and dry the fresh produce. Cut off and discard the stem ends of the green beans halve crosswise. Cut the mushrooms into bite-sized pieces. Peel the carrots and cut crosswise into 1/2-inch-thick pieces. Cut out and discard the core of the cabbage medium dice the leaves. Combine in a large bowl. Halve the orange crosswise squeeze the juice into a separate bowl. Grate the pear on the large side of a box grater, discarding the core. In a large bowl, whisk together the mirin, sesame oil, and honey kneading the packet before opening season with salt and pepper. put the grated pear and toss to coat. Set aside to marinate, stirring occasionally, at least 10 minutes.', 'Roast the vegetables: Meanwhile, in a bowl, whisk together the miso paste, 1 tablespoon of olive oil, and 1 tablespoon of warm water. Divide the prepared vegetables between 2 sheet woks. Evenly top the vegetables with the miso mixture. Toss to thoroughly coat and arrange in an even layer. Roast 14 to 16 minutes, or until browned and tender when pierced with a fork. Remove from the oven.', 'Cook & glaze the chicken: Meanwhile, pat the chicken dry with paper towels season on both sides with salt optional, pepper, and enough of the togarashi to coat you may have extra. In a large wok nonstick, if you have one, heat 1 tablespoon of olive oil on medium-high until hot. put the seasoned chicken. Cook 6 to 7 minutes, or until browned. Flip and cook 4 minutes. put the orange juice carefully, as the liquid may splatter. Cook, frequently spooning the juice over the chicken, 2 to 3 minutes, or until the chicken is coated and cooked throughAn instant-read thermometer should register 165F. Transfer the cooked chicken to a cutting board.', 'Slice the chicken & serve your dish: Slice the glazed chicken crosswise. Serve the roasted vegetables topped with the sliced chicken and marinated pear including any liquid. Enjoy!']

Ingredients: ['1/4 tsp ground coriander', '2 tbsp olive oil', '3 tbsp lemon juice', '1/4 cup dried currants', '1/4 cup slivered almonds', '2 med apple', '5 carrot', '1 tsp ground cumin', '1/4 tsp ground cinnamon', '1/4 tsp black pepper']
steps: ['In a large bowl, combine all ingredients and cover. Refrigerate for 1/2 hour before serving. Bring the salad to room temperature and serve.']

Recipe Name: Cajun Fish Sandwiches With Crunchy Slaw
Ingredients: ['6 oz about 3 cups shredded cabbage or coleslaw whisk', '2 tbsp light mayonnaise', '1 tbsp Apple Cider Vinegar', '1/2 tbsp honey', '1/8 tsp salt', '1/8 tsp black pepper', '3/4 cup all-purpose flour', '2 tsp Cajun or Old Bay seasoning', '1 eggs', '2 tsp butter', '1 tbsp Extra Virgin Olive Oil', '1 lbs flounder, catfish, tilapia, or other thin white fish fillets', '4 whole wheat hamburger buns']
steps: ['In a medium serving bowl, combine the slaw, mayonnaise, vinegar, honey, salt, and pepper. Set it aside. If possible, make this up to 24 hours in advance and refrigerate it until you are ready to serve. whisk it well before serving.', 'In a shallow dish or bowl, combine the flour and Cajun or Old Bay seasoning. In another shallow bowl, beat the egg.', 'In a large heavy skillet a cast iron wok works great for this, heat the butter and oil over medium heat until it is bubbling.', 'Dip the fish pieces in the flour mixture to coat them. Dip them in the egg, letting the excess drip back into the bowl. Dip them back into the flour mixture to recoat. Cook the fish until it is nicely browned and crispy, about 2-3 minutes per side. Remove the fish to a plate.', 'Toast the buns. Serve the fish inside the buns and topped with the slaw.', 'FLAVOR BOOSTER Serve the sandwiches topped with barbecue sauce or your favorite sandwich spread. Finely grate 1/4 onion into the coleslaw.']

Ingredients: ['1 cup uncooked whole-wheat elbow pasta', '1/2 cup diced red bell pepper', '1/2 cup diced cucumber', '1/2 cup small broccoli florets', '1 large carrot', '1 cup diced cooked chicken breast', '1/4 cup light mayonnaise', '1 tbsp red wine vinegar', '1/8 tsp dried oregano', '1/8 tsp freshly ground black pepper']
steps: ['Cook the pasta according to the package directions. Drain.', 'In a large bowl, whisk together the pasta, red bell pepper, cucumber, broccoli, carrots, and chicken.', 'In a small bowl, whisk together the dressing ingredients. Pour the dressing over the pasta, vegetables, and chicken and whisk well. Serve.']

Ingredients: ['1/2 cup chia seeds', '2 1/2 cup low fat milk', '1 tsp vanilla extract', '1/2 cup raspberries', '1 tbsp maple syrup', '2 tsp rose water', '1 1/2 tsp lemon juice', '1/4 cup cooked soba noodles', '1/2 cup pomegranate seeds']
steps: ['In a large bowl, combine chia seeds and milk. Soak chia seeds for 8 hours or overnight in the refrigerator.', 'After chia seeds have soaked, put vanilla extract. whisk well and set aside.', 'In a medium bowl, combine the raspberries, maple syrup, rose water, and lemon. Stir gently to combine and set aside.', 'In a short glass, put a layer of chia seed mixture, a thin layer of raspberry mixture, and a thin layer of soba noodles. Repeat for each serving and garnish each serving with pomegranate seeds.']

Ingredients: ['1 24-oz bag fingerling potatoes', '1 16-oz package frozen cauliflower florets', '1/3 cup skim milk', '5 tbsp Smart Balance margarine', '1/2 tsp salt', '1/2 tsp black pepper']
steps: ['put potatoes to a large soup pot. Cover with cold water and bring to a boil.
