Cook for 15 minutes. put cauliflower to pot, return to a boil, and cook for 5 more minutes.', 'Drain potatoes and cauliflower and return to pot.', 'put remaining ingredients and mash mixture with a potato masher. whisk with an electric whisker on low-speed for about 1 minute.']

Ingredients: ['4 6-oz fillets center-cut salmon with skin', '2 tbsp no-sugar-puted ketchup', '1 tbsp fruit-sweetened apricot jam', '1 tbsp reduced-sodium tamari or soy sauce', '2 tsp rice vinegar', '1/4 tsp hot sauce', '1 tsp sesame seeds']
steps: ['First heat the oven to 400 F. Line a large rimmed baking sheet with parchment paper.', 'Place the salmon, skin side down, on the baking sheet.', 'In a small bowl, stir together the ketchup, jam, tamari, vinegar, and hot pepper sauce. Lightly spread the mixture onto the top of each fillet using the back of the spoon. Sprinkle with the sesame seeds.', 'Bake until the salmon is flaky and cooked through with an internal temperature of at least 145 F, about 16 minutes. Serve.']

Ingredients: ['4 tbsp salsa', '4 tbsp Plain Nonfat Greek yogurt', '2 avocados', '1/3 cup black beans', '1/4 tsp salt', '4 tsp reduced-fat shredded cheddar or Mexican-style cheese', '1 lime']
steps: ['Place the beans in a small bowl. Using the back of a fork, chop them until they reach an almost smooth consistency.', 'Cut the avocados in half and cut off the pits. In the center of each avocado, place 1 tablespoon of beans, 1 tablespoon of Greek yogurt and 1 tablespoon of salsa and sprinkle with 1 teaspoon of cheese. Sprinkle the salt evenly over the avocados. Serve each avocado half with 1 lime wedge to squeeze over the plate.']

Recipe Name: Anjeer Khajoor Barfi Fig and Date Bars
Ingredients: ['1 cup about 15 figs dried figs', '1 cup about 18 dates pitted dates', '1 tbsp water', '1 tbsp sunflower oil', '1 tsp ghee', '3 tbsp finely chopped almonds', '2 tbsp finely chopped cashews', '2 tbsp finely chopped pistachios', '3 pods green cardamom pods']
steps: ['Soak figs and dates, separately, in bowls of hot water use just enough water to cover the fruit for 15-20 minutes. Drain water and grind figs and dates together using a food processor to form a smooth paste. put 1 Tbsp / 15 mL water to reach the right consistency.', 'Combine sunflower oil and ghee in a small bowl, then put mixture to a heavy-bottomed wok over medium heat. put the fig and date puree. Cook, stirring frequently, until mixture dries out, about 15 minutes.', 'Stir in almonds, cashews, pistachios, and cardamom seeds and whisk well to combine. Continue cooking over medium-low heat, stirring frequently, for another 10 minutes, or until mixture starts to pull away from the sides of the wok.', 'Transfer mixture to a greased plate or wok and press down to form the barfi. Set aside to cool completely. Once cool, cut into squares or diamonds and serve.']

Ingredients: ['2 15-ounce cans canned beans', '1/2 cup yellow onion', '1 cup cooked whole grain such as brown rice, oatmeal, or quinoa', '1 large eggs', '1 tsp garlic powder', '1/2 tsp salt', '1/2 tsp ground black pepper', '1 nonstick cooking spray']
steps: ['put 1 1/2 cups of the beans to a large bowl with the onions. With a fork or potato masher, mash until mostly smooth will be slightly chunky from onions. Note: If you have a food processor, you can blend until smooth then put in a bowl.', 'put the remaining beans, the cooked grain, egg, garlic powder, salt and pepper. Stir until well combined.', 'Form bean mixture into 8, 1/2-inch thick patties.', 'put cooking spray to a non-stick skillet over medium heat. put bean patties and cook about 2-3 minutes per side, until slightly brown. Work in batches if your wok is not big enough to hold all 8 burgers.', 'Store in an airtight container in the refrigerator for up to 1 week or wrap individually in freezer bags or containers and freeze up to 6 months freeze cooked burgers only, do not freeze the raw burgers.']

Recipe Name: Black Bean and Mango Salsa Lettuce Wraps
Ingredients: ['1 15-oz can black beans', '1 mango', '1/2 small red onion', '1 medium jalapenoseno pepper', '1 large red bell pepper', '2 tbsp red wine vinegar', '1 tbsp olive oil', '1 tbsp honey or 2 packets artificial sweetener', '10 butter lettuce']
steps: ['Combine all ingredients in a medium sized bowl except lettuce. Refrigerate for at least one hour, or up to two days to marinate the longer the better.', 'If using butter lettuce leaves arrange them on a large plate and fill each one with 1/4 cup of salad mixture.', 'Alternative Serving Suggestion: Use jicama instead of lettuce for the serving vessel. Peel the jicama and slice into 1/4-inch thick rounds, then slice the rounds into triangles eighths to resemble tortilla chips. Serve like chips and salsa using the raw jicama  Çìchips Ç ù instead of tortilla chips.']

Ingredients: ['1 nonstick cooking spray', '1 lbs chicken breasts', '1/4 cup barbeque sauce', '4 turkey bacon', '2 carrot', '16 oz romaine lettuce', '1/2 medium red onion', '1 large cucumber', '1 large tomato', '1/2 tsp salt', '1/2 tsp black pepper', '1/2 cup poppy seed dressing']
steps: ['First heat oven to 375 degrees F.', 'Coat a baking sheet with cooking spray. Line the sheet with chicken breasts and brush each generously with barbeque sauce. Bake for 30 minutes or until internal temperature of chicken is 165 degrees F. Set aside to cool.', 'In a large salad bowl, toss together bacon, carrots, lettuce, onion, cucumber, tomatoes, salt optional, and pepper.', 'Once chicken is cool, chop into small pieces and toss with the salad ingredients.', 'Pour dressing over salad and toss gently to coat.']

Recipe Name: Cinnamon Ginger Apple On A Stick
Ingredients: ['3 apple', '1 Juice of 1 lemon', '1 tbsp fresh ginger root', '1/2 tsp ground cinnamon', '1 tbsp honey', '1/4 cup walnuts or pecans', '6 wooden or metal skewers']
steps: ['Marinate apple halves in all ingredients except walnuts.', 'First heat grill to medium high. Cook as per directions for direct heat method for 5-6 minutes, turning once until golden brown on the outside and just warmed through on the inside.', 'Remove apples from the grill, cool for a few minutes, and roll in crushed walnuts. Press gently.', 'Place a skewer in each apple half and serve.']

Ingredients: ['4 oz drained, canned lump crab meat', '2 tbsp finely chopped green onions', '1 tbsp light mayonnaise', '2 tbsp lemon zest', '1 tsp Fresno pepper', '1 1/2 tbsp whole wheat wokko', '12 extra large', '1 Extra virgin olive oil wok spray']
steps: ['First heat the oven to 475F. Line a small baking sheet with nonstick foil.', 'whisk the crab, green onions, mayonnaise, lemon zest, and peppers in small bowl until they are well combined.', 'Spread the bread crumbs on a small plate and set aside.', 'To butterfly the shrimp: Peel all but the tail and last joint of the shell off the shrimp. On a cutting board, place a shrimp so that the head end and tail are touching the cutting board and the center arches toward the ceiling. Insert a knife into the shrimp near the head, just past the remaining shell, and cut down the center of the shrimp s back to the tail, cutting just deep enough to flatten the shrimp make sure not to cut all the way through. Run the shrimp under cold water to clean it. Dry it well with paper towels. Repeat the procedure with the remaining shrimp and place them side by side, not touching, on the prepared baking sheet.', 'Divide the crab mixture evenly among the shrimp, about 1/2 tablespoon per shrimp, forming it into a tight mound on top of the butterflied portion of each shrimp.', 'Carefully dip each shrimp, gently turning it upside down, into the bread crumbs to lightly coat the crab not the whole shrimp, just the portion with the crab. Return shrimp to the baking sheet and make sure the crab mound isn t flattened if it is, reshape it slightly to look like a mound. Sprinkle any remaining bread crumbs evenly over the tops. Mist the tops lightly with spray.', 'Bake the shrimp 7-10 minutes or until they are no longer translucent throughout. Enjoy immediately.']

Ingredients: ['1 nonstick cooking spray', '8 about 2 lbs chicken drumsticks', '1 large onion', '1 green bell pepper', '1 14.5-oz can canned diced tomatoes', '10 oz fresh or frozen cut okra', '1 tsp Worcestershire sauce', '1/2 tsp dried thyme', '1/4 tsp Louisiana-style hot sauce', '1/8 tsp salt']
steps: ['Lightly spray a Dutch oven with cooking spray. Heat over medium-high heat. Cook the chicken for about 4 minutes, or until browned on all sides, turning frequently the chicken won t be done at this point. Transfer to a plate.', 'In the same pot, cook the onion and bell pepper for 3 minutes, or until the edges are beginning to lightly brown, stirring frequently and scraping to dislodge any browned bits.', 'Gently stir in the chicken with any accumulated juices. Stir in the remaining ingredients except the salt. Bring to a boil, still over medium-high heat. Reduce the heat and simmer, covered, for 40 minutes, or until the chicken is no longer pink in the center and the okra is very tender. Remove from the heat.', 'Transfer the chicken to soup bowls. Stir the salt into the tomato mixture. Pour over the chicken.']

Ingredients: ['2 tbsp yellow cornmeal', '2 tbsp wokko or plain dried bread crumbs', '1 tsp Cornstarch', '1/2 tsp lemon pepper', '2 tilapia', '2 tsp fresh lemon juice', '2 tbsp pecans', '1 tbsp fresh Italian']
steps: ['First heat the broiler. Lightly spray an 11x7x2-inch baking wok with cooking spray.', 'In a shallow dish, stir together the cornmeal, wokko, cornstarch, and lemon pepper. put the fish, turning to coat, shaking off any excess. Transfer to the baking wok. Lightly spray both sides of the fish with cooking spray.', 'Broil for 3-4 minutes on each side, or until the fish flakes easily when tested with a fork. Transfer to plates. Drizzle with the lemon juice. Sprinkle with the pecans and parsley.']

Ingredients: ['2 can no salt puted diced tomatoes', '1 large onion', '4 clove garlic', '2 large carrots', '2 stalks celery', '1 medium parsnip', '1 large red bell pepper', '6 cup low sodium vegetable broth', '3 cup cabbage', '1 tsp Spike seasoning', '1/2 tsp salt', '1/4 tsp black pepper', '1 large sweet potato']
steps: ['Stir together all the ingredients in a crock pot.', 'Set the crock pot on high setting for 4-6 hours.', 'Stir well before serving and lightly mash the parsnips and sweet potatoes to thicken the soup slightly.']

Ingredients: ['1 nonstick cooking spray', '2 cup fresh kale', '1/2 small onion', '1/2 tsp salt', '1/2 tsp herbs dÇÑ¢provence', '1 cup cooked turkey sausage crumbles', '1 cup egg substitute', '4 egg whites', '1/2 tsp cream of tartar']
steps: ['First heat the oven to 375 degrees F.', 'Coat a saute wok with cooking spray over medium heat. Saute the kale and onions until the onions are just cooked through, about 5-6 minutes. put the salt optional, Herbs d Provence, and turkey sausage. Set aside to cool.', 'Once the vegetables and meat are cool, stir in the egg substitute and set aside.', 'In a clean bowl, combine the egg whites and cream of tartar. Using an electric whisker, whip the egg whites to stiff peaks.', 'Gently fold the egg whites into the egg and vegetable mixture, and pour it into a 2 1/2 quart round baking dish. You can also use an 8-inch square dish. Be sure not to coat baking dish with cooking spray or the souffle will not rise.', 'Bake for 30 minutes. Cut the souffle into four equal pieces and serve immediately.', 'Note: The souffle will fall a little once removed from the oven, this is normal.']

Ingredients: ['1 8-Ounce Splenda French Vanilla Diabetes Care Shake', '1/2 cup frozen mango', '1/4 small bananas', '1/4 cup spinach', '1 tbsp ground flax seed', '1 kiwi', '1 fresh strawberries', '2 tsp unsweetened coconut flakes']
steps: ['Combine Splenda Diabetes Care Shake, mango, banana, spinach, and flaxseed in a blender. Blend until smooth, scraping down the sides as needed.', 'Spoon smoothie into serving bowl and top with kiwi, strawberry, and coconut flakes. Serve immediately and enjoy.']

Ingredients: ['1 tbsp olive oil', '2 tbsp balsamic vinegar', '1/4 tsp black pepper', '1 medium zucchini', '1 medium yellow squash', '1 orange bell pepper', '1 small eggplant', '1/4 cup goat cheese', '1 cup Plain Nonfat Greek yogurt', '1 clove garlic', '1 tbsp minced fresh oregano', '1/4 tsp black pepper', '1/4 cup chopped fresh basil']
steps: ['First heat an indoor or outdoor grill.', 'In a large bowl, whisk together olive oil, balsamic vinegar and ground black pepper.', 'put sliced zucchini, squash, bell pepper and eggplant to marinade and let sit for 5 minutes.', 'Grill the vegetables about 2-3 minutes on both sides.', 'Once grilled, cut the zucchini, eggplant and squash in half width-wise so that you have 8 pieces of each and set aside to cool.', 'In a medium bowl, whisk together goat cheese, yogurt, garlic, oregano and ground black pepper.', 'Lay 1 piece of eggplant on a plate, top with 1 heaping Tbsp. of cheese mixture, top that with two slices of zucchini, then top with another heaping Tbsp. of cheese mixture. Top that with 1 slice of bell pepper then another heaping Tbsp. of cheese mixture. Top that with two slices of yellow squash, then another heaping Tbsp. of cheese mixture and then the other slice of eggplant. Sprinkle with 1 Tbsp. chopped fresh basil. Repeat process for three more Napoleons.']

Ingredients: ['3 zucchini', '1 tbsp olive oil', '1/4 cup reduced-fat crumbled feta cheese']
steps: ['First heat the grill to medium-high.', 'Drizzle the olive oil evenly over the zucchini halves. Grill the zucchini 4-5 minutes per side, until tender.', 'Remove the zucchini from the grill and sprinkle each with feta cheese.']

Ingredients: ['1/4 cup light mayonnaise', '1/3 cup sour cream', '1 clove medium garlic', '2 cider vinegar', '1 tbsp dried dill', '6 cup romaine lettuce', '1 cup fresh shelled edamame', '4 oz extra-lean ham', '1/2 medium cucumber', '1/2 cup green bell pepper', '1/3 cup red onion', '2 oz Swiss cheese', '2 large hard boiled eggs']
steps: ['In a small bowl, stir together the dressing ingredients.', 'In a large bowl, combine the salad ingredients, except the eggs. Cut the eggs in half, discard two yolk halves, and chop the remaining eggs. put eggs to the salad with the dressing and toss until well coated.']

Recipe Name: Instant Pot Coconut Curry Vegetable Rice Bowls
Ingredients: ['2/3 cup brown rice', '1 cup water', '1 tsp curry powder', '3/4 tsp salt', '1 cup chopped green onion', '1 cup sliced red or yellow bell pepper', '1 cup matchstick carrots', '1 cup chopped red cabbage', '1 8-oz can sliced water chestnuts', '1 15-oz can no-salt-puted chickpeas', '1 13-oz can lite coconut milk', '1 tbsp grated fresh ginger', '1 1/2 tbsp sugar']
steps: ['Combine the rice, water, curry powder, and 1/4 tsp of the salt in the Instant Pot. Seal the lid, close the valve, and set the Manual/Pressure Cook button to 15 minutes.', 'Use a natural pressure release for about 12 minutes. When the valve drops, carefully remove the lid and stir in the remaining ingredients.', 'Press the Cancel button and set to Saute. Then press the Adjust button to  ÇìMore Ç ù or  ÇìHigh. Ç ù Bring to a boil and boil for 2 minutes, or until all the ingredients are heated through, stirring occasionally.']

Ingredients: ['1/2 green bell pepper', '1/8 tsp salt', 'to taste crushed red pepper flakes', '1 tsp dried oregano', '1 tbsp olive oil', '2 tsp dried basil', '1/2 cup chopped red onion', '2 tbsp capers', '2 tbsp Apple Cider Vinegar', '1/2 cup chopped fresh parsley', '10 oz about 2 cups grape or cherry tomatoes']
steps: ['In a medium bowl, gently toss together all the ingredients. Let stand for 10 minutes before serving.']

Recipe Name: Italian-Style Chicken & Couscous with Carrots, Currants, and Kale
Ingredients: ['6 oz about 3 whole carrots carrots', '1 bunch about 6 oz kale', '2 clove garlic', '1/2 cup couscous', '1 cup water', '1/3 cup basil pesto', '3 tsp olive oil', '2 tbsp dried currants', '1 tbsp red wine vinegar', '2 6-oz breasts boneless, skinless chicken breasts', '1 tbsp Italian seasoning blend']
steps: ['Prepare the ingredients: Wash and dry the fresh produce. Peel the carrots thinly slice on an angle. Separate the kale leaves from stems discard the stems, then roughly chop the leaves. Peel and roughly chop 2 cloves of garlic.', 'Cook & finish the couscous: In a medium pot, combine the couscous and 3/4 cup of water. Heat to boiling on high. Once boiling, turn off the heat. Cover and let stand 6 to 8 minutes, or until the water has been absorbed and the couscous is tender. Fluff with a fork. put the pesto stir to combine.', 'Cook the vegetables: Meanwhile, in a medium wok nonstick, if you have one, heat 1 teaspoon of olive oil on medium-high until hot. put the sliced carrots season with salt optional and pepper. Cook, stirring occasionally, 3 to 4 minutes, or until slightly softened. put the chopped kale and chopped garlic. Cook, stirring occasionally, 2 to 3 minutes, or until the kale is slightly wilted. put the currants and 1/4 cup of water carefully, as the liquid may splatter. Cook, stirring occasionally, 3 to 4 minutes, or until the kale is wilted and the water has cooked off. Turn off the heat and stir in the vinegar. Transfer to a bowl and cover with foil to keep warm. Wipe out the wok.', 'Cook the chicken & serve your dish: Pat the chicken dry with paper towels season on both sides with salt optional, pepper, and enough of the Italian seasoning to coat you may have extra. In the same wok, heat 2 teaspoons of olive oil on medium-high until hot. put the seasoned chicken. Cook 6 to 7 minutes per side, or until browned and cooked through.** Transfer to a cutting board slice crosswise. Serve the sliced chicken with the cooked vegetables and finished couscous. Enjoy! **An instant-read thermometer should register 165F.']

Ingredients: ['1 lbs lean pork tenderloin', '1/2 cup plus 3 tbsp apricot or mango nectar', '2 green onion', '3 tbsp lower sodium soy sauce', '1 1/2 tsp grapeseed or safflower oil', '1 tbsp fresh gingerroot', '1/4 tsp ground cinnamon', '1/4 tsp hot pepper sauce']
steps: ['Place the pork in a large sealable food container. In a medium bowl, whisk together 1/2 cup of the nectar, half of the scallions, the soy sauce, oil, gingerroot, cinnamon, and hot pepper sauce. Pour the mixture into the container, seal tightly, and refrigerate at least 4 hours or overnight, rotating the pork occasionally. Separately cover and chill the remaining nectar and scallions.', 'First heat the oven to 450F. Remove the nectar and scallion from the refrigerator. Place the marinated pork on an unbleached parchment paper-lined baking wok. Discard the remaining marinade. Alternatively, you can boil the remaining marinade for at least 2 minutes for safe use as a sauce with the meal. Roast the pork until cooked through, but very slightly pink in the middle, about 20 minutes or to an internal temperature of 145F. Let stand at least 5 minutes before slicing.', 'Cut the pork into 24 slices. Fan out 6 slices per plate. Drizzle with reserved nectar, garnish with remaining scallion, and serve.']

Ingredients: ['1 large head cauliflower', '2 tsp butter', '1/4 cup grated white cheddar cheese', '1/8 tsp salt', '1/8 tsp black pepper', '2 tbsp chopped fresh chives']
steps: ['Cut the cauliflower into florets discard the thick stem. Insert a steamer basket in a large pot and fill the pot with water up until the level of the steamer basket. put the cauliflower florets. Cover the pot and steam over high heat for 8 minutes or until the cauliflower is softened.', 'Drain the cauliflower and put it to a large bowl. Use a fork or potato masher to mash the cauliflower. Stir in the butter and cheese while the cauliflower is still hot. put the salt and pepper and stir until the mixture is mostly smooth and creamy. Serve and top with chives.']

Recipe Name: Mini Pear and Goat Cheese Tarts
Ingredients: ['14 mini fillo shells', '1 1/2 cup pear', '2 oz goat cheese', '2 egg whites', '1/4 tsp black pepper', '1/4 cup balsamic vinegar']
steps: ['First heat oven to 350 degrees.', 'Arrange thawed fillo cups on to a baking sheet. Set aside.', 'In a medium bowl, whisk together pears, goat cheese, egg whites and ground black pepper.', 'Fill each fillo cup with a heaping Tbsp. of pear mixture.', 'Drizzle to top of each tart with a little balsamic vinegar.', 'Bake for 15 minutes. Serve hot or room temperature.']

Ingredients: ['2 1/4 cup oat bran', '1/4 cup firmly packed brown sugar', '1 tbsp baking powder', '1 1/2 tsp ground cinnamon', '3/4 cup milk', '1/4 cup egg substitute', '2 tbsp canola oil', '1 cup unsweetened applesauce', '1 medium banana', '2 tbsp Fruit']
steps: ['First heat oven to 425 degrees.', 'whisk the first four ingredients in a large bowl. Set aside.', 'Combine milk, egg, and oil. whisk applesauce with mashed banana and blend with liquid ingredients. put to dry ingredients and whisk just until moistened.', 'Pour into muffin tins that have been sprayed with nonstick cooking spray. Do not use paper liners, as the muffins have a tendency to stick to the paper. Bake for 15-17 minutes.', 'TIP: The tops of these muffins don t brown well due to the low sugar content, but they are still moist and full of flavor!']

Ingredients: ['2 medium ears of corn', '2 tsp olive oil', '1 tbsp Parmesan cheese', '1 Salt and freshly ground pepper']
steps: ['Shuck corn, and wrap each ear in a damp paper towel.', 'Place in ears on a dinner plate, and microwave on high 2 minutes. Turn corn over and microwave on high 1 1/2 minutes.', 'Remove paper towel, and rub corn with oil. Sprinkle Parmesan cheese over corn, put salt and pepper to taste, and serve.']

Ingredients: ['8 medium asparagus spears', '1 tbsp walnuts', '2 tsp light balsamic vinaigrette', '1 Pepper, to taste']
steps: ['First heat oven to 425 degrees F. Line a baking sheet with aluminum foil. Lightly spray with cooking spray.', 'Arrange the asparagus in a single layer on the baking sheet. Sprinkle the walnuts around the asparagus. Lightly spray the asparagus with cooking spray. Roll back and forth to coat.', 'Roast for 5 minutes. Using tongs, turn the asparagus over gently. Roast for 4 minutes, or until the walnuts begin to brown. Transfer to a plate.', 'Spoon the vinaigrette over the asparagus and walnuts. Roll back and forth to coat. Sprinkle with the pepper. Let stand for 10 minutes so the flavors blend.', 'Cook s Tip: Be sure to dry the asparagus thoroughly before cooking or it will not brown properly.']

Ingredients: ['1 nonstick cooking spray', '1 package white', '1 medium sweet potato', '1 medium onion', '1 medium red bell pepper', '1/2 tsp Spike seasoning', '2 eggs', '4 egg whites', '1 tsp mustard', '2 tbsp fresh sage', '1/2 tsp salt', '1/2 tsp black pepper', '8 slice whole wheat bread', '1/2 cup Parmesan cheese']
steps: ['First heat the oven to 375 degrees F. Coat a large baking sheet with cooking spray.', 'Toss all of the vegetables together and spread evenly on the baking sheet. Spray the vegetables with 5-6 sprays of cooking spray and season with salt-free Spike seasoning.', 'Roast the vegetables for 30 minutes, then set aside to cool slightly.', 'whisk together the eggs, egg whites, dried mustard, sage, salt optional, and black pepper.', 'Coat a 9x13-inch casserole dish with cooking spray. Tear four pieces of the whole wheat bread into pieces and layer them on the bottom of the casserole dish. Top with 1/2 the roasted vegetables and 1/4 cup Parmesan cheese. Pour half the egg mixture over the bread, vegetables, and cheese.', 'Repeat the layering process with the remaining torn bread, vegetables, cheese, and egg mixture. Press down on the casserole with a spatula to ensure all of the bread soaks in the egg mixture. Let the strata sit at room temperature for 15 minutes.', 'Bake the strata for 30 minutes.', 'To serve, cut the strata down the middle lengthwise, then cut down the middle width-wise. Cut each half down the middle width-wise again to make 8 equal servings.']

Ingredients: ['1 onion', '3 clove garlic', '1 1/2 tsp smoked paprika', '1/2 cup white wine', '15 oz fire-roasted tomatoes', '15 oz cannellini beans', '10 oz spinach', '2 tsp olive oil', '1 tbsp balsamic vinegar', '1/4 tsp black pepper']
steps: ['Heat the oil in a large saucewok over medium heat. put the onion and saute for 5 to 6 minutes. put the garlic and smoked paprika and saute for 1 minute.', 'put the white wine and cook for 2 minutes. put the tomatoes and cook for 5 to 6 minutes. put the beans and cook for 5 minutes. put the spinach and cook until it is wilted. Stir in the balsamic vinegar and pepper and serve.']

Ingredients: ['30 oz chickpeas', '14 oz canned diced tomatoes', '5 cup chicken or vegetable broth', '2 tsp fresh rosemary', '2 tbsp fresh basil', '2 tbsp balsamic vinegar', '4 clove garlic', '2 carrot', '2 stalks celery', '1 onion', '1 tbsp olive oil']
steps: ['In a saucewok over medium heat, heat the olive oil. put the onions, celery and carrots and sautÈ for 5 minutes. A put the garlic and rosemary and sautÈ for 1 minute. put the rest of the ingredients, except the vinegar and basil. Bring to a boil. Reduce the heat and simmer, partially covered, for 20 minutes.', 'A put the vinegar. Top with basil before serving.']

Ingredients: ['1 cup baby spinach', '2 tbsp sliced celery', '2 small button mushrooms', '1 slice red onion', '1/2 orange', '2 tbsp orange juice', '1 tbsp lemon juice', '1 tsp olive oil', '1 tsp lower sodium soy sauce', '1 tsp honey', '1/8 tsp ground ginger', '1/8 tsp black pepper', '1 tbsp pepitas']
steps: ['In a medium salad bowl, toss together the spinach, celery, mushrroms, onion, and orange sections.', 'In a small bowl, whisk together the remaining ingredients except the pumpkin seeds. Drizzle over the salad. Toss to combine. Garnish with the pumpkin seeds.']

Recipe Name: Spinach and Sweet Potato Curry Saag Aloo
Ingredients: ['2 about 12 oz total medium sweet potatoes', '1 tbsp olive oil', '1 medium onion', '2 clove garlic', '1/2 tsp salt', '1/2 tsp black pepper', '1 tsp cumin', '1 tsp turmeric', '1 tsp ground ginger', '1 tbsp chili powder', '1 cup water or vegetable broth', '5 oz baby spinach']
steps: ['put sweet potatoes and 1/2 cup water to a microwave-safe container or steamer with a lid. Microwave for 7-8 minutes or until sweet potatoes are just fork tender. Don t overcook them.', 'While the sweet potatoes are steaming, put olive oil to a large saute wok over medium heat. put the onions and saute for 3-4 minutes or until onions turn clear. put the garlic and saute 2 more minutes.', 'put the salt, pepper, cumin, turmeric, ginger, chili powder and water or broth. Bring to a simmer.', 'put in the spinach and cook until wilted, about 5 minutes.', 'Stir in the sweet potatoes to heat through.']

Recipe Name: Spinach, Tomato and Feta Cheese Baked Egg
Ingredients: ['1 nonstick cooking spray', '1/2 cup spinach', '1/4 cup tomatoes', '2 tbsp feta cheese', '1 tsp fresh oregano', '4 medium eggs']
steps: ['First heat oven to 375 degrees F.', 'Spray 4 ramekins with cooking spray. Combine the spinach, tomato, feta cheese, and oregano evenly distribute into ramekins. Place egg over spinach mixture and bake until egg whites are set but the yolks are still soft, about 10-12 minutes.']

Ingredients: ['1 lbs extra firm tofu', '1/4 cup lite sesame ginger salad dressing', '2 tsp sesame oil', '1 nonstick cooking spray', '2 cup broccoli florets', '1 package white', '1/4 cup almonds', '1 cup low sodium vegetable broth', '1 tbsp Cornstarch', '1 tbsp soy sauce', '1 tsp Asian style hot sauce', '1 tbsp Splenda Brown Sugar blend', '2 clove garlic', '4 green onion']
steps: ['whisk the tofu and sesame ginger salad dressing in a bowl and marinate for 30 minutes.', 'Once the tofu is done marinating, remove the tofu from the marinade and reserve the marinade.', 'put the sesame oil and cooking spray to a wok or large saute wok over high heat. put the tofu and stir fry for 7-8 minutes, or until the tofu is golden brown.', 'put the broccoli and mushrooms, and stir fry for 3-4 minutes. put in the scallions and almonds, and stir fry for an putitional 2 minutes.', 'In a bowl or cup, whisk together the vegetable broth, cornstarch, soy sauce, hot sauce, Splenda Brown Sugar Blend, and garlic. whisk in the reserved sesame ginger dressing marinade. Pour the mixture over the tofu and bring to a boil.', 'Reduce to a simmer and simmer for 5 minutes.', 'Serve Suggestion: Serve over brown rice or in lettuce cups']

Ingredients: ['1/2 cup Apple Cider Vinegar', '7 clove garlic', '1 2-inch piece fresh ginger', '1 tbsp cumin seeds', '2 tsp Kashmiri chili powder or smoked paprkia', '1 tsp black peppercorns', '1 tsp mustard seeds', '1/4 tsp ground cinnamon', '3/4 tsp salt', '1 1/2 lbs pork tenderloin']
steps: ['In a food processor, blend together the vinegar, garlic, ginger, cloves, cumin seeds, chili powder, peppercorns, mustard seeds, and cinnamon until ground to a fine paste. Stir in the salt until well blended.', 'Brush the spice rub over the pork. Cover and refrigerate for at least 6 hours.', 'After 6 hours, remove the pork from the refrigerator. Let stand at room temperature for 1 hour. First heat the oven to 425F.', 'Place the pork in a heavy roasting wok. Roast on the middle rack of the oven for 30 minutes, or until an instant-read thermometer inserted into the thickest part of the tenderloin registers 140F.', 'Remove from the oven. Transfer the pork to a cutting board. Tent with aluminum foil. Let stand for 10 minutes before slicing and serving.']

Recipe Name: White Bean, Lemon, and Herbed Feta Dip
Ingredients: ['1 1/2 cup canned or cooked cannellini beans', '1/2 cup Greek feta cheese', '1 juice and zest of 1 lemon', '1/4 cup extra-virgin olive oil', '1/4 cup fresh mint', '1/4 cup fresh oregano', 'to taste freshly ground black pepper']
steps: ['Combine cannellini beans, feta, lemon juice and zest, olive oil, mint, and oregano in a food processor. Pulsing on and off, puree until smooth.', 'Taste and season with salt if desired and pepper.']

Ingredients: ['1/4 cup slivered almonds', '8 sugar-free caramel-flavored hard candies', '1 pinch salt', '3/4 cup water', '1/4 cup apple juice', '1 cinnamon stick', '2 firm pears', '1 tsp light butter with canola oil', '1/2 tsp vanilla extract']
steps: ['Press the Saute button on the multicooker. When the pot is hot, put the almonds and cook for 4 minutes, stirring occasionally. Set aside to cool, then coarsely chop.', 'In a small bowl, put the chopped almonds, crushed candies, and salt. Set aside.', 'Place the water, juice, and cinnamon stick in the multicooker pot. Place the steamer basket in the pot and arrange the pears on top of it.', 'Seal the lid, close the valve, and press the Cancel button. Select Manual and cook for 2 minutes. If you prefer a very tender pear, cook an putitional minute. Use a quick pressure release.', 'When the valve drops, carefully remove the lid. Remove the steamer basket and pears. Place the pears, cut side up, in four dessert bowls. Remove and discard the cinnamon stick.', 'Press the Cancel button, then press the Saute button. Bring the liquid in the pot to a boil. Boil for 3 minutes, or until the liquid is reduced to  º cup. Stir in the butter, vanilla extract, and almond-candy mixture. Cook for 30 seconds, or until the toffee has melted, stirring constantly.', 'Working quickly, spoon about 4 tsp of the toffee sauce into the center of each pear half.']

Ingredients: ['4 tbsp unsalted butter', '3 clove garlic', '1/2 cup chopped onion', '1/2 tsp black pepper', '1/4 tsp ground nutmeg', '1 bay leaf', '1/2 cup all-purpose flour', '4 cup low sodium chicken broth', '2 cup chopped cooked chicken', '1/2 cup dry vermouth', '4 cup unsweetened almond milk', '1 bunch asparagus', '3/4 cup wild rice', '1/2 tsp dried thyme', '1/2 tsp salt']
steps: ['Prepare the wild rice according to package instructions, omitting salt and seasoning packet if included. Remove the wok from heat, allow rice to sit, covered, for putitional 15 minutes. Set aside and let cool.', 'In a Dutch oven, melt the butter and saute the garlic and onion until tender. put carrots, herbs and spices. Continue to cook over medium heat until tender.', 'whisk in the flour and cook over low heat for a few minutes, stirring frequently.', 'Pour in the 4 cups of chicken broth and vermouth. Using a wire whisk, blend until smooth.', 'put chicken and asparagus to the soup, then slowly put the almond milk. Simmer for 20 minutes.', 'Fold in prepared rice, and serve.']

Recipe Name: Curried Quinoa With Butternut Squash And Chickpeas
Ingredients: ['1 small butternut squash', '2 tbsp Extra Virgin Olive Oil', '1/2 tsp fine sea salt', '1/4 tsp freshly ground black pepper', '1 cup uncooked quinoa', '2 1/4 cup water', '1 1/2 curry powder', '1 1/2 ground cumin', '2 fresh ginger', '1 tsp mustard powder', '1 chickpeas', '2 tbsp red wine vinegar', '1 tsp lime zest', '1/4 cup pumpkin seeds', '1/4 cup fresh cilantro']
steps: ['First heat the oven to 400F. Line a rimmed baking sheet with parchment paper.', 'In a medium bowl, whisk the squash with 1 tablespoon olive oil, 1/4 teaspoon salt, and 1/8 teaspoon pepper. Toss to evenly coat. Spread squash onto the prepared baking sheet. Bake for about 15 minutes, stir, then bake for an putitional 15 minutes, or until tender. Remove baking sheet from the oven and set aside.', 'While squash is in the oven, combine the quinoa, water, curry powder, cumin, ginger, and mustard powder in a medium saucewok over medium-high heat. Bring the mixture to a boil, then reduce the heat to low, cover, and simmer until the liquid is absorbed, about 12-15 minutes. Do not stir once covered.', 'In a large bowl, combine cooked quinoa, roasted squash, the remaining 1 tablespoon olive oil, chickpeas, red wine vinegar, lime zest, pumpkin seeds, and cilantro. Season with the remaining salt and pepper. Serve warm or at room temperature.']

Ingredients: ['1 1/2 tbsp olive oil', '1/2 tsp salt', '1/4 tsp black pepper', '1 onion', '2 whole ears corn', '1/2 jalapenoseno pepper', '4 zucchini', '1 red bell pepper', '2 clove garlic']
steps: ['In a large skillet, heat the oil over medium heat. put the onion and saute for 5 minutes. put the garlic and red and jalapenoseno peppers and saute for 2 minutes.', 'put the zucchini and saute for 3 to 4 minutes. put the corn to the skillet and saute for 2 to 4 minutes. Season with the salt and black pepper.']

Ingredients: ['6 oz arugula', '1 pear', '1/4 cup walnut halves', '1 Pecorino Romano cheese', '2 tbsp balsamic vinegar', '2 tbsp Extra Virgin Olive Oil', '1/2 tsp black pepper']
steps: ['Place the arugula in a large salad bowl. Slice the pear as thinly as possible and place on top of the arugula. Sprinkle with walnut halves. Using a vegetable peeler, shave 1/2 ounce of the Pecorino over the salad bowl.', 'Sprinkle balsamic vinegar over the salad. Sprinkle extra virgin olive oil over the salad. put pepper. Toss well. Serve.']

Recipe Name: Baked Egg with Avocado, Tomato, and Citrus Salad
Ingredients: ['2 eggs', '2 tsp canola oil', '1 oz lime juice', '1 tsp Kosher Salt', '1/2 tsp black pepper', '2 oz Hass avocado', '1 large tomato', '2 oz red onion', '1/4 cup cilantro']
steps: ['First heat oven to 400F.', 'Crack each egg into a separate bowl without breaking the yolks. Set aside.', 'First heat small ovenproof wok and put 1 Tsp. canola oil. put eggs, and immediately transfer wok to the oven. Cook for about 2-5 minutes, or until eggs reach desired doneness.', 'In a small bowl put remaining canola oil, lime juice, salt and pepper, and whisk ingredients together to create the dressing. put avocado, tomato, red onion and cilantro to the dressing and toss.', 'Remove eggs from oven. Plate salad ingredients first and top with the eggs. Serve.']

Ingredients: ['1 nonstick cooking spray', '2 heads broccoli', '1 eggs', '1 egg white', '1/3 cup reduced-fat shredded cheddar or Mexican-style cheese', '1/3 cup bread crumbs', '1/2 cup onion', '1/4 tsp black pepper']
steps: ['First heat the oven to 400 degrees F. Coat one large or two small baking sheets with cooking spray. Set aside.', 'Steam the broccoli for approximately 10 to 12 minutes, until soft. Set aside to cool for about 10 minutes.', 'put the broccoli and remaining ingredients to a blender or food processor and pulse to combine. Do not overwhisk the mixture should be slightly chunky, not a paste. Let the mixture rest for 10 minutes.', 'After resting the mixture, stir it, and scoop and drop by Tbsp.fuls onto the prepared baking sheet.', 'Lightly spray the top of each ball with cooking spray. Bake for 15 minutes. Turn the pieces over and bake an putitional 10 minutes, or until golden brown.']

Ingredients: ['2 margarine', '1 medium onion', '2 carrot', '2 stalks celery', '1 cup white', '44 oz low sodium chicken broth', '1 cup water', '1/4 tsp dried thyme', '1/4 tsp black pepper', '1/4 tsp salt', '1 tbsp Cornstarch', '1 tbsp cold water', '1 cup wild rice', '2 cup cooked chicken']
steps: ['Melt the margarine in a large soup pot over medium-high heat. put the onion and saute for 3 minutes or until clear. put the carrots, celery, and mushrooms, and saute for 5 minutes.', 'put the chicken broth, water, thyme, black pepper, and salt.', 'In a small cup, whisk together the corn starch and 1 Tbsp. cold water. put the mixture to the soup.', 'Bring to a boil and stir in the rice.', 'Reduce heat, cover, and simmer for 45 minutes. put the cooked chicken and stir well.']

Recipe Name: Green Beans With Cranberries and Hazelnuts
Ingredients: ['1 lemon', '1/4 tsp black pepper', '2 lbs fresh green beans', '1 tbsp olive oil', '1/4 cup hazelnuts', '3 tbsp dried cranberries', '1/4 tsp salt']
steps: ['Fill a large pot 2/3 full of water and bring to boiling. put the green beans, turn off the heat, and let the green beans stand in the water for 3 minutes. Drain the beans and put them to a serving bowl or platter.', 'In a small bowl, combine the oil, nuts, cranberries, salt, and pepper. Top the green beans with the cranberry-nut mixture. Garnish with the lemon zest.']

Recipe Name: Grilled Chicken Salad With Candied Pecans
Ingredients: ['1 Olive oil cooking spray', '1/4 cup pecans', '1 tsp sugar', '1/8 tsp ground cayenne red pepper', '10 cup fresh salad greens', '3/4 cup Triple Citrus Vinaigrette', '2 navel oranges', '1/4 cup dried cranberries or apricots', '2 lbs chicken breasts']
steps: ['Heat a small nonstick skillet coated with cooking spray over medium-low heat. put pecans and cook 3-4 minutes or until lightly toasted, stirring frequently. Sprinkle with sugar and red pepper, and cook for 1 minute, stirring constantly. Remove pecans from skillet. Cool on wax paper.', 'Combine greens, Triple Citrus Vinaigrette, and orange sections in a large bowl. Toss well. Place 1 cup greens mixture on each of 8 plates. Top each serving with 1 1 Å û2 teaspoons pecans and 1 1 Å û2 teaspoons cranberries.', 'Top with grilled chicken breast and serve immediately.']

Ingredients: ['24 cherry tomatoes', '1 ripe avocado', '1 lime', '1 clove garlic', '2 tbsp chopped fresh cilantro', '1/2 tsp salt', '1/2 tsp black pepper']
steps: ['Cut out the stem of each cherry tomato, cutting deep enough to make a hole into the middle of the tomato without going through the other end.', 'Scoop the insides of the tomato out and finely chop the insides of tomato and reserve for the guacamole. Place each scooped out tomato upside down on paper towels to drain.', 'In a medium bowl, mash the avocado with a fork and whisk in the scooped out tomato pieces, lime juice, garlic, 1 Tbsp. cilantro, salt optional, and pepper.', 'Scoop or pipe the guacamole into the hollowed out tomatoes, dividing it equally among each tomato. Sprinkle the remaining cilantro on top of each tomato.']

Ingredients: ['1 lbs new potatoes', '1 cup celery', '1/2 cup green onion', '3 tbsp plain yogurt', '1 tbsp light mayonnaise', '1 1/2 tsp Dijon Mustard', '1/2 tsp garlic', '1/2 tsp basil', '1/4 tsp dried thyme', '1/4 tsp onion powder', '1/4 tsp salt']
steps: ['Cut potatoes into 1-inch cubes. Place in medium saucewok and cover with water. Bring to a boil. Cover, reduce heat, and simmer 12 minutes or until potatoes are tender. Drain.', 'whisk dressing ingredients.', 'Combine hot potatoes, celery, green onions, and dressing. Serve hot or refrigerate and serve cold.']

Ingredients: ['1 lbs boneless, skinless chicken breasts', '1 1/2 tbsp lower sodium soy sauce', '1 tbsp rice vinegar', '1 tbsp plus 2 tsp cornstarch or arrowroot', '1 cup low sodium chicken broth', '2 tbsp hoisin sauce', '1 tsp sriracha or garlic chili paste', '1 tbsp vegetable or peanut oil', '3 clove garlic', '1 tbsp fresh ginger', '1 medium red pepper', '2 celery stalks', '1 cup broccoli florets']
steps: ['In a medium-sized bowl, combine the chicken with 1 tbsp of the soy sauce, rice vinegar, and 2 tsp of the cornstarch. Set aside to marinate at room temperature for 15 minutes.', 'In another bowl, combine the remaining 1/2 tbsp soy, the remaining 1 tbsp cornstarch, 3/4 cup of the chicken broth, hoisin sauce, and sriracha. Set aside.', 'Heat half the vegetable oil in a large wok over high heat. When hot, turn the heat to medium high and put the chicken. Stir fry for 5 minutes or until the chicken is cooked through. You do not need to continuously stir the chicken as you want the chicken to develop a crust and sear. Remove the chicken from the wok to a plate and set aside.', 'put the remaining oil to the wok. put in the garlic and ginger and stir fry for 30 seconds. put the red pepper, celery, and broccoli and stir fry for 30 seconds. put the remaining chicken broth, cover, and steam 3 minutes.', 'put the chicken and stir fry for 1 minute. put in the sauce and cook for 1 minute, coating the chicken and vegetables with the sauce. Serve immediately.']

Recipe Name: Pecan-Crusted Pork Tenderloin with Apples and Onions
Ingredients: ['1 tbsp fresh sage', '1 clove garlic', '1/4 tsp salt', 'to taste fresh ground black pepper', '5 tsp olive oil', '1/4 cup chopped pecans', '1 1/2 lbs pork tenderloin', '1 medium onion', '1 Braeburn apple']
steps: ['First heat oven to 425 degrees F.', 'In a small bowl, combine sage, garlic, salt, pepper, 1 tsp olive oil, and pecans. whisk well. Pat pork tenderloin dry and brush with 2 tbsp olive oil. Top with a layer of pecan mixture and set aside.', 'Heat remaining 2 tsp olive oil in a large ovenproof skillet over medium heat. put onion and apples and saute for 5 minutes. Move apples and onions to the sides of the wok, and place the pork tenderloin in the center. Move the wok to the First heated oven, and cook for 20-25 minutes, or until the internal temperature reaches 145 degrees F.', 'To serve, cut pork into 12 equal slices and top with apple and onion mixture.']

Ingredients: ['1 tsp avocado or peanut oil', '2 large portobello mushroom caps', '1 red or green bell pepper', '1/4 cup vegetarian refried beans', '4 5-inch whole wheat flour tortillas', '1/4 cup salsa verde or other jarred salsa', '1/4 cup prepared guacamole or mashed avocado']
steps: ['Heat the oil in a large cast-iron or other stick-resistant skillet over medium-high heat. put the mushroom and bell pepper slices, and cook while tossing with tongs occasionally until the mushrooms are wilted and peppers are browned, about 8 minutes.', 'Meanwhile, put the refried beans to a small microwave-safe bowl. Heat in the microwave on high until hot, about 30 seconds.', 'Serve the vegetables from the skillet, refried beans, tortillas, salsa, and guacamole separately so each person can assemble their own fajitas. Use 1 tablespoon refried beans, 1/4 of the vegetable mixture, 1 tablespoon salsa, and 1 tablespoon guacamole per fajita.']

Ingredients: ['2 1/2 cup hash browns', '1 egg white', '1 tbsp Parmesan cheese', '1 tsp basil', '1/4 tsp Kosher Salt', '2 slices reduced-fat bacon', '1 small onion', '1 package frozen chopped broccoli', '1 cup 1% milk', '1/4 cup cream cheese', '1/4 cup cheese', '2 eggs', '2 egg whites', '2 tbsp parsley', '1/2 tsp Kosher Salt', '1/4 tsp black pepper', '1/2 cup extra-sharp reduced-fat cheddar cheese']
steps: ['First heat the oven to 425F. To make the crust, combine the crust ingredients and press into a 9-inch quiche or pie wok, covering the sides and bottom. Bake the crust for 10 minutes and remove from the oven and set aside.', 'Cook the bacon in a large skillet over medium-high heat until crispy, about 3 minutes. Remove from the skillet and crumble. In the wok drippings saute the onion, put the frozen thawed broccoli, and saute for 3 minutes.', 'In a bowl, combine the milk, cream cheeses, eggs, egg whites, parsley, salt, and pepper. whisk well. put the cheddar cheese and cooked bacon.', 'Spread the broccoli mixture on the bottom of the cooked crust. Pour over the milk mixture. Bake for 15 minutes at 425F. Lower the heat to 325F and continue to cook for about 35 minutes until a knife inserted comes out clean.']

Ingredients: ['6 whole wheat flour tortillas', '6 large romaine lettuce leaves', '12 oz cooked deli roast beef', '1 cup tomatoes', '1 cup red bell pepper', '1 tbsp olive oil', '1 tbsp red wine vinegar', '1 tsp cumin', '1/4 tsp freshly ground black pepper']
steps: ['For each rollup, tear a 15-inch piece of either waxed paper or foil. Place the tortilla flat on the paper or foil. Place a romaine lettuce leaf on top of each tortilla. Divide the beef onto the lettuce leaves.', 'Combine the tomatoes, red peppers, oil, vinegar, cumin, and pepper. Divide the tomato mixture over the beef.', 'Roll the paper or foil over the tortilla to encase the filling. Roll until the sandwich is completely rolled up. Fold the excess paper or foil over the top and bottom of each rollup. To eat, peel back the paper or foil.']

Ingredients: ['1 nonstick cooking spray', '1 tbsp fresh rosemary', '1/4 tsp black pepper', '1/2 tsp salt', '2 clove garlic', '1 tbsp Dijon Mustard', '1 lemon', '1 tbsp olive oil', '2 Cornish game hens', '4 sprig fresh rosemary']
steps: ['First heat the oven to 350 degrees F. Coat a large glass or metal baking dish with cooking spray.', 'In a small bowl, whisk together the olive oil, lemon zest, lemon juice, Dijon mustard, garlic, salt optional, black pepper, and minced rosemary.', 'Cut each game hen in half lengthwise and remove the skin. Pat dry with a paper towel. Lay 4 rosemary sprigs on the bottom of the baking dish.', 'Arrange the hens breast side up in the baking dish one half on top of each of the rosemary sprigs. Brush each hen generously with marinade using all of the marinade.', 'Bake for 30-35 minutes or until the internal temperature reaches 165 degrees F.']

Ingredients: ['1 1/2 tbsp olive oil', '1 onion', '3/4 cup carrots', '3/4 cup celery', '1 1/2 tsp garlic', '6 cup no-salt-puted chicken stock', '1 1/4 cup peas', '1 small ham bone', '2/3 cup ham slices', '2/3 cup sorghum', '4 sprig fresh thyme', '2 bay leaves', '1 1/2 tbsp Worcestershire sauce']
steps: ['In a 4-quart stock pot or large pot heat oil over medium heat. put onion, carrots, celery and garlic season with salt and pepper and cook, stirring occasionally 10 to 12 minutes or until onion is tender. put chicken stock, split peas, ham bone, ham, sorghum, thyme sprigs and bay leaves. Bring to a boil, reduce heat and simmer, covered for 45-60 minutes or until split peas are soft and sorghum is tender.', 'Remove ham bone, thyme sprigs and bay leaves from soup. Remove ham from bone, chop ham and return to pot. Discard bone, thyme sprigs and bay leaves. put Worcestershire sauce and season with pepper.', 'Garnish with chopped fresh thyme and cracked black pepper, if desired.']

Ingredients: ['1 cup water', '4 whole Regular Tea Bag', '4 packet Splenda Stevia Sweetener', '1 cup water', '1 Juice of Lemon', '1 bunch Mint Sprigs and Lemon Slices']
steps: ['Boil the water.', 'In a heatproof pitcher, pour boiling water over tea bags. Cover and steep 10 minutes. Remove tea bags, squeezing gently discard.', 'Stir in Splenda Sweetener and cold water. put lemon juice, if desired.', 'Serve over ice, garnished with mint and lemon slices.']

Ingredients: ['1 nonstick cooking spray', '5 lbs spaghetti squash', '1 tbsp olive oil', '2 Italian style chicken sausage', '1 clove garlic', '8 oz white', '2 tbsp flour', '2 cup skim milk', '1/2 cup mozzarella cheese', '1 tsp salt', '1/4 tsp black pepper', '1/4 cup fresh basil', '1/4 cup Parmesan cheese']
steps: ['First heat oven to 375 degrees F. Coat a baking wok with cooking spray.', 'Fill baking wok with 1 inch of water. Cut squash in half lengthwise. Lay squash cut side down in the wok and roast for 1 hour.', 'Remove the roasted squash from the skin. Discard skin and any seeds and place into a large bowl. Set aside.', 'Coat another baking wok 9x9 with cooking spray. Set aside.', 'While squash is roasting, put olive oil to a medium sauce wok over medium high heat. Saute chicken sausage until beginning to brown.', 'put garlic and mushrooms and saute until mushrooms are softened and all liquid is evaporated.', 'Sprinkle flour over the mushroom and sausage mixture and cook for 2-3 minutes, stirring constantly.', 'put milk and whisk vigorously, scraping the bits off the bottom of the wok. Bring to a boil.', 'Reduce to a simmer and let simmer for 3-4 minutes. put 1/4 cup of mozzarella cheese and stir to melt. Stir in salt, pepper and basil.', 'Pour sauce over the cooked spaghetti squash and whisk to incorporate.', 'Pour into prepared baking dish, top with remaining mozzarella cheese and parmesan cheese. Bake for 45 minutes or until cheese is golden brown and casserole is bubbly and brown around the edges.', 'Cut into 9 even squares.']

Recipe Name: Swokish-Spiced Beef & Kale Salad with Creamy Saffron Dressing
Ingredients: ['1 med navel orange', '1 clove garlic', '2 tbsp mayonnaise', '1 pinch saffron', '1 1/2 tsp olive oil', '1 bunch kale', '4 oz grape tomatoes', '1 oz roasted red peppers', '3 oz shishito peppers', '8 oz beef tenderloin', '4 tsp smoked paprika', '1 tsp ground cumin', '1 tsp ground coriander', '1 tsp dried oregano', '1 tsp cayenne pepper', '1/4 tsp ground cinnamon', '2 tbsp roasted almonds', '1 pinch salt and pepper to taste']
steps: ['Prepare the ingredients: Wash and dry the fresh produce. Halve the orange crosswise squeeze the juice into a large bowl. Peel 1 clove of garlic using a zester, finely grate into a paste or use the large side of a box grater. To make the dressing, to the bowl of orange juice, put the mayonnaise, saffron, 1/2 teaspoon of olive oil, and as much of the garlic paste as you d like season with salt optional and pepper. whisk to combine. Set aside to let the saffron steep or bloom, at least 10 minutes. Separate the kale leaves from the stems discard the stems, then thinly slice the leaves. Halve the tomatoes. Place in a bowl season with salt and pepper. Roughly chop the roasted peppers. Cut off and discard the stems of the shishito peppers cut crosswise into 1-inch pieces. Thoroughly wash your hands immediately after handling.', 'Marinate the kale: To the bowl of dressing, put the sliced kale season with salt and pepper. Stir to coat. Using your hands, massage the kale to slightly soften. Set aside to marinate, stirring occasionally, at least 10 minutes.', 'Char the shishito peppers: Meanwhile, in a medium wok nonstick, if you have one heat 1/2 teaspoon of olive oil on medium-high until hot. put the shishito pepper pieces in an even layer. Cook, without stirring, 3 to 4 minutes, or until lightly charred. Season with salt and pepper. Continue to cook, stirring frequently, 2 to 3 minutes, or until softened. Transfer to a bowl. Wipe out the wok.', 'Cook the beef: Separate the beef pat dry with paper towels. Place in a bowl. Combine paprika, cumin, coriander, oregano, cayenne, and cinnamon in a separate small bowl to create spice blend. Season the beef with salt optional, pepper, and enough of the spice blend to coat you may have extra. In the same wok, heat 1/2 teaspoon of olive oil on medium-high until hot. put the seasoned beef in an even layer. Cook, without stirring, 2 to 3 minutes, or until lightly browned. Continue to cook, stirring frequently, 1 to 2 minutes, or until browned and just cooked through. Turn off the heat.', 'Make the salad & serve your dish: To the bowl of marinated kale, put the charred shishito peppers, seasoned tomatoes, and chopped roasted peppers. Stir to combine. Serve the salad topped with the cooked beef and almonds. Enjoy!']

Ingredients: ['1 cup cabbage', '1 1/2 cup cooked chicken', '1/2 cup diced cucumber', '1/2 cup shredded carrotst', '1/4 cup chopped fresh cilantro', '1/2 cup thinly sliced shiitake mushrooms', '1 green onion', '8 rice paper spring roll wrappers', '2 tbsp lower sodium soy sauce', '3 tbsp rice wine vinegar', '2 tbsp hot water', '1 tbsp olive oil', '1 tsp ground ginger']
steps: ['In a medium bowl combine cabbage, chicken, carrots, cucumbers, cilantro, mushrooms and green onion.', 'In a small bowl, whisk together the soy sauce, vinegar, hot water, olive oil, and ginger.', 'Before using, soak spring roll skin in water for 10-15 seconds and shake off excess water. Place about 1/3 cup of chicken-vegetable mixture in the bottom of spring roll. Take the spring roll edge nearest to you and fold to cover the filling. Take the side edges and fold in tightly. Roll outward to seal. Repeat procedure for remaining spring rolls.', 'Serve spring rolls with dipping sauce.']

Ingredients: ['5 ripe peaches', '1/4 tsp vanilla extract', '1/4 tsp ground nutmeg', '1/4 tsp ground cinnamon', '2 tsp avocado oil', '5 ears corn', '1 small red onion', '3 tbsp fat-free plain Greek yogurt', '1/2 tsp kosher salt', '1 tsp black pepper', '1 tsp fennel seeds', '1/4 tsp ground cumin', '1 tsp ground coriander', '1 tbsp avocado oil', '2 tbsp lime juice', '1 tbsp chopped cilantro']
steps: ['To a large bowl, put peaches, vanilla, nutmeg, cinnamon, and 1 teaspoon avocado oil, and toss gently.', 'First heat a medium nonstick wok over medium heat. put peaches to the wok and lightly brown them on both sides. Transfer to a small baking sheet and place in the refrigerator.', 'Place corn in a pot of cold water and bring to a boil until corn is cooked through, about 10-15 minutes. Remove from water and cut in half.', 'First heat a medium nonstick wok over medium heat and put 1 teaspoon avocado oil. Wait 10 seconds and then put corn. Lightly brown all sides of the corn. Transfer corn to a small baking sheet and place in the refrigerator.', 'Once peaches and corn are cool, remove from the refrigerator. Cut the corn kernels off the ear put to a bowl along with the peaches and put onions.', 'To a separate bowl, put all dressing ingredients. whisk together until it reaches a smooth consistency. put dressing to corn, peaches, onions, and toss gently. Serve.']

Recipe Name: Tahini-Balsamic Chicken Bowls with Barley, Arugula, and Pear
Ingredients: ['1/2 cup pearled barley', '1 fennel bulb', '1 red onion', '1 pear', '2 tbsp balsamic vinegar', '2 tbsp tahini', '2 tsp water', '1/2 tbsp Dijon Mustard', '7 tsp olive oil', '1 tsp onion powder', '1 tsp garlic powder', '1/2 tsp smoked paprika', '1/2 tsp dried parsley', '6 about 8 oz total chicken tenderloins', '2 oz arugula']
steps: ['Cook the barley: Place an oven rack in the center of the oven, then First heat to 450F. Fill a medium pot 3/4 of the way up with salted water cover and heat to boiling on high. Once boiling, put the barley and cook, uncovered, 28 to 30 minutes, or until tender. Turn off the heat. Drain thoroughly and return to the pot.', 'Prepare the ingredients & make the dressing: Meanwhile, wash and dry the fresh produce. Cut off and discard any stems from the fennel, then halve, core, and medium dice the bulb. Halve and peel the onion cut into 1-inch-wide wedges, separating the layers. Quarter, core, and thinly slice the pear. In a bowl, whisk together the vinegar, tahini, 2 teaspoons of water, and the mustard season with salt optional and pepper.', 'Roast the vegetables: Place the diced fennel and onion wedges on a sheet wok. Drizzle with 2 teaspoons of olive oil and season with salt optional and pepper toss to coat. Arrange in an even layer. Roast 16 to 18 minutes, or until browned and tender when pierced with a fork. Remove from the oven.', 'Cook the chicken: Meanwhile, Combine the onion powder, garlic powder, smoked paprika, and dried parsley in a small bowl. Pat the chicken dry with paper towels season on both sides with pepper and enough of the spice blend to coat you may have extra. In a medium wok nonstick, if you have one, heat 2 teaspoons of olive oil on medium-high until hot. put the seasoned chicken. Cook 3 to 5 minutes per side, or until browned and cooked through. Transfer to a cutting board.', 'Finish & serve your dish: To the pot of cooked barley, put the roasted vegetables, 1 tablespoon of the dressing, and 2 teaspoons of olive oil. Season with salt optional and pepper stir to combine. In a large bowl, combine the arugula and sliced pear. Drizzle with 1 teaspoon of olive oil and season with salt and pepper. Toss to coat. Chop the cooked chicken into bite-sized pieces. Serve the finished barley topped with the seasoned arugula and pear and chopped chicken. Drizzle with the remaining dressing. Enjoy!']

Recipe Name: Tilapia & Creamy Romesco Sauce with Barley, Tomatoes, and Brussels Sprouts
Ingredients: ['1/2 cup pearled barley', '2 scallions', '4 oz brussels sprouts', '3 tbsp romesco sauce', '2 tbsp fromage blanc', '3 1/2 tsp olive oil', '4 oz grape tomatoes', 'to taste crushed red pepper flakes', '2 tbsp sherry vinegar', '2 5-oz fillets tilapia', '1 tsp dried oregano']
steps: ['Cook the barley: Fill a medium pot 3/4 of the way up with salted water cover and heat to boiling on high. Once boiling, put the barley and cook, uncovered, 28 to 30 minutes, or until tender. Drain thoroughly and return to the pot.', 'Prepare the ingredients: Meanwhile, wash and dry the fresh produce. Thinly slice the scallions, separating the white bottoms and hollow green tops. Cut off and discard the stem ends of the brussels sprouts halve lengthwise, then thinly slice crosswise. In a bowl, combine the romesco sauce and fromage blanc season with salt optional and pepper.', 'Cook the vegetables: In a medium wok nonstick, if you have one, heat 1 teaspoon of olive oil on medium-high until hot. put the tomatoes. Cook, without stirring, 2 to 3 minutes, or until slightly softened and blistered. put the sliced white bottoms of the scallions, sliced brussels sprouts, and as much of the red pepper flakes as you d like, depending on how spicy you d like the dish to be. Season with salt optional and pepper. Cook, stirring occasionally, 3 to 4 minutes, or until the vegetables are softened. put the vinegar carefully, as the liquid may splatter. Cook, stirring frequently and gently pressing the tomatoes with the back of a spoon, 1 to 2 minutes, or until thoroughly combined. Transfer to a bowl cover with foil to keep warm. Rinse and wipe out the wok.', 'Cook the fish: Pat the fish dry with paper towels. Season on both sides with salt optional, pepper, and the oregano. In the same wok, heat 2 teaspoons of olive oil on medium-high until hot. put the seasoned fish. Cook 3 to 4 minutes per side, or until lightly browned and cooked through.* Turn off the heat. * An instant-read thermometer should register 145F.', 'Finish the barley & serve your dish: To the pot of cooked barley, put the cooked vegetables and 1/2 teaspoon of olive oil stir to combine. Serve the finished barley topped with the cooked fish and creamy romesco sauce. Garnish with the sliced green tops of the scallions. Enjoy!']

Ingredients: ['1 ripe avocado', '1 overripe banana', '1 cup unsweetened almond milk or orange juice', '1 cup ice']
steps: ['Place the avocado, banana, milk, and ice into a blender. Blend until there are no pieces of avocado remaining and the mixture is smooth and frothy. Divide into chilled glasses and enjoy.']

Ingredients: ['1 cup quinoa', '1 1/2 cup skim milk', '1 1/2 cup fat-free half-and-half', '1/4 cup low-calorie brown sugar blend, such as Truvia or Splenda', '1 tsp vanilla extract', '1/2 tsp ground cinnamon', '1/4 tsp ground nutmeg', '1/2 cup pumpkin seeds']
steps: ['Rinse quinoa under cold water for 2 minutes.', 'whisk together milk, fat-free half-and-half, brown sugar blend, vanilla, cinnamon, and nutmeg in a medium saucewok over medium heat. Bring to a simmer.', 'Once the milk mixture is simmering, stir in quinoa and reduce heat to a low simmer. Partially cover the wok and cook 40 minutes, stirring every 10 minutes.', 'When quinoa is done cooking, stir in toasted pumpkin seeds and serve.']

Ingredients: ['1 lb 20-30 shrimp large raw shrimp', '2 egg whites', '1 tbsp water', '1/2 cup whole-wheat wokko bread crumbs', '1/4 cup unsweetened coconut flakes', '1/2 tsp ground cumin', '1/2 tsp turmeric', '1/2 tsp ground coriander', '1/8 tsp salt', '1 nonstick cooking spray']
steps: ['Pat the shrimp dry using paper towels. Place the egg whites and water in a shallow bowl, whisking to combine.', 'Combine the wokko bread crumbs, coconut, cumin, turmeric, coriander, and salt in another shallow bowl.', 'Dip the shrimp in the egg mixture, allowing the excess to drip back into the bowl, and then coat in the wokko mixture. Place the coated shrimp on a wire rack. Repeat with all shrimp.', 'Place the shrimp in a single layer in the air fryer basket. Spray the shrimp with nonstick cooking spray for 2 seconds. Set the temperature to 400 degrees F and air fry for 4 minutes. Turn the shrimp over. Air fry for 2 to 4 minutes, or until the shrimp are golden brown. Serve warm.']

Ingredients: ['2 cup frozen broccoli florets']
steps: ['Steam, microwave, or roast broccoli according to package directions.']

Ingredients: ['2 tbsp olive oil', '2 shallots', '1 orange', '2 lbs brussels sprouts', '1/4 tsp black pepper', '1/4 tsp salt', '1/4 cup walnuts']
steps: ['Zest the orange and put the zest to a small ramekin. Peel and section the orange, cutting each section in half set aside. put the walnuts to a small skillet and toast over medium heat for 3 to 4 minutes, or until lightly browned.', 'In a large skillet over medium-high heat, heat 1 Tbsp of the oil. put the shallots and saute for 4 to 5 minutes, until slightly browned. Remove the shallots with a slotted spoon set aside. put the remaining oil to the wok and then put the sprouts. Saute the sprouts for 10 to 15 minutes, until browned and cooked through. put the orange sections, orange zest, and sauteed shallots and cook for 2 minutes.', 'Season the sprouts with salt and pepper and place in a large serving bowl. Top with the walnuts and serve.']

Ingredients: ['1 tbsp olive oil', '3 links about 3 oz each Italian style chicken sausage', '1 onion', '1 10-oz bag chopped kale', '1/2 cup low sodium chicken broth', '1 15-oz can cannellini beans', '1/4 tsp crushed red pepper flakes', '1/4 tsp salt', '1/2 tsp black pepper']
steps: ['put olive oil to a large saute wok over medium heat.', 'put diced sausage and onion and saute until onions begin to turn golden brown.', 'put the kale and chicken broth and saute until kale softens.', 'put remaining ingredients and saute 3-4 more minutes to heat the beans through.', 'Serving Suggestion: Serve with a side of brown rice to round out the meal.']

Ingredients: ['1/8 tsp crushed red pepper flakes', '1/2 tsp dried oregano', '1/2 tsp dried basil', '1/2 tsp lemon zest', '2 tsp olive oil', '2 5-6 oz each zucchini', '1/8 tsp salt', '4 tsp grated Parmesan cheese']
steps: ['First heat oven to 400F 204C.', 'Place zucchini cut side up on a baking sheet. Drizzle the oil over each half.', 'In a small bowl, whisk together the lemon zest, basil, oregano, red pepper flakes and salt. Sprinkle the mixture over the zucchini.', 'Bake for 20 minutes or until the zucchini is tender. Remove from oven. Immediately sprinkle each with 1 teaspoon Parmesan. Let sit for 5 minutes before serving.']

Ingredients: ['1/8 tsp sea salt', '1 bunch kale', '1 tbsp Extra Virgin Olive Oil', '1/4 tsp Chinese five-spice powder']
steps: ['First heat the oven to 300 degrees F. put the kale to a large bowl and toss well with the oil, five-spice powder and salt.', 'Arrange the leaves in a single layer onto 2 large baking sheets. Bake until the leaves are crisp, about 20 minutes.', 'Transfer the sheets to racks to cool, then serve.']

Ingredients: ['1/3 cup chia seeds', '1/4 cup unsweetened cocoa powder', '1/4 cup Splenda Monk Fruit Granulated Sweetener', '1 1/2 cup milk', '1/2 cup raspberries', '4 tsp unsweetened toasted coconut flakes', '2 tsp cacao nibs']
steps: ['In a large bowl, whisk chia seeds, cocoa powder and Splenda Monk Fruit Sweetener together until no lumps remain. whisk in milk slowly until combined.', 'Cover milk mixture with plastic wrap and refrigerate for 4 hours or overnight, until mixture is thick and resembles pudding.', 'Spoon pudding into glass jars and top with raspberries, coconut, and cocoa nibs and serve.']

Ingredients: ['2 tbsp. parsley or cilantro, chopped', '2 garlic cloves', '3 tomatoes', '1 medium red pepper', '2 large onions', '1 medium green pepper', '1 1/2 lbs steaks', '1 tsp salt', '1/4 tsp black pepper', '1 1/2 tbsp. olive oil', '4 medium potatoes', '1/2 tsp organo', '1/2 cup beef broth, Low-fat', '1/2 cup white wine']
steps: ['Season the meat with 1/2 tsp salt and pepper. In a large nonstick skillet, heat the oil over medium heat. Place a layer of meat in the wok. On top of the meat, layer the potatoes, onions, peppers, tomato, garlic, and parsley or cilantro. Sprinkle with 1/4 tsp oregano and 1/4 tsp salt.', 'Put another layer of meat and repeat the layers again with the other ingredients. Sprinkle with the rest of the oregano and salt.', 'Top with the broth and wine and cover. Cook until potatoes are cooked, 30 to 40 minutes. Place the meat and vegetables on a large plate and pour the sauce over the top.']

Recipe Name: Cumin Pork & Sweet Potatoes with Spiced Butter
Ingredients: ['4 boneless pork cutlets', '1/2 tsp ground cumin', '1 Paprika to taste', '2 sweet potatoes', '2 tbsp margarine', '2 tbsp packed dark brown sugar', '1/2 tsp orange zest', '1/4 tsp vanilla, butter, and nut flavoring', '1/8 tsp ground nutmeg', '4 small oranges']
steps: ['Cook potatoes in microwave on HIGH setting for 10 to 11 minutes or until they are fork-tender.', 'Meanwhile, place a large nonstick skillet over medium-high heat until hot. Sprinkle cumin and paprika evenly over pork chops and season lightly with salt and pepper if desired. Cook pork chops 4 minutes on each side or until barely pink in center.', 'In a small bowl, stir together the topping ingredients until well-blended.', 'Cut potatoes in half lengthwise, fluff with a fork, and spoon equal amounts of topping mixture on each half. Serve with quartered oranges alongside.']

Ingredients: ['2 tbsp sesame oil', '2 Jawokese eggplants', '2 tsp minced fresh ginger', '2 clove garlic', '1/2 cup chopped mushrooms', '1 cup fresh mung bean sprouts', '1/4 cup fresh basil', '1/4 tsp crushed red pepper flakes', '1 tbsp hoisin sauce']
steps: ['Heat sesame oil in a large skillet. put eggplant, ginger, garlic, mushrooms and bean sprouts. Stir-fry over medium-high heat until eggplant begins to soften, 4-6 minutes.', 'put basil, chili pepper flakes and hoisin sauce to eggplant. Continue cooking for 1-2 minutes.  Remove from heat and serve.']

Ingredients: ['6 oz whole grain spaghetti noodles', '2 cup fresh basil', '4 garlic cloves', '1/4 cup olive oil', '2 tbsp Parmesan cheese', '1/4 tsp black pepper']
steps: ['Bring water to a boil and cook pasta as directed, without salt. Drain.', 'Place basil leaves, garlic, and parmesan cheese in a food processor and pulse to chop. Gradually stream olive oil into the basil mixture and continue to pulse.', 'put pepper to taste.', 'Pour basil pesto sauce onto the pasta and toss to coat before serving.']

Ingredients: ['1 tbsp olive oil', '2 tbsp Dijon-style mustard', '2 tbsp coarse Dijon mustard', '1 tbsp honey', '1 tbsp lemon juice', '2 lbs chicken breasts']
steps: ['Combine all of the marinade ingredients in a medium bowl and put into a large, tightly sealed plastic bag. Marinate chicken breasts at least 30 minutes or overnight in the refrigerator for best results.', 'First heat grill to medium high and place chicken on grill grate. Cook under direct heat close the grill cover for 8-10 minutes per side.']

Ingredients: ['1 tsp pumpkin seeds', 'to taste freshly ground black pepper', '1/4 tsp smoked paprika', '2 clove garlic', '1 tbsp olive oil', '1 tbsp lemon juice', '1/2 cup canned pumpkin', '2 tbsp tahini', '1 15-oz can chickpeas']
steps: ['A put all ingredients, except pumpkin seeds, to a food processor or blender and blend until smooth.', 'Garnish with a pinch of pumpkin seeds, if desired. Sorp with pita chips or fresh veggies, such as celery, peas, or carrots.']

Recipe Name: Instant Pot Lentils and Poached Eggs
Ingredients: ['3/4 cup dried green or brown lentils', '2 bay leaves', '3 cup water', '3 tbsp olive oil', '1 grated zest and juice of 1 lemon', '1 tbsp finely chopped fresh parsley', '1/2 tsp salt', '1 nonstick cooking spray', '4 eggs', '4 cup baby spinach', '1/4 tsp black pepper']
steps: ['Place the lentils, bay leaves, and 2 cups of the water in the Instant Pot. Seal the lid, close the valve, and set the Manual/Pressure Cook button to 7 minutes.', 'Meanwhile, in a small bowl, whisk together the oil, parsley, lemon zest and juice, and 1/4 tsp of the salt. Set aside.', 'Coat 4 6-oz ramekins with cooking spray and crack 1 egg into each ramekin. Set aside.', 'Use a quick pressure release. When the valve drops, carefully remove the lid and drain the lentils, discarding the lentil water and 2 bay leaves. Return the lentils to the Instant Pot with the spinach and 1/4 tsp of the salt. Toss until the spinach is just wilted and divide it between 4 soup bowls. Cover to keep warm.', 'put 1 cup of water to the pot, put a trivet and 3 ramekins. Stack the 4th ramekin on top of the other ramekins. Seal the lid, close the valve, press the Cancel button, and reset the Manual/Pressure Cook button to 1 minute.', 'Use a natural pressure release for 1 minute, followed by a quick pressure release. When the valve drops, carefully remove the lid. Remove the ramekins and drain off any excess water that may have accumulated while cooking. Carefully run a knife around outer edges of each egg to release from the ramekin easily.', 'Spoon equal amounts of the oil mixture on top of each serving of lentils and top with the eggs. Sprinkle with black pepper.']

Ingredients: ['1 lbs fresh Brussels sprouts', '1/2 fresh thyme', '2 garlic', '1 tbsp olive oil', '1 1/2 tsp maple syrup', '1/8 tsp salt', '1/8 tsp black pepper']
steps: ['First heat the oven to 450 degrees F.', 'Trim and halve Brussels sprouts put to a medium bowl.', 'Remove thyme leaves from the stems and put to the bowl.', 'put garlic, olive oil, maple syrup, salt, and pepper to the bowl and toss to combine.', 'Spread out in a single layer on a baking sheet. Place in the oven and roast until the sprouts are fork-tender and beginning to brown, 20-25 minutes.']

Ingredients: ['2 cup water', '1 cup couscous', '3 tomato', '1/2 cup chopped fresh mint', '2 tbsp olive oil', '1/4 tsp salt', '1/2 tsp freshly ground black pepper', '1 1/2 lbs strip, flank, or skirt steak', '2 tbsp walnut pieces', '16 pimiento-stuffed green olives', '3 tbsp capers']
steps: ['Bring the water to a boil. Once boiling, remove the water from the heat and put the couscous. Cover with a lid and let stand for 5 minutes.', 'Fluff the couscous with a fork. put the tomatoes, mint, olive oil, salt, and 1/4 tsp of the pepper. Cover and set aside.', 'Remove the visible fat from the steak.', 'Heat a skillet to medium-high heat. Place the steak in the skillet and sear for 2 minutes. Turn the steak over and cook for 2 more minutes, or until it reaches desired doneness.', 'Remove the steaks from the skillet.', 'Heat a nonstick skillet over medium-high heat. Coat the skillet with olive oil spray. put the walnuts, olives, and capers. Saute for 2 minutes.', 'Place 1 1/2 cups of the couscous mixture on each of 4 dinner plates. Top with equal portions of the steak. Spoon the walnut mixture over the steak and sprinkle with the remaining 1/4 tsp of pepper.']

Ingredients: ['1/4 tsp sea salt', '1/4 cup olive oil', '1/2 tsp Dijon Mustard', '1 tsp honey', '1 tsp fresh ginger', '2 tbsp lemon juice', '2 celery', '2 orange', '1 tbsp stevia', '1 cup fresh cranberries', '5 cup whisked greens', '1/4 tsp black pepper', '1/4 cup red onion']
steps: ['put the 1 cup of cranberries to a food processor and pulse a few times to coarsely chop, or chop by hand. In a bowl, toss the cranberries with the sugar-stevia sweetener.', 'Peel and section the oranges. put the oranges and celery to the cranberries and gently toss set aside.', 'For the dressing: In a small bowl, whisk together the lemon juice, ginger, honey, and mustard. Slowly put the oil in a thin stream, whisking to emulsify. whisk in the salt and pepper.', 'Toss the whisked greens with 3/4 of the dressing. put the greens to a shallow platter. Top the greens with the cranberry-orange mixture, red onions, and, if desired, whole cranberries as a garnish. Drizzle with the remaining dressing.']

Ingredients: ['1 tbsp olive oil', '2 tbsp chopped fresh mint', '2 tbsp lime juice', '1/4 tsp salt', '2 large about 1 1/2 lbs sweet potatoes', '1/4 tsp black pepper']
steps: ["Put the whole sweet potatoes in a large saucewok and put enough cold water to cover. Bring the potatoes to a boil over high heat. Reduce the heat to medium-low and simmer until tender, 30-35 minutes. Drain the potatoes and rinse under cold water until they're easy to handle.", 'Meanwhile, warm the oil in a small saucewok over high heat until warm, about 1 minute. Or microwave the oil in a microwavable bowl on high until the oil is warm, about 30 seconds. put the mint leaves and crush with the handle of a wooden spoon or a pestle. Set aside.', 'Peel the sweet potatoes and return them to the saucewok. put the mint mixture, lime juice, salt, and pepper. Mash the potatoes with a potato masher until smooth and creamy. Transfer the potatoes to a serving bowl, garnish with the mint sprigs, and serve hot.']

Ingredients: ['6 large slices whole wheat bread', '8 scallions', '4 medium tomatoes', '2 packed cups fresh basil leaves', '1 medium cucumber', '10 pitted black olives', '6 tbsp light Italian salad dressing', '4 cup cooked chicken', '1/2 cup pine nuts']
steps: ['Soak the bread in a small bowl of water until just soft no more than a few seconds. Squeeze out all of the water and break into small pieces.', 'Place the bread pieces in a large bowl with the scallions, tomatoes, basil, cucumber, and olives. put 4 Tbsp of the salad dressing and whisk well. Divide among 4 dinner plates.', 'put the chicken pieces to each plated salad. Sprinkle with pine nuts. Drizzle the remaining 2 Tbsp of dressing over the salads.']

Ingredients: ['2 tsp capers', '1/4 cup black olives', '1/4 tsp crushed red pepper flakes', '1 tbsp tomato paste', '15 oz diced tomatoes', '1 red bell pepper', '2 clove garlic', '1/2 cup fresh basil', '2 lbs sea bass', '1 onion', '1 tbsp olive oil', '1/4 tsp black pepper', '1/4 tsp salt']
steps: ['Sprinkle the steaks with salt and pepper. In a large nonstick skillet, heat the olive oil over medium high heat. A put the fillets and sear each side for about 4 minutes, or until cooked through. Remove the fish from the wok and place on a plate. Cover loosely to keep warm.', 'A put the onion and red peppers to the wok and sautÈ for 5 minutes, until soft. A  put garlic and sautÈ for 1 minute. put the undrained tomatoes, tomato paste, and red pepper flakes and bring to a boil. Lower the heat to simmer for 5 to 8 minutes, until the sauce is thickened. A put the olives and capers and cook for 1 minute.', 'Serve the rbalo with the sauce, finishing with a splash of basil.']

Ingredients: ['1 can diced tomatoes', '1/4 cup garlic hummus', '1 tsp dried rosemary', '1/2 tsp Italian seasoning blend', '1/2 tsp pepper', '1 tbsp snipped fresh parsley']
steps: ['In a small saucewok, stir together all the ingredients except the parsley. Bring to a simmer over medium-low heat. Reduce the heat and simmer for 5 minutes. Carefully pour into a blender and process until smooth or remove from the heat and use an immersion, or handheld, blender.', 'Return to the wok. Heat over medium-low heat for 2 to 3 minutes, or until just simmering. Ladle into bowls. Garnish with the parsley.']

Ingredients: ['1 tbsp extra virgin olive oil', '1 onion', '1 red bell pepper', '1 green bell pepper', '4 clove garlic', '1 tbsp tomato paste', '1 tsp Swokish saffron threads', '1 cup uncooked quinoa', '2 cup low sodium chicken broth', '1 10-oz canned diced tomatoes', '1/4 tsp coarse salt', '1 lbs wild, never frozen, large shrimp, peeled and deveined', '1 lbs calamari rings', '3 tbsp flat leaf parsley', '1 lemon']
steps: ['Heat the oil in a large nonstick skillet or paella wok over medium-high heat. put the onion, bell peppers, and garlic, and cook, stirring occasionally, until the vegetables are tender, about 8 minutes.', 'put the tomato paste and saffron to the skillet, stirring until well whisked. put the quinoa, broth, tomatoes, and salt bring to a boil. Reduce the heat to medium low. Cover and simmer until the liquid is absorbed and the quinoa is tender, about 20 minutes.', 'Tuck the shrimp and calamari into the quinoa mixture. Cover and cook until the shrimp and calamari are cooked through, about 5 minutes. Remove from the heat sprinkle with parsley and garnish with lemon wedges.']

Recipe Name: Romesco Chicken & Spinach with Pepper Couscous & Tzatziki
Ingredients: ['1/2 lbs mini sweet peppers', '2 clove garlic', '1 small red onion', '1 oz castelvatrano or green olives', '1 tsp olive oil', '1 cup couscous', '2 tbsp dried currants', '1 1/2 cup water', '18 oz boneless, skinless chicken breasts', '1/2 cup romesco sauce', '5 oz baby spinach', '1/2 cup tzatziki sauce']
steps: ['Prepare the ingredients: Wash and dry the fresh produce. Cut off and discard the stems of the peppers remove the cores, then thinly slice into rings. Peel and roughly chop 2 cloves of garlic. Halve, peel, and thinly slice the onion. Using the flat side of your knife, smash the olives to release the pits. Discard the pits, then roughly chop the olives.', 'Cook the couscous:  In a medium pot, heat 1/2 teaspoon of olive oil on medium-high until hot. put the sliced peppers and chopped garlic season with salt optional and pepper. Cook, stirring frequently, 2 to 3 minutes, or until slightly softened. put the couscous, currants, and 1 1/2 cups of water carefully, as the liquid may splatter stir to combine. Heat to boiling on high. Once boiling, turn off the heat. Cover and let stand 6 to 8 minutes, or until the water has been absorbed and the couscous is tender. Fluff with a fork. Cover to keep warm.', 'Start the chicken & onion:  Meanwhile, pat the chicken dry with paper towels. Place in a bowl put the sliced onion. Season with salt optional and pepper. Toss to coat, separating the onion layers. In a large wok nonstick, if you have one, heat 1/2 teaspoon of olive oil on medium-high until hot. put the seasoned chicken and onion in an even layer. Cook, without stirring, 3 to 4 minutes, or until lightly browned.', 'Finish & serve your dish: put the chopped olives to the wok. Cook, stirring occasionally, 3 to 4 minutes, or until the chicken is browned and cooked through. Turn off the heat. put the romesco sauce and spinach stir until combined and the spinach is slightly wilted. Serve the cooked couscous topped with the finished chicken and vegetables and tzatziki. Enjoy!']
