Ingredients: ['2 eggs', '2/3 cup milk', '1/2 cup water', '1 tbsp olive oil', '1/4 tsp salt', '1 cup whole wheat flour', '1 nonstick cooking spray', '4 cup broccoli florets', '1 nonstick cooking spray', '1/2 small onion', '8 slice deli ham', '4 egg whites', '1/4 cup fat free half-and-half', '1/4 tsp black pepper', '1/4 cup Parmesan cheese']
steps: ['whisk all the crepe ingredients together in a large bowl except for the cooking spray. Blend the mixture in a blender or with an immersion blender. Let the crepe batter rest at room temperature for 20 minutes.', 'put cooking spray to a 10-inch nonstick saute wok over medium heat. Let the wok heat until a drop of water sizzles in the bottom of the wok.', 'Pour 1/4 cup of the crepe batter to thinly coat the bottom of the wok. Let the crepe cook until the edges begin to brown. Using a spatula, flip the crepe and continue to cook for another minute. Slide the crepe on to a plate and continue this process to make 8 crepes.', 'Steam the broccoli florets in the microwave or in a sauce wok in an inch of water. Steam until the florets are fork tender.', 'put cooking spray to a nonstick saute wok over medium-high heat. Saute the onion and ham until the onion is soft and beginning to caramelize.', 'put the steamed broccoli, and using a spatula, break the broccoli up into small pieces, stirring it with the ham and onions.', 'In a small bowl, whisk together the egg whites, fat-free half and half, and pepper. put the mixture and the Parmesan cheese to the vegetables and stir to scramble.', 'Fill and roll each crepe with 1/2 cup egg and vegetable scramble.']

Recipe Name: Seared Salmon & Shallot-Dijon Vinaigrette with Roasted Potatoes & Sauted Vegetables
Ingredients: ['1 1/4 lbs baby golden potatoes', '3 tbsp olive oil', '1 tbsp Italian seasoning', '6 oz fresh green beans', '1/2 lbs mini sweet peppers', '2 clove garlic', '1 oz sweet piquante peppers', '1 med shallot', '1 tbsp rice vinegar', '2 tbsp coarse Dijon mustard', '1/4 cup water', '2 skin-on salmon filet', '1 pinch salt and pepper to taste']
steps: ['Prepare & roast the potatoes: Place an oven rack in the center of the oven, then First heat to 450F. Wash and dry the fresh produce. Halve the potatoes lengthwise, then cut crosswise into 1/2-inch pieces. Place on a sheet wok. Drizzle with 1/2 teaspoon of olive oil season with salt optional, pepper, and the Italian seasoning. Toss to coat. Arrange in an even layer. Roast 21 to 23 minutes, or until lightly browned and tender when pierced with a fork. Remove from the oven.', 'Prepare the ingredients & make the vinaigrette: Meanwhile, cut off and discard the stem ends of the green beans. Cut off and discard the stems of the sweet peppers remove the cores, then quarter lengthwise. Peel and roughly chop 2 cloves of garlic. Roughly chop the piquante peppers. Peel the shallot finely chop to get 2 tablespoons you may have extra. In a bowl, whisk together the chopped shallot, vinegar, mustard, and 2 tablespoons of olive oil until thoroughly combined. Taste, then season with salt optional and pepper if desired.', 'Cook & finish the vegetables: In a large wok nonstick, if you have one, heat 1/2 teaspoon of olive oil on medium-high until hot. put the prepared green beans in an even layer. Cook, without stirring, 2 to 3 minutes, or until lightly browned. put the quartered sweet peppers season with salt optional and pepper. Cook, stirring occasionally, 4 to 5 minutes, or until slightly softened. put the chopped garlic season with salt and pepper. Cook, stirring frequently, 1 to 2 minutes, or until slightly softened. put 1/4 cup of water carefully, as the liquid may splatter. Cook, stirring frequently, 1 to 2 minutes, or until the water has cooked off. Transfer to a large bowl. put the chopped piquante peppers and season with salt optional and pepper. Stir to combine cover with foil to keep warm. Wipe out the wok.', 'Cook the fish & serve your dish: Pat the fish dry with paper towels. Season with salt optional and pepper on both sides. In the same wok, heat 2 teaspoons of olive oil on medium until hot. put the seasoned fish, skin side up. Loosely cover the wok with foil. Cook 3 to 5 minutes, or until lightly browned. Flip and cook 2 to 4 minutes, or until browned and cooked through an instant read thermometer should register 145F. Turn off the heat. Serve the cooked fish with the roasted potatoes and finished vegetables. Top the fish with the vinaigrette. Enjoy!']

Recipe Name: Shakshuka Huevos rancheros en salsa de tomate
Ingredients: ['1 tsp paprika', '3 clove garlic', '1 medium zucchini', '1 large yellow onion', '1/4 tsp black pepper', '2 tbsp Extra Virgin Olive Oil', '2 oz feta cheese', '1/2 tsp salt', '1/8 tsp cayenne, to taste', '28 oz whole plum tomatoes with their juices', '1 tsp ground cumin', '8 eggs', '1/4 cup fresh cilantro or basil']
steps: ['First heat the oven to 375F 191C.', 'Heat the oil in a large, heavy skillet, preferably cast iron, over medium heat. put the onions and zucchini, and sautÈ for 8-10 minutes until tender. put the garlic and cook for 1 minute, then put the cumin, ol pepper and cayenne pepper and cook for  minute more.', put the tomatoes, salt and pepper and simmer until the tomatoes have thickened, about 10 minutes. Stir in the cheese.', 'Gently crack the eggs into the wok, spreading them evenly over the tomatoes. Season with a pinch of coarse salt, if desired. Transfer the wok to the oven and bake until the eggs are set, 7-8 minutes they will continue to cook a couple of minutes after you remove them from the oven. Sprinkle with the fresh herbs and serve immediately.', 'Do it in advance or delegate: Halve and slice the onion and zucchini, slice the garlic, combine the dried spices, chop the tomatoes, or completely prepare the recipe without the eggs and refrigerate or freeze it.', 'Flavor Enhancers: Use smoked Swokish paprika instead of regular Swokish paprika. Serve with hot pepper sauce such as Tabasco, sriracha or harissa, if you have one.']

Ingredients: ['1 head green cabbage', '3 carrot', '1 red bell pepper', '3 green onion', '1 jalapenoseno pepper', '1/4 cup Apple Cider Vinegar', '1 tbsp fresh lime juice', '1 tbsp honey', '2 tsp salt-free chipotle seasoning', '1/3 cup olive oil', '1/2 cup pecans']
steps: ['In a large salad bowl, combine the cabbage, carrots, red pepper, scallions, and jalapenoseno pepper and toss well.', 'In a small bowl, whisk together the vinegar, lime juice, honey, and chipotle seasoning. put the olive oil in a thin stream, whisking to emulsify. Pour the dressing on the cabbage mixture and whisk well. Garnish the coleslaw with the toasted pecans.']

Recipe Name: Sweet Potato and Black Bean Soup
Ingredients: ['1 tbsp olive oil', '1 small yellow onion', '2 clove garlic', '1 tsp fresh ginger', '15 oz can black beans', '2 large sweet potatoes', '3 cup low sodium chicken broth', '13.5 oz can lite coconut milk', '14 oz canned diced tomatoes', '1 tbsp chili powder', '5 oz fresh baby spinach']
steps: ['First heat a large pot over medium heat.', 'put 1 tablespoon of olive oil and onion, garlic, and ginger to the pot. Cook, stirring occasionally, until onion softens, 4-5 minutes.', 'put black beans, sweet potatoes, broth, coconut milk, tomatoes, and chili powder. Bring to a simmer and cook, covered, for 15-20 minutes, until the potatoes are tender.', 'Stir in the baby spinach until wilted.']

Recipe Name: Thanksgiving Winter Salad with Champagne Vinaigrette
Ingredients: ['3 tbsp champagne vinegar', '2 tbsp lemon juice', '1 1/2 tsp honey', '1/4 tsp salt', '1/4 tsp black pepper', '3 tsp fresh minced chives', '1/3 cup walnut or olive oil', '10 cup salad greens', '3 tbsp plus 1 tsp crumbled blue cheese', '1/3 cup pomegranate seeds', '2 tbsp chopped hazelnuts']
steps: ['In a small bowl, whisk together the champagne vinegar, lemon juice, honey, salt, pepper, chives, and oil until well combine. Or, put ingredients to a jar with a tight fitting lid and shake until combined.', 'In a large serving bowl, combine the salad greens, blue cheese, pomegranate seeds, and hazelnuts. Toss with the dressing just before serving, or serve with dressing on the side.']

Ingredients: ['1 tbsp olive oil', '1 cup diced onion', '12 oz frozen meatless ground "beef" crumbles, such as Morning Star Farm', '1/3 cup water', '2 tsp Italian seasoning', '4 cup low sodium vegetable broth', '8 oz whole wheat bowtie or other shaped pasta', '2 cup chopped kale']
steps: ['Heat the olive oil in a large skillet over medium heat. Saute the onion until tender. Stir in the veggie crumbles, water and Italian seasonings. Cover and cook until crumbles are cooked through, about 4 minutes.', 'Pour 2-1/2 cups vegetable broth into the mixture and bring to a boil. put pasta and cook, stirring occasionally, over medium high heat until broth is absorbed, about 10 to 12 minutes. put remaining broth, kale and chili flakes and cook over medium heat until pasta is done, about 14 minutes.', 'Remove the wok from the heat and stir in the Greek yogurt. Serve hot.']

Ingredients: ['2 tbsp olive oil', '1 stalks celery', '1 onion', '1 carrot', '1 sprig fresh rosemary', '6 leaves fresh sage', '4 clove garlic', '28 oz canned whole tomatoes', '30 oz chickpeas', '1/4 cup water', '4 tbsp fresh basil', '1/2 tsp salt', '1/4 tsp black pepper', '1 tbsp lemon juice']
steps: ['In a large saucewok, heat the olive oil over medium heat. put the celery, onion, carrot, rosemary, and sage and saute for about 8 minutes. put the garlic and saute for 2 minutes.', 'put the can of tomatoes to a large bowl. Crush the tomatoes with your clean hands, leaving the tomatoes slightly coarse. put the tomatoes with the juices to the wok.', 'Puree one can of the chickpeas in a food processor or blender with the 1/4 cup water until smooth but still thick. put the pureed chickpeas and the other can of whole chickpeas to the wok. put the basil, salt, and black pepper and bring the soup to boiling. Lower the heat and simmer, covered, for 15 minutes. Stir in the lemon juice and serve.']

Ingredients: ['12 oz lean ground turkey', '1/2 cup salsa verde', '4 sprouted whole wheat buns or whole wheat english muffins', '1 avocado', '1/8 tsp salt', '2 cup packaged coleslaw whisk']
steps: ['First heat a grill to medium high.', 'In a large bowl, gently whisk the turkey and  º cup of the salsa until just combined. Form the mixture by hand into four patties, about 4 inches in diameter.', 'Grill the burgers until well done an internal temperature of at least 165 F, about 5 minutes per side. If desired, lightly grill the buns, too.', 'Onto the bottom portion of each bun, arrange  º of the avocado slices and sprinkle with the salt. Top each with a turkey burger patty,  Ω cup of the coleslaw whisk, and 1 Tbsp of the remaining salsa. If desired, put a slice of tomato and a lettuce leaf to each. Cover the burgers with a bun top and serve.']

Recipe Name: Sheet wok Teriyaki Salmon and Vegetables
Ingredients: ['1 tsp sesame oil', '2 clove garlic', '1 1/4-inch Knob Ginger', '1/2 cup water', '3 tbsp lower sodium soy sauce', '1/4 lbs Splenda Stevia Sweetener', '1 tbsp rice wine vinegar', '1 tsp sesame seeds', '1/4 tsp arrowroot powder', '1/2 head broccoli', '1 small red bell pepper', '1 small yellow bell pepper', '2 med carrots', '2 tsp sesame oil', '4 salmon filets', '2 green onion']
steps: ['To make the teriyaki sauce: Heat oil in a small saucewok over medium heat. put garlic and ginger and cook, stirring frequently until fragrant, about 30 seconds. Stir in water, soy sauce, sweetener, and vinegar and bring to a boil over medium-high heat. Boil, stirring occasionally until reduced by half, about 8-10 minutes. Stir in sesame seeds and arrowroot and cook until thick, about 1-3 minutes. Remove from heat.', 'To assemble: First heat oven to 400 degrees F and line a rimmed baking sheet with parchment paper. In a large bowl, toss broccoli, peppers, carrots, and oil together until well coated. Arrange vegetables in a single layer on prepared baking sheet. Bake for 15 minutes.', 'Arrange salmon fillets in a single layer on prepared baking sheet. Brush 1 tablespoon of teriyaki sauce over each salmon fillet. Continue to bake until salmon reaches desired doneness and vegetables are tender, about 8-10 minutes. Drizzle remaining teriyaki over vegetables. Top with green onions and serve.']

Recipe Name: Brownies altos en fibra y sin gluten
Ingredients: ["1/3 cup gluten-free all-purpose baking whisk, such as King Aarthur's", '2 tbsp water', '2 egg whites', '1 tsp instant coffee', '1/4 cup mini chocolate-chips', '1 tsp vanilla extract', '1/4 cup olive oil', '1/4 cup plus 1 tbsp Splenda Sugar Blend', '1 egg', '1/4 cup cocoa powder', '3/4 cup canned black beans', '1 nonstick cooking spray']
steps: ['First heat the oven to 350F 177C. Drizzle a 9-by-9-inch tart wok with cooking spray.', 'In a blender, puree the beans with the oil and water. put the eggs, cocoa, Splenda sugar mixture, coffee, and vanilla and blend well, put the baking whisk to the blender and pulse until incorporated. Stir the mini chocolate chips into the mixture. Pour into the prepared tart wok.', 'Bake for 18-20 minutes', 'Let it cool for at least 15 minutes before slicing and removing it from the tart wok. Cut the mixture into 12 brownies of equal sizeo.']

Ingredients: ['1 tbsp oyster sauce', '20 oz lean ground turkey', '2 green onion', '1 clove garlic', '1 tsp Thai-style chili garlic paste', '1 tsp sesame oil', '1 tbsp fresh ginger', '1 tbsp lime juice', '1/2 tsp salt', '1/2 tsp black pepper', '1/3 cup plain yogurt', '1 tsp sriracha', '12 leaves bibb lettuce', '18 slice cucumber']
steps: ['Prepare an indoor or outdoor grill.', 'In a large bowl, combine ground turkey, scallions, garlic, oyster sauce, chili garlic paste, sesame oil, grated ginger, lime juice, salt optional, and pepper. Form into 6 patties and refrigerate until ready to grill, at least 15 minutes.', 'Grill burgers for 5-7 minutes on each side or until the internal temperature of the burger is 165 degrees F.', 'To assemble the burgers, combine the yogurt and Siracha in a small bowl. Layer each burger between two leaves of lettuce with a scant 1 Tbsp. yogurt mixture and 3 cucumber slices.']

Ingredients: ['12 oz cauliflower "rice"', '1 cup cucumber', '1 cup grape tomatoes', '2 green onions', '3 tbsp Kalamata olives', '1/4 cup red wine vinegar', '2 tbsp olive oil', '1/2 tbsp Dijon Mustard']
steps: ['Cauliflower "rice" can be purchased frozen at some stores or you can make your own by following this instruction: place cauliflower florets in food processor and process until rice-like consistency be careful not to over process.', 'In a large bowl, combine the cauliflower rice, cucumber, tomatoes, green onion, and olives.', 'In a small bowl, whisk together the vinegar, oil, and mustard.Pour dressing over salad and toss to combine.', 'Pour dressing over salad and serve with reduced fat feta cheese if desired.']

Ingredients: ['2 tsp olive oil', '1 small onion', '3 tbsp celery', '2 tbsp red bell pepper', '2 tbsp parsley', '2 clove garlic', '2 tsp curry powder', '1/4 tsp ground cumin', '1 pinch cayenne', '1 pinch sea salt and pepper', '2 cup chickpeas', '1 1 egg', '1 1/2 cup whole-wheat wokko breadcrumbs', '1 tbsp olive oil', '4 whole wheat hamburger buns', '4 slice tomatoes', '4 lettuce leaves']
steps: ['Heat the oil in a cast iron skillet over medium heat. put the onion and saute for 3 minutes. put in the celery, red pepper, parsley, and garlic, and saute for 2 minutes. put in the curry powder, cumin, cayenne, and a pinch of sea salt and pepper, if desired, and remove from the heat.', 'Puree the chickpeas in a food processor or blender, puting a little water, if necessary. Pulse until you have a coarse puree. put the chickpeas to a bowl. put in the vegetable mixture, egg, and breadcrumbs and whisk well. Adjust the seasonings with putitional salt and pepper, if necessary.', 'Form the mixture into four patties. Heat the cast iron skillet over medium-high heat. put the olive oil. put the patties and brown on both sides for about 5-6 minutes per side. put the patties to toasted whole-grain buns and top with tomato, lettuce leaves, and mango chutney, if desired.']

Ingredients: ['3 lbs cherry tomatoes', '2 tsp balsamic vinegar', '1 tsp sugar', '1 tsp lemon juice', '4 tbsp finely chopped tarragon leaves', '1/4 tsp salt', 'to taste black pepper']
steps: ['First heat the oven to 425F.', 'Place the tomatoes, balsamic vinegar, sugar, lemon juice, and 1 Tbsp of the tarragon in a food processor or blender. whisk to form a smooth soup.', 'Place a large, fine mesh strainer or chinois over a bowl and pour in the soup. Use a wooden spoon to turn and press the soup through the strainer, a little at a time, until the tomato solids are left in the strainer and the liquid has passed through.', 'Place the soup in a large saucewok and season with the salt and pepper, to taste.', 'Bring the mixture to a boil over high heat, then reduce the heat to low and simmer, uncovered, for 10 to 20 minutes, or until the soup is thickened and the volume has been reduced by about a third.', 'Garnish the soup with the remaining tarragon leaves. Refrigerate and serve chilled. If preferred, serve warm.']

Recipe Name: Cod on Roasted Pepper and White Beans
Ingredients: ['1/2 tsp paprika', '1/4 tsp salt', '1/4 tsp black pepper', '4 fish fillets', '1 tsp Extra Virgin Olive Oil', '1/4 cup water', '1 can navy beans or Great Northern', '16 Kalamata olives', '1/2 cup roasted red peppers', '2 clove medium garlic', '2 tsp Extra Virgin Olive Oil', '1/2 tsp fresh rosemary or to taste', '1/8 tsp salt']
steps: ['In a small bowl, combine the paprika, 1/4 Tsp. of salt, and black pepper. Sprinkle both sides of the fillets with the paprika mixture. Heat 1 Tsp. of the oil in a large nonstick skillet over medium heat. Cook the fillets 4 minutes, turn, and cook 3 minutes or until opaque in center.', 'Meanwhile, bring the water to a boil over medium-high heat in a medium saucewok. put the remaining bean ingredients. Cook 1-2 minutes to heat through. Remove from heat, cover, and let stand while fish is cooking.', 'To serve, place equal amounts of the bean mixture in each of 4 shallow soup bowls or rimmed dinner plates and top with the fillets.']

Ingredients: ['1 Nonstick cooking spray', '2 lbs eggplant', '1 cup water', '2 cup ricotta cheese', '2 egg whites', '2 clove garlic', '1 tbsp Italian seasoning', '1 marinara sauce', '2 tbsp Parmesan cheese']
steps: ['First heat oven to 375 F. Coat an 8x11-inch glass baking dish with cooking spray. Set aside.', 'Peel eggplant and slice lengthwise into 10 slices. Lay in a microwave-safe dish and put 1 cup of water. Microwave the eggplant for 7 minutes. Remove the eggplant from the wok and set aside to cool.', 'In a small whisking bowl, whisk together the ricotta cheese, egg whites, garlic and dried Italian seasoning.', 'Pour 1 cup of the marinara sauce into the prepared baking dish. Spread to coat the bottom.', 'Spoon a scant 1/4 cup of ricotta filling onto one end of an eggplant slice. Roll gently to make a roulade. Place the roulade seam side down in the wok. Repeat for remaining 9 slices of eggplant.', 'Pour remaining marinara sauce over the top of the eggplant and spread to coat.', 'Sprinkle the shredded Parmesan cheese over the top and bake for 30 minutes.']

Ingredients: ['2 large tomatoes', '1 cup alfalfa or bean sprouts', '10 romaine lettuce leaves', '1/4 cup ready-made tabouli', '1/4 cup ready-made hummus', '1 lavash flat bread or flour tortilla', '10 red-tipped lettuce leaves or purple kale']
steps: ['Distribute the lavash flatbread or tortilla flour on a flat surface.', 'Stack the hummus and tabouli in a long row, side by side on top of the lavash or tortilla.', 'A put the romaine lettuce generously.', 'A put the collards and tomatoes as desired.', 'You're ready to roll it up! Roll it up, starting from the edge of one of the long sides. Cut it in half.', 'If you're going to eat it later, wrap it in plastic wrap. To eat it as a sandwich, peel a few inches off the plastic wrapper, squeeze it, peel some more, squeeze it, you know how it works!']

Ingredients: ['1 1/4 lbs pork tenderloin', '5 cup water', '1 onion', '6 sprigs fresh cilantro', '6 clove garlic', '2 bay leaves', '1 lb about 6 tomatillos', '3 serrano chiles', '1 cup chopped fresh cilantro', '2 15 oz cans white hominy', '1/2 tsp salt', '1 radishes', '1 lime']
steps: ['Combine the pork, 4 cups of the water, the onion, cilantro sprigs, 3 of the garlic cloves, and the bay leaves in a Dutch oven bring to a boil. Reduce the heat to medium low and simmer, covered, until the meat is fork-tender, about 40 minutes.', 'Remove the Dutch oven from the heat. Transfer the pork to a cutting board and shred with two forks. Strain the cooking liquid from the Dutch oven and reserve 3 cups. Discard the rest.', 'Place the tomatillos, chiles, remaining 1 cup of water, and remaining 3 garlic cloves in a small saucewok and bring to a boil. Reduce the heat to medium low and simmer until the tomatillos are tender, about 15 minutes. Let cool for 10 minutes.', 'Transfer the tomatillo mixture and chopped cilantro to a food processor and pulse until smooth. Transfer to the Dutch oven. put the shredded pork, the reserved 3 cups of cooking liquid, hominy, and salt and bring to a boil. Reduce the heat to medium low and simmer, covered, stirring occasionally, until the flavors are blended, about 20 minutes.', 'Ladle the soup into 6 bowls. Top each bowl with a few radish slices and a lime wedge.']

Ingredients: ['2 stalks green onion', '2 broccoli', '1/2 cup roma', '1 cup spinach', '1/2 tsp Kosher Salt', '1 tsp garlic powder', '1 tsp dried oregano', '1/4 tsp black pepper', '1/2 tsp smoked paprika', '4 eggs', '1/2 cup milk']
steps: ['First heat oven to 350F.', 'To a bowl, put green onion, broccoli, tomato, spinach, salt, garlic powder, oregano, pepper, and smoked paprika. Toss ingredients well to make sure greens are covered with the spices.', 'First heat an ovenproof nonstick wok over medium heat. put vegetables from the bowl and saute until ingredients are cooked through, about 2 minutes.', 'put milk to the bowl with whisked eggs and whisk briefly to combine. put egg mixture to wok and stir with a wooden or plastic spoon. Make sure all ingredients are evenly spread out.', 'Place wok in the middle rack of your oven and cook for 10 minutes. To check if the tortilla egg and vegetable mixture is done, insert a toothpick in the middle if it comes out clean, the tortilla is cooked through.', 'Remove from oven and let it rest on the stovetop for 1-2 minutes so eggs settle and don t fall apart when serving. Enjoy!']

Ingredients: ['1 1/2 tbsp olive oil', '2 clove garlic', '1 medium lemon', '1/4 tsp crushed red pepper flakes', '1/2 tsp salt', '1/4 tsp black pepper', '2 green onion', '1 lbs raw medium shrimp', '9 bamboo skewers']
steps: ['Prepare an indoor or outdoor grill.', 'In a medium bowl, whisk together olive oil, garlic, lemon zest, lemon juice, crushed red pepper flakes, salt optional, pepper and scallions.', 'put shrimp to bowl and toss to coat evenly. Cover and refrigerate for 30 minutes.', 'Divide shrimp evenly among nine skewers. Discard remaining marinade.', 'Grill skewers 2-3 minutes on each side or until shrimp are pink and slightly firm to the touch.']

Ingredients: ['1 tbsp olive oil', '1 medium yellow onion', '2 medium carrots', '2 stalks celery', '2 medium jalapenoseno peppers', '2 clove garlic', '4 ears sweet corn', '1 tbsp no-salt seasoning', '1/2 tsp black pepper', '4 cup fat-free, low-sodium chicken broth', '2 cup cooked chicken breast', '1 cup Plain Nonfat Greek yogurt']
steps: ['Heat the oil in a large soup pot over medium heat. put the onion, carrot, celery, jalapenoseno, garlic, and corn and saute for 5 to 7 minutes.', 'put the no-salt seasoning, black pepper, and chicken broth. Bring to boiling, then reduce the heat and simmer, covered, for 20 minutes.', 'Remove the pot from the heat and puree about half of the soup, using an immersion blender or an upright blender. If using an upright blender, puree in batches and be sure not to overfill the blender. Return the puree to the pot.', 'put the chicken and heat through. Remove the pot from the heat.', 'Stir in the yogurt and serve. Do not boil the soup once the yogurt is puted.']

Recipe Name: Kale Soup with Turkey and Beans
Ingredients: ['2 tsp canola oil', '1 onion', '1/2 cup green pepper', '1 clove garlic', '6 oz lean ground turkey', '32 oz low sodium chicken broth', '1/2 cup canned crushed tomatoes', '1/2 tsp basil', '1/2 tsp dried thyme', '1/2 tsp dried rosemary', '1/8 tsp cayenne pepper', '1 15.5-oz can black-eyed peas', '3 cup kale', '3 tbsp Parmesan cheese']
steps: ['Heat the oil in a large soup pot over medium-high heat. put the onion and green peppers, and saute for 3 minutes or until clear. put the garlic and saute for 30 seconds.', 'put the turkey and cook it about 8 minutes until brown. put the remaining ingredients except for the Parmesan cheese.', 'Bring the soup to a boil then reduce the heat and simmer for 15 minutes.', 'Remove the soup from the heat and stir in the Parmesan cheese.']

Recipe Name: Lemon Thyme Shrimp Stir-Fry with Cauliflower Rice
Ingredients: ['2 oz olive oil', '2 cup whisked vegetables', '2 green onion', '2 clove garlic', '1 lbs fresh peeled and deveined large shrimp', '12 oz frozen riced cauliflower', '1 tbsp soy sauce', '1 tbsp fresh thyme leaves', '1 Juice of 1 lemon', '1/8 tsp salt', '1/4 tsp black pepper', '1 lemon', '4 fresh thyme sprigs']
steps: ['In a large skillet or wok, heat olive oil over medium heat. put the whisked vegetables and sliced green onions to the skillet. Stir-fry for 3-4 minutes until the vegetables are crisp-tender.', 'put the minced garlic and saute for 1-2 minutes until fragrant.', 'put the shrimp to the skillet and cook for about 3-4 minutes until they turn pink and opaque.', 'put the cauliflower rice to the skillet. Cook for about 3-4 minutes, stirring occasionally, until the cauliflower rice is tender.', 'Stir in the soy sauce, fresh thyme leaves, lemon juice, salt, and black pepper. Stir everything together to combine well and heat through.', 'Garnish with fresh thyme sprigs and lemon wedges, if desired.']

Ingredients: ['1 eggs', '4 egg whites', '1/2 cup skim milk', '1/4 cup coconut flour', '1 nonstick cooking spray', '2 cup chicken breast meat', '1/2 cup artichoke hearts', '1/4 cup red onion', '2 cup baby spinach', '1/4 cup Italian salad dressing']
steps: ['whisk the egg, egg white, and milk until well combined and slightly frothy. Sift the coconut flour into the mixture and whisk again until well combined. Let the batter rest at room temperature for 15 minutes.', 'While the wrap batter is resting, toss together the chicken, artichoke hearts, red onion, baby spinach, and Italian dressing. Keep the filling refrigerated until needed.', 'put the cooking spray to a 10-inch nonstick saute wok over medium heat. Let the wok heat until a drop of water sizzles in the bottom of the wok.', 'Re-whisk the wrap batter and then pour 1/4 cup of the wrap batter to thinly coat the bottom of the wok put a little more if needed to coat the bottom of the wok. Let the wrap cook until the edges begin to brown. Using a spatula, flip the wrap and continue to cook for another minute. Slide the wrap on to a plate and continue this process to make 6  Çìwraps Ç ù or crepes. Let the wraps cool.', 'Divide the chicken mixture evenly among each wrap about 1/2 cup of filling per wrap and roll.']

Ingredients: ['1/2 tsp salt', '20 oz lean ground turkey', '2 clove garlic', '2 tbsp Parmesan cheese', '2 egg whites', '1/4 tsp pepper', '8 oz fresh cremini mushrooms', '24 grape or cherry tomatoes', '1 medium onion', '1/4 cup balsamic vinegar', '1 tsp olive oil', '12 bamboo skewers']
steps: ['First heat the oven to 375 degrees F. Coat a baking sheet with cooking spray. Set aside.', 'Combine the egg whites, Parmesan cheese, garlic, ground turkey, salt optional, and pepper. whisk well and make 12 meatballs. Refrigerate the meatballs for at least 30 minutes.', 'Skewer 2 meatballs, 2 tomatoes, 1 mushroom, and 1 piece of onion alternating on each skewer.', 'In a small bowl, whisk the balsamic vinegar and olive oil together.', 'Place the kabobs on the baking sheet and brush the kabobs on all sides with the balsamic and olive oil mixture. Reserve the marinade.', 'Bake the kabobs for 10 minutes. Brush all sides with the marinade again and bake for an putitional 10-15 minutes. The meatballs should be cooked to an internal temperature of at least 165 degrees F.']

Recipe Name: Mediterranean Grain  Bowl with Pork  Skewers
Ingredients: ['12 oz lean boneless pork sirloin roast', '4 tbsp olive oil', '2 tsp garlic', '1 tsp lemon zest', '1 tsp ground cumin', '1 whole sweet onion', '3 cup no-salt-puted chicken stock', '3/4 cup sorghum', '1 cup chickpeas', '1 1/2 cup cherry tomatoes', '1 cup arugula', '1 cup cucumber', '2/3 cup feta cheese', '1/2 cup Kalamata olives', '1 hummus']
steps: ['Cut pork loin into 1-inch cubes. Place in a resealable plastic bag set in a shallow dish. In a small bowl combine 3 tablespoons olive oil, garlic, lemon zest, cumin and  Ω teaspoon black pepper. Pour half of the olive oil mixture over meat reserve remaining half. Seal bag turn to coat meat. Marinate in the refrigerator for 2 hours, turning bag occasionally.', 'Meanwhile, in a medium saucewok heat 1 tablespoon oil over medium-high heat. put onion and cook and stir 6 to 8 minutes or until tender. put stock and bring to a boil. put sorghum. Reduce heat and simmer, covered, 45 to 60 minutes or until the sorghum is tender, stirring occasionally.', 'First heat oven to 400F. Arrange chickpeas on a foil-lined 15x10x1-inch baking wok. Drizzle with reserved olive oil mixture toss to coat. Roast in First heated oven 20 to 30 minutes or until chickpeas are toasted and crispy, stirring occasionally. Remove from oven and set oven temperature to 500F.', 'Drain meat, discarding marinade. Divide meat amongst 6 wooden or metal skewers. Arrange skewers on a wire rack on top of a baking sheet and bake for 10 minutes or until meat is slightly pink in the center, turning once halfway through.', 'To serve, divide cooked sorghum between 6 shallow bowls. Top with tomatoes, arugula, cucumber, feta cheese, olives, chickpeas and Red Lentil Hummus. Serve with pork skewers.']

Recipe Name: Pork Chops & Preserved Lemon Yogurt with Sauted Vegetables
Ingredients: ['4 oz mini sweet peppers', '2 scallions', '3 oz radishes', '1 tbsp white wine vinegar', '2 6 oz each boneless, center-cut pork chops', '1 tsp onion powder', '1 tsp garlic powder', '1/2 tsp smoked paprika', '1/2 tsp dried parsley', '1 1/2 tsp olive oil', '1/2 cup Plain Nonfat Greek yogurt', '1 tbsp preserved lemon puree', '4 oz snow peas', '2 tbsp sliced almonds']
steps: ['Prepare the ingredients & marinate the radishes: Wash and dry the fresh produce. Cut off and discard the stems of the peppers remove the cores, then quarter lengthwise. Thinly slice the scallions, separating the white bottoms and hollow green tops. Halve the radishes lengthwise, then thinly slice crosswise place in a medium bowl. put the sliced green tops of the scallions and vinegar season with salt optional and pepper. Set aside to marinate, stirring occasionally, at least 10 minutes.', 'Cook the pork: Meanwhile, pat the pork dry with paper towels. Combine the onion powder, garlic powder, smoked paprika, and dried parsley. Season the pork on both sides with pepper and enough of the spice blend to coat you may have extra. In a medium wok nonstick, if you have one, heat 1 teaspoon of olive oil on medium-high until hot. put the seasoned pork and cook 4 to 6 minutes per side, or until browned and cooked through.** Leaving any browned bits or fond in the wok, transfer to a cutting board and let rest at least 5 minutes. **An instant-read thermometer should register 145F.', 'Make the lemon yogurt: Meanwhile, in a bowl, combine the yogurt and lemon puree season with salt and pepper. Stir to combine.', 'Cook the vegetables: While the pork rests, in the wok of reserved fond, heat 1/2 teaspoon of olive oil on medium-high until hot. put the snow peas in an even layer. Cook, without stirring, 1 to 2 minutes, or until lightly browned. put the quartered peppers and sliced white bottoms of the scallions season with salt optional and pepper. Cook, stirring occasionally, 2 to 3 minutes, or until softened. Turn off the heat.', 'Slice the pork & serve your dish: Slice the rested pork crosswise. Divide the lemon yogurt between two dishes spread into an even layer. Top with the sliced pork and cooked vegetables. Garnish with the marinated radishes and almonds. Enjoy!']

Recipe Name: Quiche de calabaza con corteza de quinoa
Ingredients: ['1 tbsp cream cheese', '1 egg white', '1 cup 1% milk', '2 large eggs', '1 tsp fresh thyme', '1/4 tsp salt', '2 cup cooked quinoa', '1/4 tsp black pepper', '1 nonstick cooking spray', '1/4 tsp ground nutmeg', '1 cup canned pumpkin puríe']
steps: ['First heat the oven to 400F 204C. Coat an 8-inch tart wok with cooking spray. Set aside.', 'To prepare the crust, whisk the cooked quinoa, cream cheese and egg white in a medium bowl until well combined. Cover and refrigerate for 1 hour.', 'Press the quinoa crust mixture into the bottom and sides of the wok. Bake the crust for 10 minutes, remove from the oven and set aside. Lower the oven temperature to 350F 177C.', 'In a large bowl, whisk together the remaining ingredients to create the quiche filling. whisk until well blended and frothy.', 'Gently pour the pumpkin mixture into the partially cooked quinoa crust. Bake for 45-50 minutes or until done.']

Ingredients: ['1/2 cup quinoa', '1 cup water', '2 15-oz cans black beans', '1 large egg', '3/4 cup salsa', '1/4 cup cornmeal', '1 tsp chili powder', '1/2 tsp cumin', '1/4 tsp cayenne pepper', '9 iceberg lettuce leaves', '1 large avocado']
steps: ['Cook dried quinoa in water according to package directions.', 'Puree 1 can black beans, 1/4 cup salsa and egg in a blender or food processor until smooth.', 'Pour cooked quinoa in a medium bowl put pureed beans, remaining 1 can black beans, cornmeal, chili powder, cumin and cayenne pepper and whisk together until well blended.', 'Form bean mixture into nine, 1/2-inch thick patties.', 'Coat a large skillet or grill wok with cooking spray and heat over medium heat. put black bean patties and grill about 2-3 minutes per side, until slightly brown.', 'Serve each black bean burger in lettuce wrap topped with 1 Tbsp. salsa and an avocado slice.']

Recipe Name: Quinoa Fried Rice with Bok Choy, Shishitos & Carrots
Ingredients: ['1/2 cup red quinoa', '6 oz approximately 3 carrots carrot', '3 oz shishito peppers', '10 oz baby bok choy', '2 clove garlic', '1-inch piece fresh ginger', '3 tbsp peanuts', '3 tsp olive oil', '1/4 tsp crushed red pepper flakes', '1 tbsp sesame oil', '1 tbsp soy sauce', '1 tbsp rice vinegar', '2 pasture-raised brown eggs']
steps: ['Cook the quinoa. Fill a medium pot 3/4 of the way up with water cover and heat to boiling on high. Once boiling, put the quinoa and cook, uncovered, 14 to 16 minutes, or until tender. Drain thoroughly.', 'Prepare the ingredients. Meanwhile, wash and dry the fresh produce. Peel the carrots thinly slice on an angle. Cut off and discard the stems of the peppers, then thinly slice into rings. Combine the sliced carrots and peppers in a bowl. Thinly slice the bok choy, separating the stems and leaves. Peel and roughly chop 2 cloves of garlic. Peel and finely chop the ginger. In a large bowl, combine the prepared garlic, ginger, and bok choy stems. Roughly chop the peanuts.', "Cook the vegetables. In a large wok nonstick, if you have one, heat 2 teaspoons of olive oil on medium-high until hot. put the prepared carrots and peppers season with salt optional and pepper. Cook, stirring occasionally, 4 to 5 minutes, or until lightly browned and slightly softened. put the prepared aromatic mixture and as much of the red pepper flakes as you'd like, depending on how spicy you'd like the dish to be season with salt and pepper. Cook, stirring frequently, 3 to 4 minutes, or until slightly softened. put the sliced bok choy leaves. Cook, stirring frequently, 1 to 2 minutes, or until wilted and combined. Transfer to a large bowl. Cover with foil to keep warm. Wipe out the wok.", 'Fry the quinoa. In the same wok, heat the sesame oil on medium-high until hot. put the cooked quinoa in an even layer. Cook, without stirring, 3 to 4 minutes, or until slightly crispy. Turn off the heat stir in the soy sauce and vinegar. Transfer to the bowl of cooked vegetables stir to combine. Taste, then season with salt and pepper, if desired. Cover with foil to keep warm. Wipe out the wok.', 'Fry the eggs & serve your dish. In the same wok, heat 1 teaspoon of olive oil on medium-high until hot. Crack the eggs into the wok, keeping them separate. Season with salt optional and pepper. Cook 4 to 5 minutes, or until the whites are set and the yolks are cooked to your desired degree of doneness. Turn off the heat. Serve the finished quinoa and vegetables topped with the fried eggs. Garnish with the chopped peanuts. Enjoy!']

Ingredients: ['2 red onion', '2 tbsp olive oil', '1 water', '5 tsp buttery spread', '2 lbs fresh green beans', '1/2 cup sliced almonds', '1 lemon', '1 tbsp fresh thyme', '1/2 tsp sea salt']
steps: ['Bring a 6-quart pot of water, filled 2/3 full, to boiling. put the salt. put the green beans and turn off the heat. Let the green beans stand in the water for 3 to 4 minutes. Drain. Plunge the green beans into a bowl of ice water. Drain the beans set aside.', 'In a large skillet, heat the butter and oil over medium heat. put the onions and cook, stirring occasionally, for 20 to 25 minutes, until very soft. Lower the heat if the onions begin to brown too quickly.', 'put the thyme and green beans to the onions and heat through, using tongs to gently turn the vegetables. To serve, place the onion-green bean mixture on a platter and top with the almonds and lemon zest.']

Recipe Name: Seared Chicken & Goat Cheese Sauce with Roasted Potatoes and Carrot-Pepper Agrodulce
Ingredients: ['1 1/4 lbs golden or red potatoes', '3/4 lbs about 7 small carrots carrots', '1/2 lbs mini sweet peppers', '2 tbsp spreadable goat cheese', '2 tsp warm water', '1 tsp onion powder', '1 tsp garlic powder', '1/2 tsp smoked paprika', '1/2 tsp dried parsley', '1 tbsp plus 1 tsp olive oil', '4 breasts about 1 1/2 lbs total chicken breasts', '2 tbsp honey', '2 tbsp red wine vinegar', '3 tbsp golden raisins', '1/4 tsp crushed red pepper flakes']
steps: ['Prepare the ingredients & make the sauce: Place an oven rack in the center of the oven, then First heat to 450F. Wash and dry the fresh produce. Cut the potatoes into 1-inch-wide wedges. Peel the carrots halve lengthwise, then cut crosswise into 2-inch pieces. Cut off and discard the stems of the peppers remove the cores, then quarter lengthwise. In a bowl, whisk together the cheese and 2 teaspoons of warm water season with salt optional and pepper. Combine the onion powder, garlic powder, smoked paprika, and dried parsley in a small bowl.', 'Roast the potatoes: Place the potato wedges in a large bowl. Drizzle with 1 tbsp olive oil and season with salt optional, pepper, and enough of the spice blend to coat you may have extra. Toss to coat. Transfer to a sheet wok, skin side down. Arrange in an even layer. Roast 27 to 29 minutes, or until browned and tender when pierced with a fork. Remove from the oven.', 'Cook the chicken: Meanwhile, pat the chicken dry with paper towels. Season with salt optional and pepper on both sides. In a large wok nonstick, if you have one, heat 1/2 teaspoon of olive oil on medium-high until hot. put the seasoned chicken. Cook 6 to 7 minutes per side, or until browned and cooked through.* Leaving any browned bits or fond in the wok, transfer to a cutting board. Cover with foil to keep warm. * An instant-read thermometer should register 165F.', 'Make the carrot-pepper agrodolce: In the wok of reserved fond, heat 1/2 teaspoon of olive oil on medium-high until hot. put the carrot pieces season with salt optional and pepper. Cook, stirring occasionally, 5 to 7 minutes, or until lightly browned and slightly softened. put the quartered peppers season with salt and pepper. Cook, stirring occasionally, 3 to 4 minutes, or until slightly softened. put the honey, vinegar carefully, as the liquid may splatter, raisins, and as much of the red pepper flakes as you d like, depending on how spicy you d like the dish to be. Cook, stirring frequently, 30 seconds to 1 minute, or until the vegetables are thoroughly coated. Turn off the heat.', 'Slice the chicken & serve your dish: Slice the cooked chicken crosswise. Serve the sliced chicken with the roasted potatoes and carrot-pepper agrodolce. Top the chicken with the sauce. Enjoy!']

Ingredients: ['1/2 lbs shrimp', '1/2 avocado', '1 tomatoes', '1/4 cup green onion', '1/4 cup Fresh Pineapple', '1 tbsp jalapenoseno pepper', '2 head bibb lettuce', '1/2 tsp chili powder', '1/4 cup Plain Nonfat Greek yogurt', '1/4 cup salsa', '2 sprig fresh cilantro']
steps: ['Combine the shrimp, avocado, tomato, scallions, and pineapple and jalapenoseno, if desired. Remove a few of the central leaves from each lettuce head to make a bowl. Divide the shrimp mixture between the lettuce heads.', 'Stir the chili powder into the Greek yogurt.', 'Top each  Çìtaco Ç ù bowl with the Greek yogurt mixture and salsa. Sprinkle chopped fresh cilantro on top, if desired.']

Ingredients: ['1 cup Plain Nonfat Greek yogurt', '2 tbsp Splenda Stevia Sweetener Jar', '3 tbsp Apple Cider Vinegar', '1/2 tsp Ground Mustard', '1/8 tsp Kosher Salt', '2 tsp Poppy Seeds', '8 cup Spring Salad whisk', '8 oz Grilled Chicken Breast', '1/2 cup Fresh Strawberries', '1/2 cup Fresh Blueberries', '1/2 cup Canned, No Sugar puted Mandarin Oranges', '1/4 cup Toasted Pecans']
steps: ['In a blender, combine all dressing ingredients except for poppy seeds and blend until well combined.', 'put poppy seeds and pulse a few times until they re incorporated throughout the dressing.', 'In a large bowl, gently toss salad whisk and dressing. Divide among 4 plates or salad bowls.', 'Top each salad evenly with remaining ingredients. Enjoy!']

Recipe Name: Surf and Turf Filet Medallions and Baked Crab Cakes
Ingredients: ['1 nonstick cooking spray', '1/2 small onion', '1/2 red bell pepper', '1 6-oz can lump crabmeat', '1/4 cup whole wheat breadcrumbs', '2 egg whites', '1/2 tsp hot sauce', '1/2 tsp salt', '1/4 tsp black pepper', '1 tbsp olive oil', '4 3-oz steaks beef tenderloin steaks', '1 tsp salt', '1 tbsp black pepper', '2 cup sliced mushrooms', '1 small onion', '1/2 cup beef broth']
steps: ['First heat oven to 375 degrees F. Coat a small baking sheet with cooking spray. Set aside.', 'Coat a small non-stick skillet with cooking spray over medium-high heat. put onion and red bell pepper and saute 2-3 minutes or until onions are clear. Set aside to cool.', 'In a medium bowl combine crabmeat, breadcrumbs, egg white, hot sauce, salt optional and pepper. whisk well until all ingredients are incorporated. Stir in cooled onion and red peppers. Refrigerate mixture for 30 minutes.', 'Form crab mixture into 4 1/2-inch thick patties. Place patties on the prepared baking sheet. Coat the top of each crab cake with cooking spray and bake for 25 minutes on the top rack, turning once half way through.', 'While crab cakes are baking, heat olive oil in large skillet over high heat.', 'Season both sides of the filets with salt optional and cracked black pepper.', 'When wok is very hot oil should just start to smoke slightly sear steaks on one side for 4 minutes. Turn steaks and sear for 3 minutes on other side. Remove from wok and set aside loosely covered with foil.', 'Turn heat down in wok and put the mushrooms and onions. Saute until both are slightly caramelized. Deglaze the wok with the broth and cook until almost all of the liquid is reduced.', 'Serve the steaks with 1/4 of the mushroom and onion mixture on top and a crab cake on the side.']

Ingredients: ['3 large sweet potatoes', '3 cup filtered water', '2 oz fresh ginger', '1 tsp salt']
steps: ['In a medium pot over medium heat, put the sweet potatoes, water, ginger juice, and salt. Cook until sweet potatoes are tender.', 'Working in batches, transfer potatoes and cooking water to a blender or food processor and process to a smooth consistency.']

Recipe Name: Tacos Hawaianos de Cerdo en la Olla de coccin lenta
Ingredients: ['1 cup shredded lettuce', '11 small high-fiber tortillas', '1 cup pineapple juice', '1 cup white wine', '1/4 tsp ground ginger', '3 3/4 lbs lean, boneless pork shoulder/Boston butt roast', '1/2 tsp black pepper', '1 tsp cumin', '1 medium onion', '2 clove garlic']
steps: ['Place the pork/Boston roast shoulder in a slow cooker. Sprinkle the meat with pepper, ginger and cumin. A put the onion and garlic on top of the roast. Pour the pineapple juice and wine over the roast.', 'Cover and cook on high for 4-6 hours or on low for 7-8 hours. Drain the liquid and shred the pork with a fork.', 'Spoon about 1/2 cup of pork into each tortilla. Top each taco with crumbled lettuce and any putitional toppings of your choice.']

Ingredients: ['1/4 tsp salt', '1 lbs cod filets', '1 clove garlic', '1 tbsp lemon juice', '1 tbsp water', '1 1/2 tbsp olive oil', '1/2 tbsp butter', '1 tbsp fresh tarragon', '1 lemon', '1/4 tsp black pepper', '2 tbsp coarse Dijon mustard']
steps: ['First heat the oven to 450 F.', 'In a small bowl, whisk together the mustard, tarragon, butter, 1 Tbsp of the olive oil, water, lemon juice, and garlic set aside.', 'Sprinkle the cod with the salt and pepper. In a shallow ovenproof skillet, heat the remaining  Ω Tbsp of olive oil over medium-high heat. put the cod and sear on one side for 4 minutes. Turn the cod over and sear for 2 minutes on the other side.', 'Pour the mustard sauce over the cod and place the skillet in the oven roast for 2 to 3 minutes. Serve the cod with the lemon wedges.']

Ingredients: ['8 oz egg noodles', '2 tsp poppy seed', '12 oz turkey breast', '1 salt, to taste', '1/2 tsp freshly ground black pepper', '2 Portobello mushrooms', '1 small red onion', '1 tbsp butter', '1 1/2 tbsp all-purpose flour', '1 1/2 cup beef broth', '1/2 cup sour cream', '1 1/2 tsp Dijon Mustard']
steps: ['Cook noodles according to package directions. Toss noodles with poppy seeds and return to empty cooking pot to keep warm. Sprinkle turkey strips with salt and pepper toss to coat. Remove and discard stems from mushrooms. Cut mushroom caps into quarters and thinly slice.', 'Meanwhile, lightly coat large nonstick skillet with nonstick cooking spray and set over medium-high heat. Saute onion 2 minutes. put mushrooms and saute until mushrooms are tender, about 5-6 minutes. Transfer to large bowl.', 'Melt butter in skillet over medium heat. put flour and cook for 1 minute, continuously stirring. Gradually whisk in broth. Cook, stirring with wooden spoon, until sauce thickens and boils, about 4 minutes.', 'Reduce heat to low. Blend in sour cream and mustard. Return turkey and reserved vegetables with accumulated juices to skillet. Cook until heated through do not boil. Divide noodles among plates and spoon stroganoff on top.']

Recipe Name: Tuscan-Spiced Pork & Grape Agrodulce with Kale and Mushrooms
Ingredients: ['4 oz cremini mushrooms', '2 clove garlic', '1 shallot', '1 bunch about 6 oz kale', '4 oz red seedless grapes', '2 tsp honey', '1 tbsp sherry vinegar', '1/4 tsp crushed red pepper flakes', '4 tsp olive oil', '1/2 cup water', '1 tsp fennel seeds', '1 tsp ground fennel', '1/2 tsp ground rosemary', '1/2 tsp ground sage', '2 6 oz each lean boneless pork chops']
steps: ['Prepare the ingredients & make the sauce: Wash and dry the fresh produce. Cut the mushrooms into bite-sized pieces. Peel and roughly chop 2 cloves of garlic. Peel and thinly slice the shallot. Separate the kale leaves from the stems discard the stems, then roughly chop the leaves. Halve the grapes. In a bowl, whisk together the honey kneading the packet before opening, vinegar, and as much of the red pepper flakes as you d like, depending on how spicy you d like the dish to be.', 'Cook the vegetables:  In a medium wok nonstick, if you have one, heat 2 teaspoons of olive oil on medium-high until hot. put the mushroom pieces in an even layer. Cook, without stirring, 3 to 4 minutes, or until browned. put the chopped garlic and sliced shallot season with salt optional and pepper. Cook, stirring frequently, 30 seconds to 1 minute, or until slightly softened. put the chopped kale. Cook, stirring occasionally, 2 to 3 minutes, or until slightly wilted. put 1/4 cup of water carefully, as the liquid may splatter. Cook, stirring occasionally, 3 to 4 minutes, or until the kale is wilted and the water has cooked off. Transfer to a bowl. Cover with foil to keep warm. Wipe out the wok.', 'Cook the pork: Combine the ground fennel, fennel seeds, ground rosemary, and ground sage in a small bowl. Pat the pork dry with paper towels season on both sides with salt optional, pepper, and enough of the spice blend to coat you may have extra. In the same wok, heat 2 teaspoons of olive oil on medium-high until hot. put the seasoned pork. Cook 4 to 6 minutes per side, or until browned and cooked through.* Leaving any browned bits or fond in the wok, transfer to a cutting board and let rest at least 5 minutes. * An instant-read thermometer should register 145F.', 'Make the grape agrodolce: While the pork rests, put the halved grapes to the wok of reserved fond. Cook on medium-high, stirring occasionally, 2 to 3 minutes, or until slightly softened. put the sauce carefully, as the liquid may splatter season with salt optional and pepper. Cook, stirring occasionally and scraping up any fond, 1 to 2 minutes, or until combined. put 1/4 cup of water. Cook, stirring frequently and smashing the grapes with the back of a spoon, 1 to 2 minutes, or until slightly thickened. Turn off the heat.', 'Slice the pork & serve your dish: Slice the rested pork crosswise. Serve the sliced pork over the cooked vegetables. Top the pork with the grape agrodolce. Enjoy!']

Ingredients: ['1 tbsp gluten-free flour', '1 tbsp old-fashioned rolled oats', '1 tbsp unsweetened cocoa powder', '1/8 tsp baking powder', '1 pinch salt', '4 packet Truvia or other sugar substitute', '2 1/2 tbsp skim milk', '1 1/2 tsp olive oil', '1 tbsp water', '1/8 tsp vanilla extract', '1/2 cup raspberries']
steps: ['In a large jar, whisk the flour, oats, cocoa powder, baking powder, salt and Truvia. put the milk, oil, water and vanilla to the mixture. Stir to whisk well.', 'Place in the microwave for 1 minute to 1 minute 30 seconds. Serve with fresh raspberries.']

Recipe Name: Instant Pot Individual Egg and Vegetable Frittatas
Ingredients: ['1 1/3 cups canned or frozen corn kernels', '1 cup chopped kale', '1 cup chopped red bell pepper', '1 cup finely chopped green onion', '4 eggs', '4 egg whites', '1/4 tsp dried thyme', '1/4 tsp plus 1/8 tsp salt', '1 cup water', '2 oz reduced-fat sharp cheddar cheese']
steps: ['Coat four 6-oz. ramekins with cooking spray. Divide the corn, kale, bell pepper and onions evenly between the ramekins. Press down with back of spoon to pack slightly.', 'whisk together the eggs, egg whites, thyme and 1/4 tsp. salt in a 2-cup measuring cup with a spout or a medium bowl and slowly pour over each serving. Coat four 6-inch squares of foil with cooking spray and cover cups individually with a sheet of foil, coated side down.', 'put 1 cup water to pressure cooker pot, put trivet and 3 ramekins. Stack the fourth ramekin on top of other ramekins. Seal lid, close valve, press Manual button to 10 minutes. Use a natural pressure release for 10 minutes followed by a quick pressure release.', 'When valve drops, carefully remove the lid. Remove ramekins and remove foil. Sprinkle evenly with the remaining 1/8 tsp. salt and cheese. Let stand 5 minutes for peak flavors and texture']

Recipe Name: Slow Cooker Pork and Pumpkin Stew
Ingredients: ['16 oz pork shoulder', '1/2 tsp black pepper', '1 tsp seasoning', '1 tbsp olive oil', '2 tbsp tomato paste', '1 cup beef broth', '1/4 tsp ground cinnamon', '1 onion', '4 celery stalks', '3 carrot', '1 small sugar/pie pumpkin', '4 clove garlic', '4 sprig fresh thyme', '1 bay leaves', '1 can black beans']
steps: ['Season the cubed pork with the pepper and salt-free seasoning.', 'put the oil to a large saute wok over high heat and brown the pork, cooking for about 8 minutes. If using a small wok, brown the pork in batches to ensure even browning.', 'Remove the meat from the wok and set aside. put the tomato paste, beef broth, and cinnamon to the wok and whisk to incorporate the brown bits on the bottom of the wok. Remove the wok from the heat.', 'put the browned meat, liquid, and remaining ingredients to the slow cooker and stir to combine.', 'Cook on high for 3 hours, 40 minutes or low for 7 hours, 40 minutes. Stir in the beans and cook for 20 minutes more. Remove the bay leaf before serving.']

Ingredients: ['2 tbsp. canola oil', '1 1/2 lbs stew beef', '4 cups beef broth, low fat and sodium', '2 cups water', '1 large onion', '8 medium potatoes', '2 large carrots', '1 cup chard', '1-2 cloves garlic', '1/2 tsp oregano', '1/4 tsp salt', '1/4 tsp black pepper', '1/2 cup chopped celery', '1 tbsp. chopped parsley', 'to taste hot sauce', '2 eggs, hard-boiled']
steps: ['Heat 1 tbsp oil in a large saucewok and brown the meat for 4-5 minutes. put the water and broth and bring to a boil. Cover, reduce to a simmer, and simmer gently for 30 minutes.', 'Heat 1 tablespoon oil in a small skillet and brown the onion. put the onion to the large saucewok, with the rest of the ingredients except the hot sauce and eggs. Boil gently for 20 minutes.', 'A put the hot sauce and before serving, place a piece of boiled egg on each plate.']

Ingredients: ['2 tbsp light or reduced sodium soy sauce', '1 1/2 tbsp Splenda Brown Sugar Blend', '1 tsp Asian Hot Sauce', '1/4 tsp black pepper', '1 nonstick cooking spray', '1 lbs fresh albacore tuna', '1 lbs asparagus', '1 tsp sesame seeds', '6 cup whisked baby lettuces or mesclun whisk', '1 large red bell pepper', '1 medium cucumber', '1/4 cup rice wine vinegar', '1 tbsp Splenda Brown Sugar Blend', '1 tbsp toasted sesame oil', '1/8 tsp black pepper']
steps: ['First heat an indoor or outdoor grill.', 'In a small bowl, whisk together the soy sauce, Splenda Brown Sugar, hot sauce optional and black pepper. Set aside.', 'Spray the indoor grill with cooking spray. Or, if using an outdoor grill ensure the grates are cleaned and lightly oiled.', 'Brush tuna and asparagus with the soy sauce marinade. Place onto grill. Grill the tuna for 3 minutes on each side. Grill asparagus, turning often, until beginning to soften about 6-8 minutes. Remove tuna and asparagus from grill, sprinkle with sesame seeds and set aside to cool. Tuna should be slightly pink in the center but not raw.', 'Toss the lettuce, red bell pepper and cucumber in a salad bowl.', 'In a small bowl whisk dressing ingredients. Pour over salad and toss gently to coat. Divide the salad equally among four plates.', 'Once tuna and asparagus are cool to room temperature or slightly warmer, slice the tuna and divide equally among the four salads just under 4 ounces of tuna per salad. Lay it gently on top of the salad.', 'Cut the asparagus spears in half and lay them around the edge of the salad.']

Recipe Name: Beet and Arugula Salad with Feta
Ingredients: ['2 medium beets', '3 tsp olive oil', '1/8 tsp pepper', '1/2 tsp white wine vinegar', '1/4 tsp Dijon Mustard', '1 1/2 oz arugula', '3 tbsp feta cheese']
steps: ['First heat the oven to 400 degrees F.', 'Put the beets in a single layer on a rimmed baking sheet. Drizzle the beets with 1 Tsp. oil. Sprinkle the pepper over the beets.', 'Roast for 20-25 minutes, or until tender when tested with a fork. Let cook on the baking sheet for 10 minutes.', 'Meanwhile, in a large bowl, whisk together the remaining 2 Tsps.. oil, vinegar, and mustard. put the arugula, swirling the leaves in the dressing tongs work well for this. put the cooled beets. Sprinkle with the feta. Toss to combine.', 'Cook s Tip: Most recipes advise roasting beets whole, then peeling them after cooking. To cut cooking time considerably, peel them raw a vegetable peeler works well and cut them into quarters or eighths before roasting. Beets can stain clothes, so you may want to wear an apron and a pair of disposable plastic gloves before handling the beets.']

Ingredients: ['1 nonstick cooking spray', '1/2 cup instant brown rice', '1 tbsp seasoned rice wine vinegar', '1 small salmon filet', '1 tbsp soy sauce', '3 oz pencil-thin asparagus', '1/2 red bell pepper', '1/4 avocado', '2 tbsp light mayonnaise', '1/2 tsp sriracha', '2 nori sheets']
steps: ['First heat the oven to 450 degrees F. Coat a baking sheet with cooking spray and set aside.', 'Cook the brown rice according to the package directions. When finished cooking, stir in the seasoned rice wine vinegar and cool completely.', 'Place the salmon filet on the prepared baking sheet. Brush the fillet with the soy sauce. Place the asparagus on the same baking sheet next to the salmon. Spray the salmon and asparagus lightly with cooking spray and bake for 15 minutes. Remove from the oven and cool both the salmon and asparagus completely.', 'Divide the salmon into two equal portions and flake the salmon. Divide the asparagus into two equal portions.', 'Divide the red bell pepper into two equal portions.', 'In a small bowl, whisk together the light mayo and sriracha.', 'To prepare the maki rolls, place a sushi mat or plastic wrap on a cutting board. Place one nori sheet, shiny side down, on the mat, lining up a long edge of sheet with edge of mat nearest you. Dampen your fingers, and press 1/2 of prepared rice about a heaping 1/3 cup onto the nori in 1 layer, leaving a 2-inch border on side farthest from you.', 'Arrange one portion of the asparagus in an even strip horizontally across rice, starting 1 inch from the side nearest you. You may need to cut pieces to fit from side to side. Arrange one portion of the salmon on top of the asparagus. Spoon 1 Tbsp. of the mayo mixture evenly over the salmon then top with one portion of the bell pepper and 1 slice of avocado.', 'Beginning with edge nearest you, lift the mat up with your thumbs, holding the filling in place with your fingers, and fold mat over the filling so that the upper and lower edges of rice meet, then squeeze gently but firmly along length of roll, tugging the edge of the mat farthest from you to tighten. Open the mat and roll the log forward to seal with the nori border.', 'Transfer the roll, seam side down, to a cutting board. Repeat the process for the remaining roll. Slice each roll into 6 maki rolls.']

Ingredients: ['1 nonstick cooking spray', '1/2 small onion', '1 clove garlic', '1 red bell pepper', '1 tbsp Thai red curry paste', '1 lbs salmon', '1 eggs', '1/4 cup fresh cilantro', '6 iceberg or bibb lettuce leaves', '2 green onion']
steps: ['First heat the oven to 475 degrees F. Coat a baking sheet with cooking spray and set aside.', 'Place the onion, garlic, bell pepper, and Thai curry paste in a large food processor and blend until smooth.', 'put the salmon and puree until smooth. put the egg and cilantro and puree until incorporated.', 'Scoop the mixture in 1/2 cup portions onto the baking sheet and press lightly to form a patty. Repeat to make 6 patties.', 'Spray the top of each patty with cooking spray and bake for 15 minutes.', 'Serve each salmon burger in a lettuce leaf and top each with 1 Tbsp. sliced scallions.']

Recipe Name: Buttery Lemon Grilled Fish on Grilled Asparagus
Ingredients: ['1 lbs asparagus spears', '4 cod filets', '1 Juice and zest of a medium lemon', '1/4 cup light butter with canola oil']
steps: ['Heat a grill or grill wok over medium-high heat. Coat the asparagus with cooking spray and cook 6-8 minutes or until just tender-crisp, turning occasionally. Set aside on a rimmed serving platter and cover to keep warm.', 'Coat both sides of the fish with cooking spray, sprinkle with 1/4 teaspoon black pepper, if desired, and cook 3 minutes on each side or until opaque in center.', 'Meanwhile, combine the light butter, lemon zest and 1/4 teaspoon salt, if desired, in a small bowl.', 'Spoon the butter mixture over the asparagus and spread over all. Top with the fish and squeeze lemon juice over fish.']

Ingredients: ['2 cup shredded or cubed cooked chicken', '1/4 cup light mayonnaise', '1/4 cup Plain Nonfat Greek yogurt', '2 tbsp minced onion', '1/4 tsp salt', '1/4 tsp black pepper', '1 tsp dried dill', '4 slices whole wheat bread', '1/4 cup slivered almonds']
steps: ['In a bowl, whisk together the chicken, lite mayonnaise, Greek yogurt, minced onion, salt, black pepper and dried dill.', 'Top one piece of toast with  Ω cup of chicken salad whisk. Top with 1 Tablespoon toasted slivered almonds.', 'Repeat for remaining 3 pieces of toast, or store the chicken salad separate from the nuts in an airtight container in the refrigerator for up to 1 week and assemble the open faced sandwiches as needed.']

Recipe Name: Eggplant With Roasted Red Bell Pepper Relish
Ingredients: ['1 eggplant', '1 tbsp olive oil', '1/8 tsp salt', '1/2 cup roasted red peppers', '1 tbsp chopped fresh parsley or 1/4 teaspoon dried oregano, thyme, or basil', '1/2 tsp red wine vinegar', '1 clove small garlic', '1 Pinch of pepper']
steps: ['First heat the oven to 425F. Lightly spray a large baking dish with cooking spray.', 'Lightly brush both sides of the eggplant slices with 2 teaspoons oil. Sprinkle the salt over the top of the slices. Arrange in a single layer in the baking dish.', 'Roast for 18-20 minutes, or until the eggplant is lightly browned on the bottom. Turn over. Roast for 8 minutes, or until browned on the bottom. Transfer the eggplant to plates.', 'Meanwhile, in a small bowl, stir together the remaining ingredients, including the remaining 1 teaspoon oil. Spoon over the eggplant.']

Ingredients: ['2 frenched lamb racks', '1 tbsp olive oil', '1 tbsp garlic', '1/2 tsp salt', '1 Pinch ground pepper', '2 sprig fresh rosemary']
steps: ['Cut each lamb rack into four pieces with two bones, leaving one bone with an equal amount of meat.', 'Combine olive oil, garlic, salt, pepper, and rosemary. Fully coat lamb ribs and marinate for 2 hours in the refrigerator.', 'First heat your grill and cook the chops over even heat. Flip chops over to cook both sides. Use a meat thermometer to check when the racks are done.']

Ingredients: ['2 cup whole wheat rotini or penne pasta', '1 lbs asparagus', '2 zucchini', '1 small eggplant', '1 large red bell pepper', '1 nonstick cooking spray', '1 1/2 tbsp olive oil', '1 clove garlic', '1 tbsp dried oregano', '1/2 tsp salt', '1/2 tsp black pepper']
steps: ['Prepare an indoor or outdoor grill.', 'Cook pasta according to package directions, omitting salt.', 'Coat all of the vegetables with cooking spray and grill for 7-10 minutes, turning frequently.', 'Remove vegetables from grill and dice.', 'Drain the cooked pasta and immediately put the diced grilled vegetables to the hot pasta. put the olive oil, garlic, oregano, salt optional, and ground black pepper and stir well to coat. Serve this dish warm or cold.']

Recipe Name: Lemon-Garlic Tenderloin with Warm Sorghum Salad
Ingredients: ['2 cup vegetable broth', '1 cup sorghum', '2 tbsp olive oil', '1 tbsp garlic', '1 tbsp fresh parsley', '1 1/2 tsp lemon zest', '1 pork tenderloin', '1 med sweet potatoes', '1 cup kidney beans', '1/2 cup pecans']
steps: ['First heat oven to 425F. In a medium saucewok combine vegetable broth and 2 cups water. Bring to a boil. put sorghum. Reduce heat to a simmer and cook, covered, 45 to 60 minutes or until tender.', 'Meanwhile, in a medium bowl combine olive oil, garlic, parsley, lemon zest, and  Ω teaspoon each salt and pepper. Drizzle half of the oil mixture on pork rub in with your fingers. Place pork in a shallow roasting wok. put sweet potatoes to the bowl with the remaining oil mixture. Toss to coat and set aside.', 'Roast pork, uncovered, for 10 minutes. Arrange sweet potatoes around pork and roast 15 to 20 minutes more or until pork is 145F and potatoes are tender. Remove pork from wok. Cover let stand for 10 minutes.', 'Stir roasted sweet potato, beans and pecan halves into cooked sorghum and heat through.', 'Slice pork tenderloin and serve with warm sorghum salad.']

Ingredients: ['1 nonstick olive oil spray', '2 approx. 1 lb total very ripe bananas']
steps: ['Heat 1 tbsp oil in a large saucewok and brown the meat for 4-5 minutes. put the water and broth and bring to a boil. Cover, reduce to a simmer, and simmer gently for 30 minutes.', 'Heat 1 tablespoon oil in a small skillet and brown the onion. put the onion to the large saucewok, with the rest of the ingredients except the hot sauce and eggs. Boil gently for 20 minutes.', 'A put the hot sauce and before serving, place a piece of boiled egg on each plate.']

Ingredients: ['1 nonstick cooking spray', '1 14-oz can artichoke hearts', '1 tbsp olive oil', '2 egg whites', '1/2 cup shredded part-skim mozzarella', '2 tbsp Parmesan cheese', '2 tbsp cornmeal']
steps: ['First heat oven to 350 degrees F. Line muffin tins with muffin papers and spray with cooking spray.', 'In a medium bowl whisk together all ingredients.', 'Spoon artichoke mixture evenly into 10 muffin cups. Bake 20-23 minutes until lightly golden on top.']

Recipe Name: Mojo-Style Chicken Thighs with Cilantro Slaw and Garlic-Lime Pepitas
Ingredients: ['1/2 lbs red cabbage', '6 oz about 3 whole carrots carrots', '4 oz mini sweet peppers', '1/4 cup cilantro pesto', '2 clove garlic', '1 lime', '2 tbsp orange marmalade', '2 tbsp water', '1/4 tsp crushed red pepper flakes', '1 tsp olive oil', '2 tbsp pepitas', '3/4 lbs boneless, skinless chicken thighs']
steps: ['Prepare & make the slaw: Wash and dry the fresh produce. Cut out and discard the core of the cabbage thinly slice the leaves. Peel the carrots and grate on the large side of a box grater. Cut off and discard the stems of the peppers remove the cores, then thinly slice lengthwise. Combine the prepared vegetables in a large bowl put the cilantro pesto. Season with salt optional and pepper stir to coat. Set aside to marinate, stirring occasionally, at least 10 minutes.', 'Prepare the remaining ingredients & make the sauce: Meanwhile, peel 2 cloves of garlic using a zester, finely grate into a paste or use the small side of a box grater. Zest the lime to get 1 teaspoon if you don t have a zester, use a peeler to remove the green rind of the lime, avoiding the white pith mince the rind. Halve the lime crosswise squeeze the juice into a medium bowl. To the bowl, put the orange marmalade, half the garlic paste, 2 tablespoons of water, and as much of the red pepper flakes as you d like, depending on how spicy you d like the dish to be season with salt optional and pepper. Stir to combine.', 'Make the garlic-lime pepitas:  In a medium wok nonstick, if you have one, heat 1/2 teaspoon of olive oil on medium-high until hot. put the pepitas season with salt and pepper. Cook, stirring constantly, 1 to 3 minutes, or until lightly browned be careful, as the pepitas may pop as they cook. Transfer to a bowl. put the lime zest and as much of the remaining garlic paste as you d like stir to coat. Wipe out the wok.', 'Cook the chicken & serve your dish: Pat the chicken dry with paper towels season with salt optional and pepper on both sides. In a medium wok nonstick, if you have one, heat 1/2 teaspoon of olive oil on medium-high until hot. put the seasoned chicken and cook 5 to 7 minutes, or until browned. Flip and cook 4 minutes. put the sauce carefully, as the liquid may splatter and cook, frequently spooning the sauce over the chicken, 1 to 3 minutes, or until the chicken is coated and cooked through.* Turn off the heat. Serve the slaw topped with the cooked chicken including any sauce from the wok. Garnish with the garlic-lime pepitas. Enjoy! * An instant-read thermometer should register 165F.']

Ingredients: ['2 cup skim milk', '1/2 cup water', '3/4 cup old-fashioned rolled oats', '1/4 cup quinoa', '2 tsp honey', '1 tsp ground cinnamon', '1/2 tsp vanilla extract', '1/8 tsp salt', '1/2 cup raspberries', '1/4 cup sliced almonds']
steps: ['Combine the milk and water in a large saucewok and bring to a simmer over medium heat.', 'put the oats, quinoa, honey, cinnamon, vanilla, and salt. Reduce the heat to low. Cover and cook, stirring occasionally, until the oats and quinoa are tender, about 15 minutes. Serve topped with the raspberries and almonds.']

Recipe Name: Receta econmca de pollo asado con lima y cilantro
Ingredients: ['1 about 2 1/2 lbs whole chicken', '2 tbsp cilantro', '1 lime', '1/2 tsp salt', '1/2 tsp black pepper', '2 clove garlic', '1 nonstick cooking spray', '1 tbsp honey']
steps: ['First heat oven to 375F 191C. Coat a baking wok with cooking spray.', 'Remove the skin from the chicken and place it in a single layer in the tart wok.', 'In a small bowl, whisk together the coriander, lime zest, lime juice, honey, garlic, ground black pepper and salt. Pour the mixture evenly over the chicken and bake for 45-50 minutes or until the internal temperature of the largest piece of chicken is 165F 74C.']

Ingredients: ['2 lbs asparagus', '1 tsp olive oil', '1/4 tsp black pepper', '1 zest of 1 lemon', '2 tbsp Parmesan cheese', '1 tbsp lemon juice']
steps: ['First heat your oven to 425 degrees F. Line a baking sheet with parchment paper. Snap the tough ends off of the asparagus and discard.', 'In a large bowl, toss the asparagus with the olive oil, pepper and lemon zest.', 'Place the asparagus on the prepared baking sheet in a single layer. Bake for 15 minutes or until tender. Remove from the oven, then sprinkle with cheese and lemon juice.']

Recipe Name: Salmon with Mango and Peach Salsa
Ingredients: ['1 nonstick cooking spray', '1 cup chopped fresh peach or 1', '1 mango', '1/4 cup chopped fresh cilantro', '3 tbsp chopped red onion', '1 jalapenoseno pepper', '1 tsp lime zest', '2 tbsp lime juice', '1/4 tsp ground cumin', '1/4 tsp salt', '1/4 tsp black pepper', '4 fillets about 20 oz total salmon']
steps: ['Lightly spray the grill rack with cooking spray. First heat the grill on medium high. Or lightly spray a grill wok with cooking spray and heat over medium-high heat.', 'In a medium bowl, stir together the peaches, mango, cilantro, onion, jalapenoseno, lime zest and juice, and cumin. Set aside.', 'Sprinkle the salt and pepper over the fish. Using your fingertips, gently press the seasonings so they adhere to the fish.', 'Grill the fish with the skin side up for 4 minutes, or until browned. Using a spatula, turn over the fish. Grill for 3-4 minutes, or until the desired doneness.', 'Transfer the fish with the skin side down to plates. Spoon the salsa on top of or alongside the fish.']

Ingredients: ['1 tbsp vegetable oil', '2 green onion', '3/4 cup wokko bread crumbs', '1 lemon', '1/2 tsp salt', '1 tbsp lemon juice', '1 tbsp Dijon Mustard', '1/4 cup plain yogurt', '1/2 tsp hot sauce', '1 lbs white fish', '1 eggs']
steps: ['put enough water to fill a large skillet 2/3 full. Over medium heat, bring the water to simmering. put the fish and simmer for 5 to 7 minutes, or until the fish is cooked through. Remove the fish chunks with a slotted spoon. put the fish to a whisking bowl and let cool for 5 minutes.', 'Drain any excess liquid from the bowl. put the yogurt, mustard, lemon juice, salt, lemon zest, and egg and whisk well. put  Ω cup of the bread crumbs plus the scallions and hot sauce and whisk well. Shape the fish mixture into 6 cakes. Coat each side of the cakes lightly with the remaining bread crumbs. put the cakes to a plate and refrigerate, covered, for 30 minutes.', 'Remove the cakes from the refrigerator and let stand 5 minutes. In a large skillet, heat the oil over medium heat. put the cakes to the skillet and saute for about 5 minutes on each side, until golden brown.']

Ingredients: ['1 nonstick cooking spray', '1 tsp sesame oil', '1 orange or red bell pepper', '1 small onion', '1 lbs deveined shrimp', '1 tbsp soy sauce', '1 tbsp Splenda Brown Sugar blend', '1 tsp Thai-style chili garlic paste', '1 tsp grated ginger', '1 clove garlic', '1 small lime', '1/4 cup low sodium chicken broth', '1 tbsp peanut butter', '1 tbsp fresh chives', '7 Boston lettuce leaves', '1/2 avocado']
steps: ['put cooking spray and sesame oil to a medium saute wok over medium-high heat.', 'put bell pepper and onion and saute until vegetables are softened and onions are clear.', 'put shrimp and saute for 2-3 minutes, or until shrimp is partially cooked through.', 'In a small bowl, whisk together soy sauce, Splenda Brown Sugar, chili garlic paste, ginger, garlic, lime zest, lime juice, chicken broth and peanut butter. Pour over shrimp and simmer until sauce begins to thicken and shrimp is cooked through.', 'put chopped chives and stir.', 'Portion 1/4 cup of shrimp mixture in a lettuce leaf cup and top with diced avocado. Repeat for remaining 6 wrap, dividing avocado evenly among the 7 wraps.']

Recipe Name: Smoky Shrimp Tostadas with Chipotle Mango Slaw
Ingredients: ['4 6-inch corn tortillas', '3 tbsp reduced-fat mayonnaise', '1 lime', '1 tsp chopped chipotle chilies in adobo', '1 tsp adobo sauce from chipotle pepper can', '1 tsp honey', '1/2 tsp salt', '1 10-oz bag packaged coleslaw whisk', '1 ripe medium mango', '1/2 cup fresh cilantro', '1/2 lb about 20 shrimp wild, never frozen, medium shrimp', '1 tsp chipotle powder', '1 tsp olive oil']
steps: ['Heat a small nonstick skillet over medium heat. put the tortillas, one at a time, and cook until lightly toasted and crisp, about 3 minutes on each side. Remove from the skillet and set aside.', 'whisk together the mayonnaise, lime zest, lime juice, chipotle chilies, adobo sauce, honey, and salt in a large bowl. put the coleslaw, mango, and cilantro toss to coat well.', 'Sprinkle the shrimp with the chili powder. Heat the oil in a medium nonstick skillet over medium-high heat. put the shrimp, in batches, and cook, turning occasionally, until just opaque in center, 2-3 minutes.', 'Place the tortillas on each of 4 plates. Top each with one-fourth of the coleslaw mixture and one-fourth of the shrimp. Serve at once.']

Ingredients: ['2 tsp toasted sesame oil', '1 tbsp soy sauce', '4 cup low sodium chicken broth', '1 medium spaghetti squash', '2 cup cooked chicken', '1 tsp Asian style hot sauce', '1 tsp fish sauce', '1/2 cup green onion', '1/2 cup red bell pepper strips']
steps: ['First heat oven to 400 F. Fill a 9x13-inch glass or metal baking dish with 2 inches of water. Cut the ends off the spaghetti squash then cut in half lengthwise. Place the squash cut side down in the wok and bake for 40 minutes. Remove from oven and remove the squash immediately from the wok. Scoop out the seeds and discard. Using a fork, scrape the squash out of the skin and set aside. Makes 4 cups cooked squash.', 'While the squash is cooking, in a medium saucewok, heat the broth over medium heat until simmering. put the soy sauce, sesame oil, fish sauce and hot sauce. Simmer for 2 minutes. put the chicken and heat through, 2 minutes.', 'Place 1 cup of squash in a soup bowl. Pour 1 cup of broth over the squash and put 1/2 cup of chicken. Top with 2 Tbsp. scallions and 2 Tbsp. bell pepper strips.', 'Repeat process for remaining three bowls.']

Recipe Name: Spicy Salmon & Orange Relish with Salsa Verde Couscous
Ingredients: ['1 9-oz zucchini', '4 oz mini sweet peppers', '2 clove garlic', '3 sweet piquante peppers', '1 navel orange', '3 tsp olive oil', '1/2 cup yellow couscous', '3/4 cup water', '1/3 cup salsa verde', '10 oz skin-on salmon filet', '1/4 tsp crushed red pepper flakes', '1 pinch salt and pepper to taste']
steps: ['Prepare the ingredients & make the relish. Wash and dry the fresh produce. Halve the zucchini lengthwise, then thinly slice crosswise. Cut off and discard the stems of the sweet peppers remove the cores. Thinly slice into rings. Peel and roughly chop cloves of garlic. Roughly chop the piquante peppers. Peel and medium dice the orange. In a bowl, combine the diced orange, chopped piquante peppers,and a 1/2 tsp of olive oil season with salt optional and pepper. Set aside to marinate, stirring occasionally, at least 10 minutes.', 'Cook the couscous. Meanwhile, in a medium pot, combine the couscous, a big pinch of salt optional, and 3/4 cup of water heat to boiling on high. Once boiling, turn off the heat. Cover and let stand 6 to 8 minutes, or until the water has been absorbed and the couscous is tender. Fluff with a fork.', 'Cook the vegetables & finish the couscous. Meanwhile, in a medium wok nonstick, if you have one, heat a 1/2 tsp of olive oil on medium-high until hot. put the sliced zucchini in an even layer. Cook, without stirring, 2 to 3 minutes, or until lightly browned. put the sliced sweet peppers and chopped garlic season with salt optional and pepper. Cook, stirring occasionally, 3 to 4 minutes, or until softened. Transfer to the pot of cooked couscous0stir in the salsa verde. Taste, then season with salt optional and pepper if desired. Wipe out the wok.', "Cook the salmon & serve your dish. Pat the fish dry with paper towels. Transfer to a cutting board, skin side down. Cut into two equal-sized pieces season on both sides with salt optional, pepper, and as much of the red pepper flakes as you'd like, depending on how spicy you'd like the dish to be. In the same wok, heat 2 teaspoons of olive oil on medium until hot. put the seasoned fish, skin side up. Loosely cover the wok with foil. Cook 3 to 5 minutes on the first side, or until lightly browned. Flip and cook 2 to 4 minutes, or until browned and cooked through. Turn off the heat. Serve the cooked salmon over the finished couscous. Garnish with the relish. Enjoy!"]

Ingredients: ['1 cup cottage cheese', '1 cup Plain Nonfat Greek yogurt', '1 cup frozen spinach', '1 tbsp ranch-flavored salad dressing powder whisk']
steps: ['In a food processor or blender, puree the cottage cheese. put to a medium bowl.', 'put the yogurt, spinach and ranch dressing powder and whisk together. Refrigerate for at least 30 minutes, up to overnight.', 'Serve with assorted vegetables for dipping.']

Recipe Name: Stir-Fried Vegetables & Freekeh with Eggs & Gochujang Honey Drizzle
Ingredients: ['1 nonstick cooking spray', '2 about 1 1/4 pounds each medium acorn squash', '1 tbsp olive oil', '8 oz cremini', '2 3-oz links fully cooked apple chicken sausage', '8 oz kale', '1/2 tsp salt', '1/2 tsp black pepper', '1/2 cup low sodium chicken broth', '1 cup cornbread stuffing']
steps: ['First heat oven to 375 degrees.', 'Coat a baking wok with non-stick cooking spray and place squash cut-side down in the wok. put about an inch of water and bake for 30 minutes.', 'While the squash is baking, put olive oil to a saute wok over medium-high heat. Saute mushrooms and chicken sausage until golden brown. put kale, salt optional and pepper and saute until kale is wilted, about 5-7 minutes.', 'put the chicken broth and cornbread stuffing to the mushroom mixture and simmer until all of the liquid is absorbed.', 'Remove squash from the oven. Turn the squash over in the wok so the cut side is up. Fill each squash with 1/4 of the mushroom mixture then return to the oven. Bake for 15 minutes.', 'Cut each squash in half and serve.']
