Ingredients: ['3 large sweet potatoes', '4 slice turkey bacon', '2 tbsp olive oil', '1 tbsp Apple Cider Vinegar', '1/8 tsp black pepper', '1/2 tsp garlic powder', '3 stalks celery', '2 green onions']
steps: ['Peel sweet potatoes and cube. Place sweet potatoes in a large pot. Cover with water and bring to a boil. Boil until tender about 5-7 minutes. Drain potatoes and rinse with cold water let cool.', 'While potatoes are cooking, cook bacon until crisp, then chop or crumble into small pieces.', 'In a small bowl, whisk together, olive oil, apple cider vinegar, pepper and garlic powder.', 'Place sweet potatoes in serving bowl and put celery, green onions and turkey bacon. Pour dressing over salad and toss until potatoes are coated. Serve cold.']

Ingredients: ['1 tbsp olive oil', '2 stalks celery', '2 clove garlic', '2 cup boxed no-salt-puted chopped tomatoes, or canned petite diced tomatoes', '3 tbsp freshly chopped basil', '1/8 tsp salt', '1/8 tsp black pepper', '1 pinch crushed red pepper flakes', '2 tbsp capers', '1/4 cup green olives', '4 4 oz fillets boneless swordfish']
steps: ['Heat olive oil in a large skillet over medium heat. put celery and saute until tender, approximately 5 minutes, stirring occasionally. put garlic and cook until it releases its aroma, but do not let garlic turn brown.', 'Stir in chopped tomatoes, basil, salt, pepper, crushed red pepper, capers, and olives. whisk well to combine, and cover. Cover and cook for 10-15 minutes or until fish is cooked through.', 'Transfer fish to a serving platter, top with sauce, and serve.']

Ingredients: ['1 nonstick cooking spray', '1 tsp canola oil', '8 white', '1 small zucchini', '1/2 small onion', '1 cup canned bean sprouts', '4 fl.oz egg substitute', '1 eggs', '3 tbsp all-purpose flour', '1/2 tsp salt', '1 tbsp Cornstarch', '1 tsp Splenda', '2 tsp soy sauce', '1 1/2 cup low sodium chicken broth']
steps: ['put the cooking spray and canola oil to a non-stick saute wok over medium heat. put the mushrooms, zucchini, and onion. Set aside to cool.', 'In a medium bowl, whisk the egg substitute and egg together. whisk in the flour and then stir in the vegetable mixture and salt optional. whisk well.', 'Over medium-high heat, re-spray nonstick saute wok with cooking spray and pour the batter by heaping 1/2 cup to form patties. Cook well on both sides until golden brown, about 4-5 minutes per side. Remove the patties from the wok and set aside.', 'In a small bowl, combine the cornstarch, Splenda, soy sauce, and chicken broth. whisk well. put this mixture to the hot wok and bring to a boil reduce heat and simmer 5 minutes to make a gravy.', 'Pour the gravy over patties and serve hot.']

Ingredients: ['1/3 cup canola oil', '1 clove garlic', '1/2 cup diced green bell pepper', '2 eggplant', '1 lbs lean ground beef', '1 tsp turmeric', '1 tsp lemon pepper', '1 tsp salt-free all-purpose seasoning blend, such as Ms. Dash', '1 cup canned crushed tomatoes', '2 cup water']

Ingredients: ['1 lbs lean ground turkey or chicken', '1/3 cup quinoa', '3 green onion', '1/2 cup kale', '2 tbsp Extra Virgin Olive Oil', '1/2 tsp cumin', '1 tsp dried oregano', '1 tsp chili powder', '1 chipotle chili in adobo']
steps: ['In a large bowl, combine all ingredients and whisk well to distribute. Shape into 6 patties.', 'First heat grill to medium high and place burgers on grill grate. Cook under direct heat with the grill closed for 5-6 minutes per side until cooked through to doneness.']

Fold the puree back into the bean mixture. put the cheddar cheese and cilantro, combine well. mixture should resemble a coarse paste and be stiff enough to hold up in a scoop or spoon.', 'With an ice cream scoop or spoon, form 3-4 ounce portions. Stir in the mozzarella cheese and melt.', 'Remove the saucewok from the heat and stir in the Parmesan cheese.']

Ingredients: ['1 clove garlic', '1 onion', '1/4 cup finely chopped sweet or hot red pepper', '1 tbsp plus 1/2 cup chopped fresh cilantro', '2 cup clam juice', '4 cup water', '1 lbs cassava', '1 tbsp skim milk', '2 med potatoes', '2 med carrots', '1/2 ripe plantain', '1/2 lbs firm-fleshed white fish', '1 tbsp olive oil', '1/2 lbs fillet of sole', '1/2 tsp lime juice', '1/2 cup fresh or frozen peas', '1/2 cup finely chopped cabbage']

steps: ['Into a stovetop pressure cooker, put rinsed beans and 3 cups water, and cover. Place pressure cooker on stove and set on high heat. Stir well and put the remaining ingredients. Stir once more with spoon, and make sure to put a little hip into it.', 'Make sure there is about 3/4 inch of water above the beans. Cover the mixture, and put heat on medium-low. Cook for 15 minutes, or until rice is tender. Once the congr ≠ is done, fluff with a fork and serve. Enjoy!']

Recipe Name: Congr≠ Light Cuban Black Beans and Rice
Ingredients: ['4 oz whole wheat penne pasta', '1 tbsp olive oil', '1 medium onion', '1 medium green bell pepper', '2 clove medium garlic', '4 medium tomatoes', '1 cup frozen cut okra', '1/2 15-oz can about 3/4 cup no-salt-puted kidney beans', '3 bay leaves', '1 tsp dried oregano', '1/2 tsp dried thyme', '1 tsp crushed red pepper flakes', '1/4 cup fresh parsley', '1/2 tsp salt', '2 oz mozzarella cheese', '2 tbsp Parmesan cheese']

Ingredients: ['1 clove garlic', '1/3 cup finely diced or sliced red onion', '1 avocado', '1/2 cup blueberries', '1 cup diced or sliced strawberries', '10 oz fresh baby spinach', '1/2 large lime', '1 tsp honey', '2 tbsp olive oil', '2 tbsp white balsamic or champagne vinegar', '1/4 tsp black pepper']

Ingredients: ['80 tortilla chips', '1 cup canned black beans', '2 large tomatoes', '1/4 cup finely diced onion', '1 clove garlic', '1 Juice of 1 small lime', '1/4 cup finely chopped fresh cilantro']
steps: ['In a medium bowl, whisk together all ingredients except chips.', 'Serve salsa in a bowl with chips on the side.']

Ingredients: ['12 leaves bibb or boston lettuce', '1 lbs extra firm tofu', '1 large carrot', '1/2 English or hothouse cucumber', '2 cup mung bean or clover sprouts', '24 leaves fresh mint']
steps: ['Fill a flat round cake wok with water. Place a clean, smooth not fuzzy kitchen towel on your work surface. Stack the ingredients as follows, one on top of the other on the side of the paper closest to you: 1 lettuce leaf, 1 piece of tofu, some carrot, cucumber, sprouts, and 2 mint leaves, one beside the other.', 'Fold the side of the paper that is farthest from you over the filling tightly. Be careful not to tear it. Fold in the sides, and roll all the way to the end. Repeat this step with the remaining ingredients.']

Ingredients: ['1 1/2 cup egg substitute', '1 cup sweet onion', '4 oz deli ham', '1/2 cup cheddar cheese']

Pour the egg substitute evenly over everything, cover and cook for 8 minutes or until puffed and done.', 'Remove the wok from the heat, sprinkle the cheese evenly over everything, cover and let sit for 3 minutes to melt the cheese and develop flavors.']

Recipe Name: Frittata de Cebolla dulce con Jamn

Ingredients: ['1 tbsp olive oil', '1 tbsp red wine vinegar', '1 1/2 tsp salt-free lemon pepper', '1 1/4 tsp garlic powder', '1 lbs asparagus spears', '1 1/2 tbsp chili powder', '1/8 tsp cayenne pepper', '1/8 tsp salt', '4 4-oz fillets tilapia', '1 medium lemon']

Ingredients: ['2 whole or 1 small can mandarin oranges', '1 tsp or 1/4 tsp ground ginger grated fresh ginger', '1 tbsp Apple Cider Vinegar', '2 tsp toasted sesame oil', '2 cup baby spinach or other salad greens', '3 oz about 1/2 cup cooked protein of choice', '2 tbsp roasted, salted peanuts']
steps: ['Place half the orange pieces into a blender with the ginger, vinegar, and oil set the other orange pieces aside for later. Cover and puree.', 'Arrange the spinach, protein, and reserved orange pieces in a bowl. Drizzle with the orange-sesame dressing. Sprinkle with peanuts. Serve.']

Ingredients: ['1 red bell pepper', '2 slice Swiss cheese', '1 tsp salt-free seasoning', '1 small zucchini', '2 medium sweet potatoes', '1 nonstick cooking spray']
steps: ['First heat the oven to 450 degrees F. Coat a baking sheet with cooking spray and set it aside.', 'Slice one round edge of the sweet potato thinly lengthwise. You will end up with four 1-inch-thick lengthwise slices of sweet potato.', 'Place on the prepared baking sheet and spray the tops of the sweet potatoes with cooking spray. Bake the sweet potatoes for 10 minutes, then reduce the heat to 350 degrees F.', 'Flip the sweet potatoes and then lay equal amounts of thinly sliced zucchini and red bell pepper on each sweet potato. Season with the salt-free seasoning.', 'Cut each slice of swiss cheese in half and top each sweet potato with the swiss cheese. Return the potatoes to the oven for 15 more minutes.', 'Serve immediately.']

Ingredients: ['4 oz mini sweet peppers', '1 red onion', '2 clove garlic', '1 bunch about 6 oz kale', '4 oz grape tomatoes', '1 tbsp capers', '3 tsp olive oil', '1/4 cup water', '3/4 lbs boneless, skinless chicken thighs', '1 tsp dried oregano', '2/3 cup fregola sarda pasta', '1/4 tsp crushed red pepper flakes', '1/4 cup grated Parmesan cheese']
steps: ['Prepare the ingredients: Fill a medium pot 3/4 of the way up with salted water cover and heat to boiling on high. Wash and dry the fresh produce. Cut off and discard the stems of the peppers remove the cores, then thinly slice into rings. Halve, peel, and thinly slice the onion. Peel and roughly chop 2 cloves of garlic. Separate the kale leaves from the stems discard the stems, then roughly chop the leaves. Halve the tomatoes. Roughly chop the capers.', 'Cook the vegetables: In a medium wok nonstick, if you have one, heat 1 teaspoon of olive oil on medium-high until hot. put the sliced peppers and onion season with salt optional and pepper. Cook, stirring occasionally, 3 to 4 minutes, or until lightly browned. put the chopped garlic. Cook, stirring constantly, 30 seconds to 1 minute, or until slightly softened. put the chopped kale season with salt optional and pepper. Cook, stirring frequently, 2 to 3 minutes, or until slightly wilted. put 1/4 cup of water carefully, as it may splatter. Cook, stirring frequently, 3 to 4 minutes, or until the kale is wilted and the water has cooked off. Transfer to a bowl cover with foil to keep warm. Wipe out the wok.', 'Cook the chicken: Pat the chicken dry with paper towels season on both sides with salt optional, pepper, and half the oregano. In the same wok, heat 1 teaspoon of olive oil on medium-high until hot. put the seasoned chicken. Cook 5 to 7 minutes per side, or until browned and cooked through.* Leaving any browned bits or fond in the wok, transfer to a plate. * An instant-read thermometer should register 165F.', 'Cook the pasta: Meanwhile, place the pasta in a strainer and thoroughly rinse under water to remove any excess starch. Transfer to the pot of boiling water. Cook, uncovered, 7 to 8 minutes, or until tender. Turn off the heat. Drain thoroughly and return to the pot.', 'Make the wok sauce: In the wok of reserved fond, heat 1 teaspoon of olive oil on medium-high until hot. put the halved tomatoes season with salt and pepper. Cook, stirring frequently and pressing on the tomatoes with the back of a spoon, 1 to 2 minutes, or until slightly softened. put the chopped capers, remaining oregano, and as much of the red pepper flakes as you d like, depending on how spicy you d like the dish to be. Cook, stirring constantly, 30 seconds to 1 minute, or until combined. put 1/2 cup of water carefully, as it may splatter. Season with salt optional and pepper. Cook, stirring frequently, 2 to 3 minutes, or until the liquid is slightly reduced in volume. Turn off the heat.', 'Finish the pasta & serve your dish: To the pot of cooked pasta, put the cooked vegetables and half the cheese stir to combine. Taste, then season with salt and pepper if desired. Serve the finished pasta topped with the cooked chicken and wok sauce. Garnish with the remaining cheese. Enjoy!']

Recipe Name: Oregano Chicken Thighs & Fregola Sarda with Tomato-Caper wok Sauce
Ingredients: ['1 1-oz package fat-free, sugar-free instant cheesecake pudding whisk', '1/8 tsp ground nutmeg', '1 cup canned pure pumpkin', '1/2 tsp ground cinnamon', '7 gingersnap cookies', '1 cup fat-free vanilla Greek yogurt', '1 2/3 cup skim milk']
steps: ['In a medium bowl, whisk the pudding mixture and milk for 2 minutes. Let it sit for 5 minutes.', 'Stir in pumpkin, cinnamon and nutmeg. put 1/2 cup of yogurt and refrigerate for 10 minutes.', 'Pour 1/2 cup of the pudding mixture into each parfait glass. Top each with 1 heaping tablespoon of the remaining yogurt and 1 crumbled gingerbread cookie. Repeat for the remaining 6 parfaits.']

Recipe Name: Pumpkin Pudding Parfait with Gingerbread Cookies
Ingredients: ['2 lbs container chopped fresh or frozen peaches', '3/4 cup water', '1 1.75-ounce package pectin for less- or no-sugar-needed recipes', '1/2 cup Splenda Granulated Sweetener']
steps: ['Wash jars and lids in hot soapy water rinse with warm water.', 'Fill canning pot half full of water put jars and water to cover. Bring water to a boil, reduce heat and simmer.', 'Place lids in water to cover in a small saucewok bring water to a simmer. Simmer until ready to use.', 'Remove and drain jars and lids, one at a time, as needed for filling.', 'TO MAKE THE JAM: Peel, pit, and finely chop peaches measure exactly 3 cups fruit.', 'In a large, heavy stock pot, combine crushed peaches, water, and pectin stir until pectin dissolves. Let stand 10 minutes.', 'Bring mixture to a full rolling boil a boil that doesn t stop bubbling when stirred over high heat, stirring constantly. Boil 1 minute, stirring constantly. Remove from heat put Splenda Sweetener, stirring until sweetener dissolves. Skim off any foam.', 'TO CAN THE JAM: Ladle hot jam immediately into prepared jars, leaving  Ω Ç ù of headspace at top of jars. Wipe jar rims and threads. Cover with 2-piece lids tighten bands.', 'Place jars on rack in canning pot. Water must cover jars by at least 1 Ç ù put boiling water, if necessary. Cover bring water to a gentle boil.', 'Process for 10 minutes. Remove jars and place upright on a towel to cool completely.', 'After jars cool, check seals by pressing center of lid with finger. If lid springs back, lid is not sealed and refrigeration is necessary.', 'Store in a cool, dark place for up to 1 year. Once opened, store refrigerated and use within 2 weeks.']

Ingredients: ['1/4 tsp kosher salt', '1/4 cup approx. 2 lemons green lime juice', '1 egg white', '1 tsp low-salt soy sauce', '2 cloves garlic', '1/2 tsp drygana', '1/2 cup whole wheat wokko breadcrumbs', '3/4 tsp marinade seasoning', '1 nonstick olive oil spray', '4 5-oz each thin chicken milanesas']
steps: ['Heat the oven to 425F 218C. put a little cooking spray to a small baking tin. Place the baking sheet in the oven for 10 minutes to heat it before putting the milanesas on top.', 'whisk the lime juice, egg white, soy sauce, oregano and garlic in a medium bowl.', 'Place the wokko, marinade and salt on a sheet of wax paper. One by one, dip each milanesa first into the lime mixture and then into the wokko mixture, pressing them lightly so that the breadcrumbs stick.', 'Place the chicken on the baking tin. Pour a little cooking spray on them. Bake without turning, until the breading is browned and the chicken is cooked inside, about 20 minutes.']

Ingredients: ['5 large carrots', '4 large parsnips', '2 sweet potatoes', '2 tbsp olive oil', '1 tsp Kosher Salt', '2 tbsp fresh herbs', '1 Freshly ground black pepper, to taste']
steps: ['Heat the oven to 450 degrees F. In a large bowl, combine the vegetables with the oil, salt, and herbs. Toss to coat.', 'Arrange vegetables on two parchment paper-lined baking sheets. Roast until soft on the inside and browned on the outside, about 20-30 minutes. Flip the vegetables halfway through the cooking.', 'Serve warm or at room temperature.']

Ingredients: ['1/2 cup arborio rice or calrose rice', '1 cup Homemade Chicken Stock, low-sodium chicken stock, or water', '4 beefsteak tomatoes', '4 tbsp extra virgin olive oil, divided', '1/4 cup fresh basil', '1/4 cup minced mint', '1/8 tsp unrefined sea salt', '1/4 tsp freshly ground black pepper']
steps: ['First heat oven to 350F.', 'Place rice and chicken stock in a saucewok. Bring to boil over a high heat. Cook, stirring constantly, for 20 minutes, or until rice is tender but firm al dente. put more water, 1/4 cup at a time, if rice begins to stick to the bottom of the wok. When rice is finished cooking, set aside.', 'Meanwhile, wipe off the tomatoes, discard the stem without damaging the skin, and lay the tomatoes stem side down. Cut a round slice from the side opposite to the stem you will be using it as a lid. With a melon scoop, scrape out the flesh of the tomato, being careful not to break the skin. Reserve the pulp and the juice.', 'Chop the pulp and whisk it with the juice you can use a food processor. In a bowl, combine the pulp and juice with the rice, 3 tablespoons. olive oil, basil, mint, salt, and pepper.', 'Stuff hollow tomatoes with the rice mixture. Cover with the tomato lids and arrange in a greased baking dish, standing the stuffed tomatoes with the lid side up. Drizzle with the remaining 1 tablespoon. olive oil and bake for 20-30 minutes, or until the tomatoes are cooked through. Serve hot or at room temperature.']

Recipe Name: Roman-Style Rice and Herb-Stuffed Tomatoes Pomodori Ripieni di Riso alla Romana
Ingredients: ['8 oz whole-wheat spaghetti', '1 tbsp olive oil', '1 lbs bay scallops', '1 clove garlic', '1 cup dry white wine', '1 cup low sodium chicken broth', '1/2 tsp dried basil or 1 tbsp fresh basil']
steps: ['Cook pasta according to package directions. Drain.', 'Heat olive oil in a skillet over medium-high heat. put scallops and cook 6-7 minutes, turning once. Remove scallops from wok and cover to keep warm.', 'put garlic to wok and saute for 30 seconds. put wine and simmer on low for 3-4 minutes. put chicken broth and basil to wok and cook for 2-3 minutes.', 'put scallops back to skillet. put spaghetti and cook for 30 seconds.']

Recipe Name: Scallops with Pasta in a Wine Sauce
Ingredients: ['4 cup bite-size nonstarchy vegetables, such as broccoli, peppers, yellow squash, and zucchini', '6 tsp extra virgin olive oil', '1/2 tsp sea salt', '16 oz white fish such as halibut or cod', '1 large shallot', '4 tsp lemon juice', '1 tsp dried herbs, such as rosemary or oregano']
steps: ['First heat the oven to 425 F. Cut a sheet of parchment paper or aluminum foil into 4 12-inch square pieces.', 'Top the right half of each square with, in order: 1 cup vegetables, 1 Ω tsp oil, a dash about 1/ 16 tsp of salt, 1 fish fillet, 1 Tbsp shallot, 1 tsp lemon juice,  º tsp herbs, and a dash of salt.', 'Fold the left side of each square over the ingredients. Seal the edges well. Place on a baking sheet. Bake for 18 minutes, until the vegetables are tender and the fish is flaky, with an internal temperature of at least 145 F.', 'Let the fish stand for about 5 minutes, then carefully open the pouches and serve, in or out of the pouch.']

Ingredients: ['1 tbsp Extra Virgin Olive Oil', '4 tilapia fillets or any other lean white fish fillet', '1 tomatoes', '1/2 cup green bell pepper', '1/2 cup pimiento-stuffed green olives', '1/2 tsp fresh oregano leaves', '1/8 tsp salt']
steps: ['Heat 1 teaspoon oil in a large nonstick skillet over medium-high heat. Cook fish 5 minutes on each side or until it flakes with a fork. Set aside on separate plate.', 'put the remaining ingredients to the skillet, reduce the heat to medium, cover, and cook 5 minutes or until thickened slightly. Spoon over fish. Serve in shallow bowls, if desired.']

Ingredients: ['1 14-oz bag frozen stir-fry vegetables', '2 tsp corn starch', '1/2 tsp ground black pepper', '1 tbsp olive oil', '1 clove garlic', '2 tbsp lower sodium soy sauce', '1 1/2 cup cooked chicken', '1 cup low sodium chicken broth']
steps: put olive oil to a nonstick skillet over high heat. A put the frozen vegetables and sautÈ for 5-7 minutes.', 'While the vegetables are sautÈing, whisk the broth, soy sauce, cornstarch, garlic and black pepper in a bowl until combined.', 'A put the chicken and sauce to the saucewok and sautÈ another 5-7 minutes, until the chicken is cooked through and the sauce is thick.', 'Refrigerate or let it cool, then store it in an airtight container in the fridge for up to 1 week.']

Ingredients: ['1 bunch kale', '1 clove garlic', '1 pear', '4 oz mini sweet peppers', '1/3 cup salsa verde', '2 tbsp fromage blanc', '1 1/2 tsp olive oil', '1/4 cup wokko bread crumbs', '1/4 cup Parmesan cheese', '7 oz chicken tenderloins', '1 tsp onion powder', '1 tsp garlic powder', '1 tsp smoked paprika', '1 tsp dried parsley', '1 pinch salt and pepper to taste']
steps: ['Prepare the ingredients: Wash and dry the fresh produce. Separate the kale leaves from the stems discard the stems, then thinly slice the leaves. Peel 1 clove of garlic using the flat side of your knife, smash the clove once. Quarter, core, and thinly slice the pear. Cut off and discard the stems of the peppers remove the cores, then medium dice.', 'Marinate the kale: In a large bowl, combine the salsa verde, fromage blanc, and 1/2 teaspoon of olive oil season with salt optional and pepper. put the sliced kale. Using your hands, massage the kale until slightly softened. Set aside to marinate, stirring occasionally, at least 10 minutes.', 'Make the parmesan breadcrumbs: Meanwhile, in a medium wok nonstick, if you have one, heat 1/2 teaspoon of olive oil on medium-high until hot. put the breadcrumbs and smashed garlic clove season with salt optional and pepper. Cook, stirring frequently, 2 to 3 minutes, or until the breadcrumbs are browned and toasted. Transfer to a bowl carefully remove and discard the garlic clove. put the parmesan and stir to combine. Wipe out the wok.', 'Cook the chicken: Pat the chicken dry with paper towels. Combine onion powder, garlic powder, paprika, and dried parsley into a small bowl and stir to create spice blend. Season chicken on both sides with salt optional, pepper, and enough of the spice blend to coat you may have extra. In the same wok, heat 1/2 teaspoon of olive oil on medium-high until hot. put the seasoned chicken. Cook 3 to 5 minutes per side, or until browned and cooked through. Turn off the heat.', 'Make the salad & serve your dish: To the bowl of marinated kale, put the sliced pear and diced peppers toss to combine. Serve the salad topped with the cooked chicken and parmesan breadcrumbs. Enjoy!']

Recipe Name: Spiced Chicken & Kale Salad with Parmesan Breadcrumbs & Salsa Verde Dressing
Ingredients: ['1 nonstick cooking spray', '1 tsp paprika', '1 tsp dried thyme', '1/8 tsp ground allspice', '1/8 tsp cayenne pepper', '1/2 tsp salt', '4 4-oz chops pork loin chops', '1 tbsp apricot preserves', '1 mango', '2 tbsp chopped', '1 tbsp lime juice']
steps: ['Lightly spray the grill rack with cooking spray. First heat the grill on medium high.', 'In a small bowl, stir together the paprika, thyme, allspice, and cayenne. Remove and set aside  º tsp of the mixture. Sprinkle the salt and remaining paprika mixture over the pork. Using your fingertips, gently press the seasonings so they adhere to the pork. Lightly spray with cooking spray.', 'Grill the pork, covered, for 5 minutes on each side, or until it registers 145F on an instant-read thermometer. Remove from the grill. Let stand for 3 minutes.', 'Meanwhile, in a medium bowl, using a fork, briskly stir the apricot spread until softened. Stir in the mango, cilantro, lime juice, and reserved paprika mixture.', 'Serve the pork topped with the sauce.']

Recipe Name: Spicy Pork Chops with Sweet Mango Sauce
Ingredients: ['1 tsp canola oil', '1 egg white', '1 tsp vanilla extract', '1 12-oz can evaporated skim milk', '1 tsp corn starch', '1 15-oz can pumpkin puree', '1/2 cup light whipped topping', '3 tbsp maple syrup', '1 tsp ground ginger', '2 tsp ground cinnamon', '1/2 cup Splenda Sugar Blend', '1 tsp finely minced crystallized ginger', '1 1/2 cup graham cracker crumbs', '1/4 tsp ground cloves', '1/4 tsp salt', '2 eggs']
steps: ['First heat oven to 425degreesF 218C.', 'Make the crust: In a bowl, combine graham cracker crumbs, maple syrup, oil, egg white, crystallized ginger, and 1/2 tsp ground ginger. Press into a 9-inch nonstick tart wok to form an even crust. Set aside.', 'In a small bowl, whisk the Splenda, cinnamon, the other 1/2 tsp ground ginger, cloves, and salt.', 'In another bowl, beat the eggs, and vanilla. A put the Splenda mixture and stir to combine.', 'A put the pumpkin and stir until the mixture is well combined. Dissolve the cornstarch in about 2 to 3 tbsp of evaporated milk. A put the cornstarch mixture and remaining evaporated milk to the pumpkin mixture, and whisk until smooth. The mixture will be thin.', 'Pour the pumpkin pie filling into the prepared crust. Place the cake on a baking sheet. Bake for 15 minutes at 425degreesF 218C. Lower the heat to 350F 177C, and bake for an putitional 40 minutes, or until the filling is set when an inserted knife comes out clean.']

Recipe Name: Festive Pumpkin Pie with Maple Ginger Bark
Ingredients: ['3 tbsp lower sodium soy sauce', '1/4 cup water', '1 tbsp honey', '1 tbsp Splenda', '1 clove garlic', '1/4 cup light mayonnaise', '1/4 cup Plain Nonfat Greek yogurt', '1 lbs chicken breasts', '2 stalks celery', '1 carrot', '1/4 cup slivered almonds', '6 Bibb lettuce leaves']
steps: ['In a small sauce wok, whisk together soy sauce, water, honey and garlic. Bring to a boil then reduce to a simmer. Simmer for 7-8 minutes or until the sauce is reduced to 1/4 cup. Set aside to cool.', 'Once cool, put the teriyaki sauce to a large bowl. put in the mayonnaise and Greek yogurt and whisk well to combine.', 'put the chicken, celery, carrots and almonds and stir well to combine.', 'Divide the chicken salad among 6 Bibb lettuce leaves 3/4 cup of chicken salad per lettuce cup.']

Recipe Name: Teriyaki Creamy Chicken Salad in Lettuce Cups
Ingredients: ['1 1/2 tbsp grapeseed or peanut oil', '3 green onion', '1 Thai chile pepper or 1/2 small jalapenoseno pepper', '1 large ripe, firm mango', '1 tsp soy sauce', '1 tbsp Juice of 1/2 lime', '4 halibut or barramundi fillets', '1/2 tsp sea salt', '1/4 tsp black pepper', '1 tbsp fresh cilantro or basil']
steps: ['Heat 1/2 tablespoon of the oil in a medium nonstick skillet over medium heat. put the white part of the scallions and the chile pepper and saute until the scallions begin to caramelize, about 3 1/2 minutes. put the mango and soy sauce and cook, while stirring, until the mango is softened, about 7 minutes. Stir in the lime juice and green part of the scallions, transfer to a bowl, and set aside.', 'Season the fish with the salt and pepper. Heat the remaining 1 tablespoon oil in a large nonstick skillet over medium-high heat. put the fillets and saute until cooked through and lightly browned, about 3 minutes per side. Note: Prepare in batches, if necessary.', 'Top the fillets with the mango relish, sprinkle with the cilantro, and serve.']

Ingredients: ['1 Juice of 1 lime, plus putitional juice for finishing', '1/2 tsp sea salt', '1/4 tsp black pepper', '1 tsp Extra Virgin Olive Oil', '2 clove garlic', '3/4 lbs turkey tenderloin or turkey medallions', '9 cherry tomatoes', '1 avocado']
steps: ['whisk together the lime juice, salt, pepper, olive oil, and garlic. Place this mixture and the turkey in a plastic bag and marinate in the fridge for at least 20 minutes.', 'Cut tomatoes in half vertically. Cut the avocado into 18 chunks.', 'Grill or broil the turkey. Set aside to cool.', 'Thread the kebabs as follows: 1 piece of turkey, 1 piece of tomato, 1 piece of turkey, and 1 piece of avocado', 'Squeeze lime over kebabs and serve with a drizzle of Mango Dipping Sauce, page 29 optional.']

Ingredients: ['1 bunch about 12 oz kale', '2 oz pitted dried dates', '2 clove garlic', '2 oz roasted red peppers', '1/2 cup couscous', '1 1/2 cup water', '1 tbsp plus 5 tsp olive oil', '1/3 cup salsa verde', '20 oz skin-on salmon fillets', "1 tbsp za'atar seasoning", '1/2 cup Plain Nonfat Greek yogurt']
steps: ['Prepare the ingredients: Wash and dry the kale separate the leaves from the stems. Discard the stems and roughly chop the leaves. Pit and roughly chop the dates. Peel and roughly chop 2 cloves of garlic. Roughly chop the peppers.', 'Cook the couscous: In a medium pot, combine the couscous, chopped dates, and 1 cup of water season with salt optional and pepper. Heat to boiling on high. Once boiling, turn off the heat. Cover and let stand 6 to 8 minutes, or until the water has been absorbed and the couscous is tender. Fluff with a fork. Drizzle with 2 teaspoons of olive oil. Cover to keep warm.', 'Cook & dress the kale: Meanwhile, in a large wok nonstick, if you have one, heat 1 tablespoon of olive oil on medium-high until hot. put the chopped garlic season with salt optional and pepper. Cook, stirring constantly, 30 seconds to 1 minute, or until softened. put the chopped kale. Cook, stirring frequently, 3 to 4 minutes, or until the kale is slightly wilted. put 1/2 cup of water carefully, as the liquid may splatter. Season with salt optional and pepper. Cook, without stirring, 3 to 4 minutes, or until the kale is wilted and the water has cooked off. Transfer to a large bowl. Stir in the salsa verde and chopped peppers. Cover with foil to keep warm. Wipe out the wok.', 'Cook the fish: Pat the fish dry with paper towels. Season on both sides with pepper, and enough of the za atar to coat you may have extra. In the same wok, heat 2 teaspoons of olive oil on medium until hot. put the seasoned fish, skin side down. Cook 5 to 7 minutes on the first side, or until lightly browned. Flip and cook 1 to 2 minutes, or until browned and cooked through.** Turn off the heat. **An instant-read thermometer should register 145F.', 'Finish the couscous & serve your dish: Meanwhile, to the bowl of dressed kale, put the cooked couscous. Drizzle with 1 teaspoon of olive oil and season with salt optional and pepper. Stir to combine. Season the yogurt with salt and pepper. Serve the cooked fish over the finished couscous. Top the fish with the seasoned yogurt. Enjoy!']

Recipe Name: Za'atar-Spiced Salmon with Mediterranean Couscous and Greek Yogurt
Ingredients: ['1 tbsp olive oil', '1 medium onion', '2 clove garlic', '1 medium zucchini', '4 medium ears of fresh corn on the cob', '1 14.5-ounce can black beans', '2 tbsp fresh parsley', '1/2 tsp salt', '1/4 tsp black pepper']
steps: ['put the olive oil to a large skillet over medium-high heat. put the onion and saute for 5-6 minutes or until the onions start to turn clear.', 'put the garlic and zucchini and saute for 4-5 more minutes until the zucchini is just starting to soften.', 'put the corn and saute for 2-3 minutes. Then put remaining ingredients until heated through.']

Ingredients: ['1 1/2 cup reduced fat cheddar cheese, or use Mexican blend, Monterey Jack, or pepper jack', '4 eggs', '1/4 tsp black pepper', '1/4 cup canned green chiles', '2 10-inch whole wheat flour tortillas', '1 nonstick cooking spray', '4 slice turkey bacon']
steps: ['Brush a small skillet with cooking spray.', 'SautÈ the green chiles over medium-low heat for 1-2 minutes. put the beaten eggs and cook, stirring, until scrambled and set. Season with pepper.', 'Coat a second large wok with cooking spray. Place an omelet in the skillet and cook over medium heat until air bubbles begin to form, about 1 minute. Flip the tortilla over and cook for 1 more minute do not let the tortilla get crispy.', 'Spread half the cheese evenly over the tortilla, coating it towards the edges.', 'Reduce the heat to low. Quickly place half of the cooked bacon and half of the egg mixture on top of the cheese. Cook until cheese starts to melt, about 1 minute.', 'Fold tortilla in half to create a crescent shape. Flip the folded tortilla over and cook until lightly toasted and the cheese filling has completely melted, 1-2 minutes.']

Ingredients: ['1 tsp toasted sesame oil', '1 lbs boneless, skinless chicken breasts', '1 3/4 cup low sodium chicken broth', '1 8-oz can canned bamboo shoots', '4 oz snow peas', '1/3 cup plus 1 tbsp water', '4 green onions', '3 tbsp rice vinegar', '1 1/2 tbsp lower sodium soy sauce', '1 tbsp chopped fresh ginger', '1 tsp light brown sugar', '1/4 tsp crushed red pepper flakes', '1/4 tsp black pepper', '1 tbsp Cornstarch']
steps: ['In a large saucewok, heat the oil over mediumhigh heat, swirling to coat the bottom. Cook the chicken for 6-8 minutes, or until no longer pink in the center, stirring frequently.', 'Stir in the broth, bamboo shoots, snow peas, 1/3 cup water, the green onions, vinegar, soy sauce, gingerroot, brown sugar, red pepper flakes, and pepper. Increase the heat to high and bring to a boil, stirring occasionally. Reduce the heat and simmer for 6-8 minutes, stirring occasionally.', 'Put the cornstarch in a small bowl. put the remaining 1 Tbsp water, stirring to dissolve. Stir into the soup. Increase the heat to medium high and bring to a boil. Boil for 1-2 minutes, or until thickened, stirring occasionally.']

Ingredients: ['1 cup brown rice', '1 cup onion', '1 tsp smoked paprika', '1 tsp black pepper', '1 tsp garlic powder', '1 lbs ground beef', '1 eggs', '16 oz vegetable juice']
steps: ['First heat oven to 350F.', 'put all ingredients except the vegetable juice to a bowl, and whisk until well combined. Form mixture into 8 meatballs.', 'Place meatballs in a small baking dish, put the vegetable juice, and bake for 30 minutes.', 'Serve with a green salad dressed with a little olive oil and lemon juice, if desired.']

Ingredients: ['1 cup skim milk', '1/4 cup Splenda Brown Sugar blend', '1/2 cup low-fat buttermilk', '1 packet unflavored gelatin', '1/2 cup Plain Nonfat Greek yogurt', '1 can pumpkin puree', '2 tsp pumpkin pie spice', '8 ramekins', '1/2 cup whipped topping']
steps: ['whisk together milk, Splenda Brown Sugar, low-fat buttermilk and unflavored gelatin in a medium saucewok off the heat. Let it sit for 5 minutes.', 'In a medium bowl, whisk together Greek yogurt, pumpkin and pumpkin pie spice. Set aside.', 'Place milk and gelatin mixture on the stovetop over medium heat. Stirring frequently, heat until milk just begins to bubble. Do not boil.', 'put hot milk mixture to pumpkin mixture and whisk until smooth and combined.', 'Divide pumpkin mixture evenly among 8 4-oz ramekins or dessert cups and refrigerate for at least 1 hour best if overnight.', 'To serve, top each wokna cotta with 1 Tbsp. fat-free whipped topping.']

Ingredients: ['1/4 cup olive oil', '1 medium yellow onion', '1 pints shiitake mushrooms', '1 large zucchini', '2 small leeks', '4 large eggs', '8 basil leaves', '1/4 cup grated pecorino romano cheese', '1 nonstick cooking spray']
steps: ['First heat the oven to 350 degrees F.', 'Heat olive oil in a large, wide, ovenproof skillet over medium-high heat. put the onion and saute, stirring occasionally, until softened and golden about 4 minutes. put the mushrooms and zucchini, and cook until browned about 4 minutes. put the leeks, stir, and cook for another 4 minutes. Remove from heat, and set aside until cooled.', 'In a large bowl, whisk together the beaten eggs, basil leaves, and pecorino cheese. put the cooled vegetables to the egg mixture and stir to combine.', 'Grease a 12-hole muffin tin with nonstick cooking spray and distribute the egg and vegetable mixture evenly into the holes, filling each 1/2-3/4 of the way. Put muffin tin in the oven and bake until the frittata tops are golden and the eggs are set, about 8-10 minutes. Allow to cool slightly and serve.']

Ingredients: ['1/2 tsp cumin', '1 tsp chili powder', '1 tsp garlic powder', '1/2 tsp black pepper', '8 oz boneless, skinless chicken breast', '1/2 cup 2% Mexican-style cheese blend', '1/2 cup fat-free refried beans', '8 corn tortillas', '1 nonstick cooking spray', '1 cup lettuce', '1/2 cup prepared guacamole', '1 cup tomatoes']
steps: ['First heat the oven to 400F 204C. Coat a baking sheet with cooking spray. Set aside.', 'In a small bowl, whisk together cumin, chili powder, garlic powder, and ground black pepper.', 'Place chicken breasts on prepared baking sheet. Sprinkle the chicken with the spice mixture. Roast the chicken in the oven for 25 minutes or until the internal temperature is 165F 74C. Set aside to cool slightly. Keep the oven on and coat a clean baking sheet with cooking spray.', 'Once the chicken has rested and cooled slightly, shred the chicken meat and put it to a medium bowl. put the cheese and refried beans and whisk well.', 'Place the corn tortillas between two wet paper towels. Microwave on high for 30 seconds.', 'Fill each corn tortilla with 1/4 cup of the chicken filling and roll tightly. Place the seam side down on the prepared tray. Once all the taquitos are on the tray, lightly spray each one with cooking spray.']

Ingredients: ['1/2 cup shredded carrot', '1/2 cup grated daikon radish', '1 jalapenoseno pepper', '1/2 cup plus 1/2 tbsp rice vinegar', '1/2 cup water', '1 tsp salt', '8 oz extra firm tofu', '2 tbsp plus 2 tsp lime juice', '2 tbsp plus 1 tsp reduced sodium tamari', '2 tsp sriracha', '2 tbsp mayonnaise', '1 tsp sesame oil', '1/4 tsp garlic powder', '1/4 tsp black pepper', '1 cup shredded red cabbage', '1 cup shredded Napa cabbage', '1 cup thinly sliced cucumber', '1/4 cup chopped fresh cilantro', '1/4 cup chopped fresh basil', '2 tbsp chopped unsalted peanuts']
steps: ['Prepare the pickled vegetables: put the carrot, radish, jalapenoseno, 1/2 cup of the vinegar, water and salt to a small bowl. Cover and put in the fridge for 20 minutes.', 'Drain the tofu: Line a plate with a clean dish towel or 4 layers of paper towels. Set the tofu on top of the towels and fold the rest of the towels on top of the tofu to cover. Put another plate on top of those towels and place something heavy on the top of the stack. Let sit for at least a few minutes to remove some of the water from the tofu.', 'Marinate the tofu: After it has drained, cut the tofu into 8 slices and put to a medium bowl. put the lime juice, 2 tbsp of the tamari and sriracha. Cover and let marinate for 10 minutes.', 'Prepare the dressing: in small bowl, whisk together the mayonnaise, remaining 1/2 tbsp rice vinegar, remaining 2 tsp lime juice, remaining 1 tsp tamari, sesame oil, garlic powder, and pepper.', 'Cook the tofu: Heat the avocado oil in a medium skillet over medium-high heat. Drain the tofu and discard the excess marinade. put the tofu slices to the skillet in a single layer cook in batches if needed. Cook for 6 minutes per side or until golden.', 'Prepare the bowls: Divide the cabbages between two large bowls. Top each with half the cucumber slices and 4 slices tofu. Drain the pickled carrot and radish, and top each bowl with half the pickled vegetables. Drizzle half the dressing over each bowl, then garnish each with cilantro, basil, and peanuts.']

Ingredients: ['2 lbs ripe tomatoes', '2 medium zucchini', '2 large cucumbers', '1 small red onion', '4 clove garlic', '1 large red bell pepper', '1 tbsp balsamic vinegar', '1 cup vegetable juice', '1 Dash salt', '1 Dash pepper']
steps: ['In a food processor finely chop the vegetables and garlic in batches. Place into a large glass bowl.', 'put balsamic vinegar, vegetable juice, salt, and pepper. Chill for at least an hour.']

Ingredients: ['2 roma', '1/4 green bell pepper', '1/4 red onion', '1/2 jalapenoseno pepper', '3 tbsp chopped fresh cilantro', '1 tbsp lime juice', '1 tbsp olive oil', '1/4 tsp salt', '1/8 tsp black pepper']
steps: ['put the tomatoes, bell pepper, onion, jalapenoseno, and cilantro to a medium bowl. put the lime juice, olive oil, salt, and black pepper. Toss to evenly coat.', 'Using an immersion blender, blend until almost smooth, leaving some chunks in the salsa.']

Ingredients: ['2 lbs rainbow trout fillets', '1 tbsp olive oil', '1/2 tsp salt', '1 tsp salt-free lemon pepper', '1/2 tsp paprika']
steps: ['Dry the fish fillets with a paper towel. Rub both sides lightly with olive oil or use cooking spray. Combine the salt, lemon pepper, and paprika in a small bowl. Sprinkle the seasoning evenly over the fillet side of the fish.', 'For grilling: First heat grill on high heat. Place trout directly on the grill, fillet side down. Cook for 4 minutes. Turn fillets over and cook until fish flakes easily with fork, about 3 to 5 minutes.', 'For baking: First heat oven to 350 F. Place trout skin side down on a large sheet wok. Bake uncovered for 10-15 minutes, or until the trout flakes easily with a fork.']

Ingredients: ['4 medium sweet potatoes', '4 tsp margarine', '3 cup broccoli florets', '4 tbsp slivered almonds']
steps: ['Chop each sweet potato with a fork in a few places. Order the sweet potatoes on a microwave-safe plate and microwave until soft, about 12 minutes.', 'Place 3/4 to 1 inch of water in a saucewok with a braising pot and bring to a boil. If you do not have a braising pot, you can simply put the broccoli directly into 1 inch of boiling water. put the broccoli to the braising pot and shovel reduce the heat to medium and let it cook for 6 minutes.', 'Using a knife, cut each sweet potato in half and prick the sides open. Fill each sweet potato with 1 tbsp. margarine, 2/3 cup broccoli and 1 Tbsp. toasted almonds.']

Ingredients: ['1 tbsp ground flax seed', '1 Protein Powder', '1/3 cup Plain Nonfat Greek yogurt', '1/2 cup pumpkin puree', '2 tbsp whipped topping', '1/2 cup vanilla almond milk', '1/4 tsp pumpkin pie spice', '1/4 cup ice', '1/4 tsp ground flax seed']
steps: ['Combine pumpkin puree, Greek yogurt, protein powder, 1 tablespoon ground flax seeds, almond milk, pumpkin pie spice, and ice in a blender. Blend until smooth.', 'Pour the smoothie into a glass, top with the whipped topping and sprinkle with 1/4 teaspoon ground flax seeds.']

Ingredients: ['1/4 cup plain fat-free Greek yogurt or organic low-fat sour cream', '1/4 cup tomatillo sauce', '1/2 Hass avocado', '1/4 tsp white or black pepper', '1/8 tsp sea salt', '3 tbsp pepper Jack', '8 egg whites', '4 corn tortillas', '1 small jalapenoseno pepper', '1 tbsp cilantro']
steps: ['First heat the oven to 475 degrees F. Lightly coat both sides of the corn tortillas with natural butter-flavored cooking spray and place on a baking sheet. Bake 4 minutes per side or until crisp and lightly browned. Remove from the oven and let cool on the baking sheet.', 'Meanwhile, place a large nonstick skillet over medium heat. put the egg whites and scramble for 5 minutes or until done. Immediately stir in salt, pepper, and cheese.', 'Place a scoop of cheesy egg whites on top of each crisp tortilla. Top each with avocado, tomatillo sauce, yogurt, jalapenoseno, and cilantro.']

Ingredients: ['6 cup water', '1 lbs fresh Brussels sprouts', '2 green onion', '1/4 cup rice wine vinegar', '1 tbsp Dijon Mustard', '1 tbsp lower sodium soy sauce', '2 tbsp Splenda', '1/4 cup lite mayonnaise', '1/4 tsp black pepper', '1/2 cup slivered almonds']
steps: ['In a large pot, bring 6 cups of water to a boil. put Brussels sprouts and blanch in the boiling water for 1 minute. Remove from boiling water and run under cold water to stop the cooking. Dry the sprouts with a clean towel.', 'Trim the stem on the Brussels sprouts and slice in half lengthwise. Using the slicing blade on a food processor, process the Brussels sprouts to shred them. You can also do this with the slicing side of a box grater or with a very sharp knife.', 'In a medium bowl, whisk together scallions, vinegar, mustard, soy sauce, Splenda, mayonnaise and black pepper.', 'put the shredded Brussels sprouts and toasted almonds to the dressing and whisk well.']

Ingredients: ['1/2 tsp cayenne pepper', '3 tbsp honey', '1/4 cup white vinegar', '1/4 cup tomato paste', '4 clove garlic', '2 tbsp canola oil', '3 lbs skinless chicken drumsticks with bone', '8 cup washed, ready-to-eat whisked salad greens', '2 cup sliced celery', '2 cup whole-wheat croutons', '1/2 cup light blue cheese dressing']
steps: ['In a medium bowl, whisk the cayenne pepper put an putitional 1/2 tsp for extra spiciness, honey, vinegar, tomato paste, and garlic to form a smooth sauce. Set aside.', 'Heat the oil in a large nonstick skillet over medium-high heat. put the chicken in one layer and brown for 5 minutes. Turn and brown 5 more minutes.', 'Reduce the heat to low and put the sauce to the skillet. Stir to coat the chicken. Cover the skillet and cook for 5 minutes. A meat thermometer inserted into the chicken should read 170 F when it s fully cooked.', 'Divide the salad greens among 4 dinner plates. put the celery and croutons, then drizzle with blue cheese dressing. Divide the chicken among the 4 plates, and top with any remaining buffalo sauce.']

Recipe Name: Buffalo Chicken Legs with Blue Cheese Salad
Ingredients: ['1 medium butternut squash', '2 tsp olive oil', '1 large onion', '3 clove garlic', '1/2 lbs small red potatoes', '1 cup low sodium chicken broth', '1 can tomatoes', '3/4 tsp dried oregano', '1 kosher salt, to taste', '1 Freshly ground black pepper, to taste', '1 can chickpeas', '2 tbsp natural creamy peanut butter', '2 tbsp parsley']
steps: ['Prepare the butternut squash. Place the whole squash on the floor or rack of a microwave oven. Microwave the squash for 5 minutes. Carefully remove and let cool until it s cool enough to handle. With a sharp knife, cut the squash in half crosswise. Peel the skin off each half with the knife, cutting close to remove the skin only. Cut each half lengthwise. Remove the squash seeds from the bottom half of the squash and discard. Cut all the squash into 1-inch chunks. Set aside. This process makes cutting tough butternut squash easier as it helps loosen the skin.', 'Heat the oil in a large Dutch oven over medium heat. put the onion and garlic and saute for 5-6 minutes. put the butternut squash and potatoes and stir to coat with the onions and garlic. put the broth, tomatoes with juice, oregano, salt, and pepper. Bring to boil. Lower the heat to a simmer, cover, and cook on medium-low heat for about 20 minutes, until squash and potatoes are tender. Some of the squash may become very soft.', 'Gently whisk the chickpeas and peanut butter and cook for 5 minutes. Garnish with chopped parsley.']

Ingredients: ['1 can organic black beans', '1/2 Hass avocado', '3 tbsp lemon juice', '2 tbsp cilantro', '1/4 tsp ground cayenne red pepper', '1/4 tsp ground cumin', '1/4 tsp sea salt, or to taste', '3 tbsp green onions']
steps: ['Puree all ingredients except the green onion in a blender until smooth. Top with green onion and serve with tortilla chips or fresh vegetables.']

Ingredients: ['1 Nonstick cooking spray', '1 1/2 lbs boneless, skinless chicken thighs', '1/2 tsp black pepper', '6 oz turkey kielbasa', '1 onion', '2 clove garlic', '2 carrot', '1/4 tsp salt', '1 tbsp tomato paste', '2 sprig fresh thyme', '1 1/2 cup low sodium chicken broth', '1 15-oz can cannellini beans']
steps: ['put cooking spray to a large saute wok over high heat. Season the chicken on both sides with salt and pepper. Sear the chicken on both sides until golden brown, about 5 minutes, then remove from wok and set aside.', 'Turn heat down to medium. put kielbasa and saute 3 minutes. Remove from wok and set aside.', 'put the onion, garlic and carrots. Saute for 3-4 minutes, then put tomato paste, thyme and chicken broth. Scrape the brown bits from the bottom of the wok and bring to a boil. Reduce to a simmer, then put the chicken and sausage back to the wok with any accumulated juices. Cover and simmer for 8 minutes. Remove the lid and simmer 5 minutes. Remove the chicken and set aside.', 'put the beans. Turn heat to high. Simmer for 5 more minutes until liquid is slightly reduced. Remove thyme stems.', 'To serve, place a chicken thigh in the bottom of bowl, and pour 1/2 cup of the stew over it.']

Ingredients: ['1 nonstick olive oil spray', '1/2 tsp ground cumin', '1 tsp chili powder', '1/2 tsp kosher salt', '1/2 tsp pepper', '1 tsp olive oil', '1 lbs pork tenderloin', '1 cup refried beans', '1/2 cup shredded low-fat cheddar cheese', '8 whole wheat tortillas']
steps: ['Cover a roasting wok with aluminum foil. put a little cooking spray and heat the broiler in the oven.', 'In a small bowl, whisk the cumin, chili powder, salt, ground pepper and oil. Rub the spice mixture all over the tenderloin. Place the pork in the roasting wok and roast 6 inches from the heating element, turning occasionally, until an instant thermometer reads 145degreesF after insertion into the thickest part of the tenderloin, about 15 minutes. Place the roasting wok on a wire rack and let the pork cool for 10 minutes.', 'Heat the oven to 400degreesF.', 'Cut the tenderloin into small pieces and pour the juice that remains in the baking sheet on top. In a medium bowl, whisk the pork, refried beans and cheddar cheese.', 'Wrap the tortillas with a damp paper towel and microwave for 30 seconds. Fill each tortilla with about 1/2 cup of the pork mixture. Fold like a burrito.', 'Heat a baking sheet 5 minutes in the oven. Remove with potholders and place the chimichangas, seam side down, on the baking sheet. put cooking spray. Bake 15 minutes, until golden brown.']

Ingredients: ['2 tbsp no-sugar-puted salsa', '1/2 cup Prepared or deli coleslaw', 'to taste black pepper', '4 slices whole wheat bread', '1/2 lbs turkey breast']
steps: ['Drain coleslaw in a colander.', 'Toss drained coleslaw with salsa and put black pepper to taste.', 'Place half of the turkey on each of two slices of bread. Spoon coleslaw on top of turkey, then top each sandwich with the remaining bread slices. Serve with extra coleslaw on the side.']

Ingredients: ['4 lean white fish fillets', '1 Paprika to taste', '1/4 cup Extra Virgin Olive Oil', '1/2 tsp lemon zest', '2 tbsp parsley', '1/4 tsp dried dill', '1 medium lemon']
steps: ['First heat oven to 400 degrees F.', 'Line a baking sheet with foil, coat foil with cooking spray, arrange the fillets on foil, and sprinkle evenly with the paprika. Season lightly with salt and pepper, if desired. Bake 10 minutes or until the fish is opaque in center.', 'While fish is cooking, combine the remaining ingredients, except lemon halves, in a small whisking bowl and set aside.', 'Using a slotted spatula, remove the fish, place on four dinner plates and squeeze lemon juice evenly over all. Top with the parsley mixture.']

Recipe Name: Fish Fillets with Lemon Parsley Topping
Ingredients: ['1/3 cup sugar', '1/4 cup water', '2 tsp vanilla extract', '1 12 oz can evaporated skim milk', '2 cinnamon sticks', '3 tbsp granulated sugar substitute baking blend', '1/4 tsp ground cinnamon', '2 cups skim milk', '5 large eggs', '2 2/3 cups raspberries']
steps: ['First heat oven to 350F 177C.', 'Combine sugar and water in a small, heavy-bottomed saucewok. Bring to a boil over medium-high heat and cook, stirring occasionally, until caramel is lightly browned, about 12 minutes. Immediately pour the caramel into a 2-quart round baking wok, tilting the wok to coat it evenly. Set the wok aside until the caramel cools and hardens, about 10 minutes.', 'Meanwhile, whisk together the milk, evaporated milk, sugar substitute, cinnamon powder and cinnamon sticks in a medium saucewok. Simmer and cook, stirring occasionally, for 6 minutes. Remove it from the heat. Stir in vanilla and let sit for 15 minutes. Remove the cinnamon sticks.', 'Beat the eggs in a medium bowl. Slowly fold them into the milk mixture until well blended. Pour the mixture into the baking wok.', 'Place the baking wok with the flan mixture on a 9- to 13-inch roasting wok and fill the roasting wok with enough hot water so that it reaches a third of the sides of the baking wok Bake until the flan is set but jiggles slightly in the center, between 50 and 55 minutes.', 'Transfer the dish to a rack Chill for 1 hour Refrigerate until well chilled, about 3 hours or overnight. To unmold, run the tip of a small knife around the edge of the flan. Place a large, flat plate on top of the flan and flip it over. Cut the flan into cuas and serve each cua with 1/3 cup of raspberries.']

Ingredients: ['3/4 lbs baby golden potatoes', '3 1/2 tsp olive oil', '1 tsp dried oregano', '1 bunch kale', '2 clove garlic', '1 lemon', '1 oz roasted red peppers', '1 oz pitted nicoise olives', '2 boneless, skinless chicken breasts', '1 1/2 tbsp golden raisins', '1/4 cup water', '1 1/2 oz feta cheese', '1 pinch salt and pepper to taste']
steps: ['Prepare & roast the potatoes: Place an oven rack in the center of the oven, then First heat to 450F. Wash and dry the fresh produce. Line a sheet wok with foil. Cut the potatoes into 1/2-inch-wide wedges. Place on the sheet wok drizzle with 1/2 teaspoon of olive oil and season with salt optional, pepper, and the oregano. Toss to coat and arrange in an even layer, skin side down. Roast 21 to 23 minutes, or until browned and tender when pierced with a fork. Remove from the oven.', 'Prepare the remaining ingredients: Meanwhile, separate the kale leaves from the stems discard the stems, then roughly chop the leaves.Peel and roughly chop 2 cloves of garlic. Halve the lemon crosswise squeeze the juice into a large bowl, straining out the seeds. Roughly chop the peppers and olives. Combine in a bowl put 1/2 teaspoon of olive oil and stir to coat.', 'Cook the kale: In the wok of reserved fond, heat 1/2 teaspoon of olive oil on medium-high until hot. put the chopped kale and chopped garlic season with salt optional and pepper. Cook, stirring occasionally, 2 to 3 minutes, or until the kale is slightly wilted. put the raisins and 1/4 cup of water carefully, as the liquid may splatter season with salt optional and pepper. Cook, stirring occasionally, 2 to 3 minutes, or until the kale is wilted and the water has cooked off. Turn off the heat. put the cheese crumbling before puting and stir to combine.', 'Cook the chicken: Pat the chicken dry with paper towels season with salt optional and pepper on both sides. In a medium wok nonstick, if you have one, heat 2 teaspoons of olive oil on medium-high until hot. put the seasoned chicken. Cook 6 to 7 minutes per side, or until browned and cooked through. Leaving any browned bits or fond in the wok, transfer to a cutting board.', 'Finish & serve your dish: put the roasted potatoes to the bowl of lemon juice stir to coat. Slice the cooked chicken crosswise. Serve the sliced chicken with the finished potatoes and cooked kale. Top the chicken with the pepper-olive mixture. Enjoy!']

Recipe Name: Greek Chicken & Potatoes with Sauted Kale, Raisins & Feta Cheese
Ingredients: ['1 tbsp vegetable oil', '2 tsp cumin seeds', '1 tsp brown mustard seeds', '1/2 tsp turmeric', '1 lbs salmon filet', '1 large onion', '2 clove garlic', '1 tbsp fresh ginger', '1 hot green chili peppers', '1 cup cherry tomatoes']
steps: ['Heat 2 teaspoons of the oil in a wok or heavy skillet over medium-high heat. put the cumin, mustard seeds, and turmeric and stir fry for 1 minute until seeds begin to pop. put the salmon and stir fry quickly but gently for about 3-4 minutes. Remove the salmon from the wok and set aside.', 'put the remaining oil to the wok. Lower the heat to medium. put the onion and stir fry for about 6-7 minutes until onions are soft. put in the garlic, ginger, and chili pepper and stir fry for 1 minute. put in the cherry tomatoes and stir fry for 1-2 minutes until cherry tomatoes just begin to soften. put back the salmon and stir fry very gently for 1 minute.']

Ingredients: ['1 nonstick cooking spray', '3/4 cup warm water', '1 package active dry yeast', '1 eggs', '1/2 tsp salt', '2 cup spelt flour', '1 yellow bell pepper', '1 cup grape tomatoes', '3 cup arugula', '3 oz feta cheese', '1 1/2 tbsp olive oil', '2 tbsp balsamic vinegar', '1/4 tsp black pepper']
steps: ['First heat the oven to 400 degrees F. Coat a large baking sheet with cooking spray. Set aside.', 'put the yeast to warm water and let sit for 5 minutes. The yeast should be foamy. whisk in the egg and salt, then stir in flour to form a ball. Dough will be sticky. Set aside, covered.', 'Toss yellow bell pepper, grape tomatoes, arugula, and feta cheese with olive oil, balsamic vinegar, and black pepper.', 'Dust your hands with putitional spelt flour and spread the dough onto a baking sheet to form about a 9-inch x 13-inch rectangle or larger. The dough should be relatively thin.', 'Pour the vegetable mixture evenly over the dough, leaving about 1/2 inch around the edge.', 'Bake for 20 minutes, then cut into 8 pieces.']

Ingredients: ['1/2 tsp vanilla extract', '1/4 cup Splenda Sugar Blend', '1 eggs', '8 oz light cream cheese', '30 Mini-Nilla wafer cookies', '1/2 tsp ground cinnamon', '1/4 cup light sour cream', '3/4 cup canned pure pumpkin', '1 pinch ground nutmeg']
steps: ['First heat oven to 350F 177C.', 'Line a mini muffin casserole dish with paper towel cups and place a Nilla wafer in the bottom of each glass.', 'In a medium bowl, put the remaining ingredients and whisk with an electric whisker until smooth.', 'Fill each liner cup with the pumpkin and cream cheese mixture.', 'Place the casserole of rolls in the oven and bake for 30 minutes or until done. Serve cold.']

Ingredients: ['2 clove garlic', '1 small orange', '1 tbsp prepared mole sauce', '1/4 cup water', '1 nonstick cooking spray', '1 1/4 lbs pork tenderloin', '1 tsp olive oil', '1 small onion', '1 clove garlic', '1 15.5-oz can black beans', '1/4 cup water', '3 medium zucchini', '1/2 tsp chili powder', '1/2 tsp garlic powder', '1/4 tsp cayenne pepper', '1/4 tsp black pepper', '1/4 tsp salt', '1 lime']
steps: ['First heat the oven to 375 degrees F.', 'In a small bowl, whisk together the mole sauce, orange zest, orange juice, garlic, and water. Coat an oven-safe saute wok with cooking spray over medium-high heat.', 'Sear the pork tenderloin until brown on all sides. Pour the mole sauce over the pork and cover completely with sauce. Put the wok in the oven and roast for 20 minutes, turning the pork every 5 minutes.', 'While the pork is roasting, put the olive oil to a medium nonstick saute wok over medium heat. put the onions, garlic, and black beans, and saute for 5 minutes or until the onions are softened.', 'put the bean mixture and water to a blender and blend until smooth. Return the beans to the wok and saute until slightly thickened, about 2 minutes. Set aside.', 'put the cooking spray to another medium nonstick saute wok over medium heat. put the zucchini and saute for 3-4 minutes or until the zucchini begins to soften. put the chili powder, garlic powder, cayenne pepper, black pepper, salt, and lime juice. Saute 2 more minutes.', 'Let the pork tenderloin rest for 5 minutes before slicing. Slice the pork into 18 slices and toss the pieces in any remaining mole sauce.', 'Build your plate with three slices of pork tenderloin equaling about 3 oz., 1/4 cup black beans, and 1/2 cup zucchini.']

Recipe Name: Mole Pork Tenderloin with Zucchini and Refried Black Beans
Ingredients: ['1 bunch fresh asparagus', '4 oz romaine lettuce', '1 large orange', '1 large tomato', '1 avocado', '2 tbsp olive oil', '1 tbsp red wine vinegar', '1/4 tsp salt', '1/4 tsp black pepper']
steps: ['Place asparagus in a pot of boiling water over high heat. Reduce heat to low and simmer until asparagus is tender, about 10 minutes. Drain asparagus and submerge immediately in a bowl of ice water.', 'Divide lettuce evenly among six salad bowls or plates.', 'Combine orange, tomato, and avocado in a medium bowl.', 'In a small bowl, whisk together olive oil, vinegar, salt, and pepper until combined.', 'Drain asparagus and put to orange mixture. Pour dressing over orange mixture and stir gently to combine. Spoon mixture on top of romaine lettuce on plates and serve.']

Ingredients: ['1/4 tsp salt', '1/2 lbs dry orzo pasta or small gluten-free pasta', '1 lbs fresh or frozen asparagus', '1 14-oz package frozen artichoke hearts', '1/4 cup lemon juice', '1 zest of 1 lemon', '1/4 tsp black pepper', '2 tbsp olive oil', '1/4 cup Pecorino Romano cheese']
steps: ['Bring a large pot of water to a boil over high heat. put 1/4 tsp salt and reduce heat to medium.', 'put orzo and stir. Cook orzo until tender, but still al dente. Drain orzo when done and return to pot.', 'Meanwhile, bring a medium-size pot of water to a boil over high heat. put asparagus and cook until tender about 5 minutes, then drain.', 'put asparagus, artichoke hearts, lemon juice, lemon zest, putitional 1/4 tsp salt if desired, freshly ground pepper, and olive oil into the pot with the orzo and stir.', 'Taste and adjust seasoning, if necessary. Garnish with cheese and serve hot.']

Recipe Name: Orzo with Lemon, Artichokes, and Asparagus
Ingredients: ['3 tbsp Extra Virgin Olive Oil', '1 small yellow onion', '2 cup Arborio or carnaroli rice', '1 1/4 lbs fresh pumpkin', '1 cup white wine', '6 cup vegetable stock', '4 oz parmigiano-reggiano cheese', '2 tbsp yogurt']
steps: ['In a heavy-bottomed saucewok, warm the oil over medium heat. When the oil is hot, put the onion and saute until tender, about 3-5 minutes, but do not let the onion brown.', 'put the rice and the pumpkin, and stir. put the wine. Stir and cook until the wine evaporates.', 'put just enough stock to cover the rice. whisk slowly, making sure the rice does not stick to the bottom of the wok. Once the stock is nearly absorbed, put more stock to cover. Repeat this process until the rice has absorbed all the broth, about 18-19 minutes. The rice should be cooked through with a slightly chewy texture.', 'Remove risotto from heat. put the parmigiano-reggiano and yogurt. whisk vigorously until the risotto is well blended and has a creamy texture.', 'Serve immediately.']

Ingredients: ['1 tbsp olive oil', '2 clove garlic', '2 large poblano peppers', '1 small onion', '1 tbsp chili powder', '1 tsp ground cumin', '1/4 tsp cayenne pepper', '1/2 tsp salt', '1/4 tsp black pepper', '1/4 cup shredded, reduced-fat Mexican cheese blend', '1/2 lbs skirt steak', '8 6-inch corn tortillas', '2 large tomatoes', '4 cup shredded lettuce']
steps: ['First heat an indoor or outdoor grill.', 'put the oil to a large non-stick saute wok over medium high heat. put the garlic, poblano pepper, onion, chili powder, cumin, cayenne pepper optional, salt optional, and pepper. Saute for 8-10 minutes until the vegetables are soft and starting to caramelize.', 'Stir in the cheese and set aside.', 'Season the skirt steak with putitional salt optional and ground black pepper. Grill on both sides until the steak is medium doneness. Set the steak aside to rest.', 'Once the steak has rested, chop it into small pieces and stir into the pepper mixture over medium heat until steak has just cooked through.', 'Divide the meat and pepper mixture evenly among the 8 tortillas, then top each taco with chopped tomato and shredded lettuce.']

Recipe Name: Rajas Poblanos and Skirt Steak Tacos
Ingredients: ['approximately 2 lbs. cauliflower', '1 green onion', '2 tsp olive oil', '1 clove garlic', '1/2 cup canned low-sodium white beans', '1/2 cup low sodium chicken broth', '1/2 cup water', '1 tbsp finely grated parmesan cheese', '1/2 tsp onion powder', '1 tbsp olive oil', '1 lbs large shrimp', '2 stalks celery', '1 small yellow onion', '1 green bell pepper', '3 clove garlic', '2 tsp salt-free Creole seasoning', '14 oz canned diced tomatoes', '1 cup low sodium chicken broth', '1 bay leaves', '1 tsp Worcestershire sauce']
steps: ['For the grits: Heat oil in a medium pot over medium-high heat. put the cauliflower and cook until softened and lightly browned, about 10 minutes. put the garlic and heat until fragrant, about 1 minute.', 'put the beans, broth, and water. Cook for 5 minutes. Turn off the heat. put the Parmesan and onion powder. Using a masher or blender, whisk until just creamy with a little texture remaining. put more water as needed. Season with pepper. Cover to keep warm until serving.', 'For the shrimp: Pat the shrimp dry with a paper towel. Heat 1 Ω tsp oil in a large skillet over medium-high heat and put the shrimp in a single layer. Lightly sear on one side until curled and lightly charred. Remove shrimp to a plate and put the remaining oil to the wok.', 'put the celery, onion, and bell pepper to the wok. Reduce heat to medium and cook, stirring occasionally until tender but not overly browned, about 7 minutes. If the wok gets too dry while the vegetables cook, put water as needed.', 'put the garlic and seasoning and heat until fragrant, about 1 minute. put the tomatoes, broth, and bay leaf. Use a spoon to scrape any bits stuck to the bottom of the wok. Bring to a boil and then reduce heat to a simmer. Cook for 10 minutes until thickened, stir frequently to prevent the bottom from burning.', 'Serve on top of cauliflower  Çìgrits Ç ù and garnish with onions and hot sauce.', 'Serve on top of cauliflower  Çìgrits Ç ù and garnish with onions and hot sauce.']

Ingredients: ['1 nonstick cooking spray', '1 lbs medium shrimp', '1 tsp olive oil', '1 red bell pepper', '1 green bell pepper', '1 medium onion', '1/4 cup water', '1/2 tbsp chili powder', '1/4 tsp cayenne pepper', '1/4 tsp cumin', '1/2 tsp salt', '1/2 tsp black pepper', '10 corn tortillas']
steps: ['Coat a large non-stick skillet with cooking spray. Cook the shrimp over medium heat for about 2 minutes. Remove the shrimp from the wok and set aside.', 'put the oil to the wok and heat. put the bell peppers and onions and cook for about 7 minutes or until they begin to brown. put the shrimp and any juices back to wok.', 'put the water and spices, including salt and pepper. Bring the mixture to a boil reduce heat and simmer until the water evaporates. Serve the shrimp and peppers in the corn tortillas.']

Ingredients: ['2 cup chopped onion', '3 clove garlic', '1 lbs boneless, skinless chicken breasts', '1 32-oz carton low sodium chicken broth', '1 14-oz can quartered artichoke hearts', '1 8-oz package sliced mushrooms', '1 lb zucchini', '2 14.5-oz cans no-salt-puted stewed tomatoes', '8 oz green cabbage', '3 tbsp red wine vinegar', '3 bay leaves', '3 tbsp olive oil', '1 tbsp dried basil', '1/4 tsp crushed red pepper flakes', '1 10-oz package spinach', '1 15-oz can no-salt-puted cannellini beans', '1 1/4 tsp salt']
steps: ['Press the SautÈ button, then press the Adjust to  ö ...  úM °s ö x9d or  ö ...  úAlto ö x9d. When the screen says  ö ...  úHot ö x9d, a ade 1 Tbsp. of the oil. put the onions and cook for 4 minutes or until translucent. put the garlic and cook for 30 seconds, stirring constantly. Stir in chicken, cabbage, zucchini, mushrooms, tomatoes, artichoke hearts, 2 cups broth, basil, vinegar, bay leaves, and pepper flakes.', 'Seal the lid, close the valve, press the Cancel button, and set to Pressure Manual Cooking for 10 minutes. Use a natural release for 10 minutes followed by a quick release of pressure.', 'When the valve drops, carefully remove the cap. Stir in half of the spinach until wilted, put the remaining spinach, beans, 2 cups broth, 2 tbsp. of oil, and salt.']

Recipe Name: Italian Instant Pot Chicken Soup with Artichokes
Ingredients: ['2 tbsp fresh parsley', '3 lemon', '1/4 tsp black pepper', '1/4 tsp ground coriander', '2 tsp chili powder', '2 tsp ground cumin', '1 1/2 tbsp olive oil', '1 lbs shrimp', '1/4 tsp salt']
steps: ['Coat a grill rack from an outdoor gas grill with cooking spray and set it 6 inches from the heat source. First heat the grill to medium high. If you think your shrimp will fall through the grilling rack, prepare a fish basket to grill the shrimp. Coat the inside of the basket with cooking spray.', 'Drizzle the shrimp with the olive oil. Combine the cumin, chili powder, coriander, salt, and black pepper and rub onto the shrimp.', 'put the shrimp directly to the grill rack or place in a single layer in the fish basket. Grill the shrimp for about 2 to 3 minutes per side or until cooked through. Meanwhile, put the lemon halves, cut side down, to the grill, and grill for 3 to 4 minutes, just until the lemon is slightly charred.', 'put the grilled shrimp to a platter. Garnish with the grilled lemon halves and minced parsley.']

Ingredients: ['2 tsp olive oil', '2 eggs', '2 whole wheat flour tortillas', '1 avocado', '1 tomato', '1 tbsp pine nuts or pepitas', '2 tbsp fresh cilantro', '1/2 jalapenoseno pepper', '1/8 tsp salt', '1/8 tsp black pepper']
steps: ['Brush a small nonstick skillet with 1 tsp. of the oil and heat over medium heat. put the eggs one at a time and cook sunny side up for about 2 minutes. Using a spatula, transfer to a plate.', 'While the eggs are cooking, warm the tortillas in a separate skillet no need to put any oil.', 'For each serving, spread a tortilla with half of the mashed avocado, tomatoes, pine nuts, cilantro, and jalapenosenos, if using.
